5003.name: antimage_mana_break
5003.desc_loc: Burns an opponent's mana on each attack.  Mana Break deals %percent_damage_per_burn%%% of the mana burned as damage to the target. Mana Break has %illusion_percentage%%% effect if caused by illusions.
5003.lore_loc: A modified technique of the Turstarkuri monks' peaceful ways is to turn magical energies on their owner.

5004.name: antimage_blink
5004.desc_loc: Short distance teleportation that allows Anti-Mage to move in and out of combat.
5004.lore_loc: In his encounter with the Dead Gods, Anti-Mage learned the value of being elusive.
notes_loc: You can use Blink to dodge incoming projectiles.
5004.shard_loc: Increases range by 300 and reduces cooldown by 2.

7314.name: antimage_counterspell
7314.desc_loc: Passively grants you magic resistance. Can be activated to create an anti-magic shell around you that sends any targeted spells back towards enemies instead of affecting you.
7314.lore_loc: With the proper focus, Anti-Mage turns innate resistance into calculated retaliation.
7314.shard_loc: Successful Counterspell creates an illusion attacking the caster for 5 seconds. Removes Counterspell manacost.

543.name: antimage_mana_overload
543.desc_loc: Blinks an illusion at the target enemy or location and attack them for 7 seconds. Counterspell is replicated on the Blink Fragment illusion.

5006.name: antimage_mana_void
5006.desc_loc: For each point of mana missing by the target unit, damage is dealt to it and surrounding enemies.  The main target is also mini-stunned.
5006.lore_loc: After bringing enemies to their knees, Anti-Mage punishes them for their use of the arcane arts.
notes_loc: Damage is calculated based on the primary target's mana, but applied to all enemies within the area of effect.

5007.name: axe_berserkers_call
5007.desc_loc: Axe taunts nearby enemy units, forcing them to attack him, while he gains bonus armor during the duration.
5007.lore_loc: Mogul Khan's warcry taunts opponents into engaging in an unconquerable battle with the Axe.
5007.scepter_loc:
Berserker's Call applies Battle Hunger to affected units. Battle Hunger also reduces enemy armor by 7 and grants Axe 7 armor per affected target. 

Reduces Berserker's Call cooldown by 3.

5008.name: axe_battle_hunger
5008.desc_loc: Enrages an enemy unit, causing it to be slowed and take damage over time until it kills another unit or the duration ends. Axe gains movement speed for each unit affected with Battle Hunger, half speed from creeps.
5008.lore_loc: Ordinary heroes cannot withstand Mogul Khan's rage for battle, such that it injures them until it is satisfied.
notes_loc: Destroying buildings will also remove the debuff.

5009.name: axe_counter_helix
5009.desc_loc: When attacked, Axe has a chance to perform a helix counter attack, dealing pure damage to all nearby enemies.
5009.lore_loc: Axe is the only reinforcement this army needs.
notes_loc: Counter Helix triggers when the attack hits.
5009.shard_loc: Causes Axe's attacks to have a chance to proc a Counter Helix. Attack procs ignore Counter Helix cooldown. Increases attack speed by 35 and proc chance by 10%.

5010.name: axe_culling_blade
5010.desc_loc: Axe spots a weakness and strikes, instantly killing an enemy unit with low health, or dealing moderate damage otherwise. When an enemy hero is killed with Culling Blade, its cooldown is reset, and Axe and nearby allied units gain bonus movement speed.
5010.lore_loc: Mogul Khan is the embodiment of battle and fury, launching into a gruesome fatality against those who dare engage the Axe in combat.

5012.name: bane_enfeeble
5012.desc_loc: Lowers the enemy's total attack damage, cast speed, and regeneration.
5012.lore_loc: Each tendril of fear that Atropos weaves increases the vulnerability of his victims to arcane and unknown arts.

5011.name: bane_brain_sap
5011.desc_loc: Feasts on the vital energies of an enemy unit, healing Bane and dealing damage.
5011.lore_loc: Atropos finds no greater pleasure than to harvest the fear he creates.
5011.shard_loc: Causes Brain Sap to become a 550 AoE spell. Secondary targets only heal for 25%.

5014.name: bane_nightmare
5014.desc_loc: Puts the target enemy or friendly Hero to sleep. Sleeping units are awakened when damaged. If the target was directly attacked, the Nightmare passes to the attacking unit. Bane can attack nightmared targets freely.
5014.lore_loc: A stolen prowess from the goddess Nyctasha is to put his prey into forever sleep.
notes_loc: In the first second of Nightmare, the unit is invulnerable.
Bane can wake himself from Nightmare.
On cast, replaced with Nightmare End: Ends all ongoing Nightmares on any affected units.

5013.name: bane_fiends_grip
5013.desc_loc: CHANNELED - Grips an enemy unit, disabling it and causing heavy damage over time, while stealing mana every %fiend_grip_tick_interval% seconds based on the unit's maximum mana.
5013.lore_loc: Victims of Atropos are frequently torn apart by vivid conjurations of their own nightmares.
notes_loc: Fiend's Grip will disable and drain mana from Spell Immune units, but not damage them.
5013.scepter_loc: Reduces Fiend's Grip cooldown by 45 seconds. Fiend's Grip now creates two uncontrollable illusions that are also channeling Fiend's Grip on the target. Illusions takes 700%% incoming damage and immediately dies if they are interrupted. Damage does not stack.

5015.name: bloodseeker_bloodrage
5015.desc_loc: Drives Bloodseeker into a bloodthirsty rage which causes him to attack faster and deal more spell damage at the cost of a percentage of his health per second. Provides half attack speed to allied heroes.
5015.lore_loc: Strygwyr shares his animalistic thirst for bloodshed.
notes_loc: Bloodrage can be cast on yourself or an enemy units.
5015.shard_loc: Bloodrage attacks now deal 2% of the target’s max health as pure damage and heals Bloodseeker for that amount. Only works for Bloodseeker.

5016.name: bloodseeker_blood_bath
5016.desc_loc: Bloodseeker baptizes an area in sacred blood. After %delay_plus_castpoint_tooltip% seconds the ritual completes, causing any enemies caught in the area to take damage and become silenced.
5016.lore_loc: The Flayed Twins are ever willing to aid those who spill blood upon the field of battle.
notes_loc: Total time is a %delay% second delay plus a %abilitycastpoint% second cast time.

5017.name: bloodseeker_thirst
5017.desc_loc: Bloodseeker is invigorated by the wounds of his enemies, restoring some life when he kills an enemy unit. Also gains bonus movement speed when an enemy hero's health falls below %min_bonus_pct%%%, with the bonuses increasing as their health falls further. If an enemy hero's health falls below %invis_threshold_pct%%%, he will also gain vision and True Sight of that hero. Bonuses stack per hero. Unlocks max movement speed for Bloodseeker.
5017.lore_loc: Strygwyr becomes frenzied when blood is spilled.
notes_loc: Not triggered by Illusions.
Max movement speed and attack speed bonuses occur when an enemy's health is at or below %max_bonus_pct%%%.
Effects linger for %linger_duration% seconds if a target dies.

5018.name: bloodseeker_rupture
5018.desc_loc: Causes an enemy unit's skin to rupture, dealing initial damage based on its current health. If the unit moves, it takes damage based on the distance moved.  The damage is dealt through spell immunity.
5018.lore_loc: When the Bloodseeker hunts you, injuries become fatalities.
5018.scepter_loc: Grants Bloodseeker two charges of Rupture

5126.name: crystal_maiden_crystal_nova
5126.desc_loc: A burst of damaging frost slows enemy movement and attack rate in the targeted area.
5126.lore_loc: The air temperature around Rylai drops rapidly, chilling all around her to the core.

5127.name: crystal_maiden_frostbite
5127.desc_loc: Encases an enemy unit in ice, prohibiting movement and attack, while dealing damage over time. Lasts %creep_duration% seconds on creeps level 6 or lower.
5127.lore_loc: Rylai channels winds from the Blueheart Glacier, imprisoning attackers in thick blocks of ice.
notes_loc: Frostbite is considered a root.

5128.name: crystal_maiden_brilliance_aura
5128.desc_loc: Gives additional mana regeneration to all friendly units on the map. This bonus is increased for Crystal Maiden.
5128.lore_loc: Cold temperatures promote the essence of magic, causing Rylai's presence to allow spell usage in abundance.

5129.name: crystal_maiden_freezing_field
5129.desc_loc: CHANNELED - Surrounds Crystal Maiden with random icy explosions that slow enemies and deal massive damage. Grants bonus armor while channeling. Lasts %abilitychanneltime% seconds.
5129.lore_loc: Once the place of her exile, Icewrack has become an anchor for Rylai's frigid onslaught.
notes_loc: The slow is applied on all enemies in the radius, even if they aren't hit by an explosion (lasts %slow_duration% second).
Explosions occur every %explosion_interval% seconds.
5129.shard_loc: Allows you to move, cast and attack during Freezing Field. Can still be interrupted by enemies. You move 75% slower during this.
5129.scepter_loc: Applies Frostbite to any unit that has been standing in the Freezing Field for over a set amount of time.

5019.name: drow_ranger_frost_arrows
5019.desc_loc: Adds a freezing effect to Drow's attacks, slowing enemy movement and dealing bonus damage.  Slow lasts %abilityduration% seconds.
5019.lore_loc: Ice-encased arrows pierce the silence, chilling their victims to the core.
notes_loc: The slow duration is refreshed on successive casts.
5019.shard_loc: Frost Arrows now apply a Hypothermia stack to enemy heroes, reducing their regeneration by 10% per stack. Increases damage by 5 per stack. Lasts 7 seconds. If an enemy hero dies with Hypothermia stacks, they burst and deal 60 magic damage per stack and 40%% slow for 2 seconds to enemies within 650 radius. Max Stacks: 7

5632.name: drow_ranger_wave_of_silence
5632.desc_loc: Releases a wave that silences and knocks back enemy units. Knockback distance is relative to how close they are to Drow.
5632.lore_loc: Traxex is rather fond of the tranquility of physical combat, calling on her Drow heritage to end the incantations of opposing magi.

343.name: drow_ranger_multishot
343.desc_loc: Channeling. Drow releases a flurry of arrows in continuous salvos, hitting enemies for extra damage and applying longer duration Frost Arrows. Lasts up to %abilitychanneltime% seconds.
343.lore_loc: In the ranger's youth, learning to fire multiple arrows at once was considered a distracting frivolity. In the war of the Ancients, such technique has become strange necessity.

5022.name: drow_ranger_marksmanship
5022.desc_loc: Drow's experiences in battle grant her a chance to launch arrows with incredible accuracy and effectiveness. Pierces through the enemy's defenses, ignoring their base armor. Grants Drow and nearby ranged heroes with bonus agility based on Drow's current agility. This ability is disabled if there is an enemy hero within %disable_range% range.
5022.lore_loc: The Drow Ranger is the epitome of archery prowess.
notes_loc: Marksmanship procs have true strike.
5022.scepter_loc: Causes Drow Ranger's attacks to splinter on the target, hitting nearby units with normal attacks that deal reduced damage.

5023.name: earthshaker_fissure
5023.desc_loc: Slams the ground with a mighty totem, creating an impassable ridge of stone while stunning and damaging enemy units along its line.
5023.lore_loc: The Nishian totem splits the world to its core with tectonic force.
notes_loc: Creeps will wait for Fissure to disappear. They will not attempt to walk around it.
Fissure is not blocked by Linken's Sphere.
5023.shard_loc: Reduces Fissure cooldown by 2 seconds and allows Earthshaker to walk on it. When he casts any ability, an Aftershock is released along its path that stuns for half the duration.

5024.name: earthshaker_enchant_totem
5024.desc_loc: Empowers Earthshaker's totem, causing it to deal extra damage and have %bonus_attack_range% bonus attack range on the next attack.
5024.lore_loc: Raigor's gorilla strength can destroy mountains.
notes_loc: Bonus damage is based on base damage and that given by primary attribute.
Self-cast with Scepter will make it behave in the non-Scepter form, without jumping.
5024.scepter_loc: Enchant Totem becomes a %distance_scepter% range ground target ability, causing Earthshaker to jump in the air and land at the target spot, casting Enchant Totem there.  Self-casting the ability will behave in the original form, without jumping. Grants Enchant Totem a 40%% cleave hit.

5025.name: earthshaker_aftershock
5025.desc_loc: Causes the earth to shake underfoot, adding additional damage and stuns to nearby enemy units when Earthshaker casts his abilities.
5025.lore_loc: The earth trembles beneath the mighty footsteps of Raigor.
notes_loc: Using items does not trigger Aftershock.

5026.name: earthshaker_echo_slam
5026.desc_loc: Shockwaves travel through the ground, damaging enemy units.  Each enemy hit causes an echo to damage nearby units. Real heroes cause two echoes.
5026.lore_loc: Tectonic plates crack, mountains fold, and foes are crushed by the Echo Slam.

5028.name: juggernaut_blade_fury
5028.desc_loc:
Causes a bladestorm of destructive force around Juggernaut, rendering him immune to magic and dealing damage to nearby enemy units. 

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
5028.lore_loc: Yurnero's renowned katana techniques are feared by warriors and sorcerors alike.
notes_loc: You can use items during Blade Fury.
Juggernaut can still perform attacks while in Blade Fury. However, only units that are not affected by Blade Fury, such as wards or structures, will take damage from these attacks.
5028.shard_loc: Increases movement speed during Blade Fury by 100 and attacks a random nearby unit once per second dealing 75% damage.

5029.name: juggernaut_healing_ward
5029.desc_loc: Summons a Healing Ward which heals all nearby allied units, based on their max health.  The Healing Ward moves at %healing_ward_movespeed_tooltip% movement speed after being summoned.  Lasts %abilityduration% seconds.
5029.lore_loc: Of the rituals learned at the Isle of Masks, tending wounds with a bit of voodoo magic has proven to be quite useful.
notes_loc: The healing ward can be controlled.
Multiple healing wards do not stack.

5027.name: juggernaut_blade_dance
5027.desc_loc: Gives Juggernaut a chance to deal critical damage on each attack.
5027.lore_loc: The last remnant of his heritage's commitment to bladework, Yurnero ensures that the style is remembered.

419.name: juggernaut_swift_slash
419.desc_loc: Performs a mini Omnislash for a short duration.

5030.name: juggernaut_omni_slash
5030.desc_loc: Juggernaut leaps towards the target enemy units, and then slashes the target and other nearby enemy units at an increased attack rate. Juggernaut is invulnerable for the duration.
5030.lore_loc: 'The fruits of discipline; with practice comes strength.'
notes_loc: You can use items during Omnislash.
Can target Spell Immune units.
Omnislash applies a basic dispel to Juggernaut on cast.

5051.name: mirana_starfall
5051.desc_loc: Calls down a wave of meteors to damage nearby enemy units. The closest enemy unit to Mirana in a %starfall_secondary_radius% radius will be struck a second time for %secondary_starfall_damage_percent%%% of the damage.
5051.lore_loc: The Goddess breaks the strata to empower her Princess in the time of need.
notes_loc: Starstorm is not blocked by Linken's Sphere.
Starstorm cannot hit invisible units.
Starstorm will choose a new target for the second star if the first died before impact.

5048.name: mirana_arrow
5048.desc_loc: Fires a long-range arrow with deadly precision, which stuns and damages the first enemy unit it strikes. The stun duration ranges from %arrow_min_stun% to %arrow_max_stun% seconds, with bonus damage up to %arrow_bonus_damage% added, based on the distance the arrow travels to its target. Instantly kills the first non-ancient creep it hits.
5048.lore_loc: Lunar energies make the Princess of the Moon's arrows more deadly than most.
notes_loc: For every 150 distance the arrow travels, the stun duration upon impact increases by 0.5 seconds, and the bonus damage added increases by 14.
Sacred Arrow can hit invisible units.
5048.scepter_loc: Causes Sacred Arrow to release a Starstorm on enemies within 500 AoE along the travel path of the primary arrow, releasing a second starfall that deals 50% damage to the impacted unit.

5050.name: mirana_leap
5050.desc_loc: Mirana leaps forward into battle, empowering herself with a ferocious roar that grants bonus attack and movement speed. Speed bonus lasts %leap_bonus_duration% seconds.
5050.lore_loc: None can fail to recognize Mirana's iconic white beast in the heat of battle.
5050.shard_loc: Grants +1 Leap Charge. Leap buff grants Mirana 1.5x Critical Strike attacks for its duration.

5049.name: mirana_invis
5049.desc_loc: Turns Mirana and all allied heroes invisible and grants bonus movement speed. If a hero is revealed, invisibility will restore after the fade delay as long as Moonlight Shadow's duration has not expired.
5049.lore_loc: Her tenure with Selemene allows Mirana to eclipse the ground, wrapping her allies in a cloak of shadows.
notes_loc: Units affected will not auto attack enemies.
Spell Immune allies will be affected.

6242.name: special_bonus_unique_mirana_2
6242.desc_loc: The extra arrows are launched in a cone shape, 30 degrees to the left and right of the original arrow, and cannot hit the same target.

5059.name: nevermore_shadowraze1
5059.desc_loc: Shadow Fiend razes the ground directly in front of him, dealing damage to enemy units in the area. Adds a stacking damage amplifier on the target that causes the enemy to take bonus Shadow Raze damage per stack.
notes_loc: Stack duration refreshes on stack gain.

5062.name: nevermore_necromastery
5062.desc_loc: Shadow Fiend steals the soul from units he kills, gaining bonus damage. On death, he releases 40% of them from bondage.
5062.lore_loc: Harvested souls swirl in and out of the Abysm, empowering the Shadow Fiend to increase the size of his collection.
notes_loc: Denies and neutral creeps also provide bonus damage through Necromastery.

5063.name: nevermore_dark_lord
5063.desc_loc: Shadow Fiend's presence reduces the armor of nearby enemies.
5063.lore_loc: Even being near Nevermore eats away at one's soul.
notes_loc: Stacks fully with other armor reduction abilities and aura.
5063.shard_loc: Lowers nearby enemy magic resistance by 14%%.

5064.name: nevermore_requiem
5064.desc_loc:
Shadow Fiend gathers his captured souls to release them as lines of demonic energy. Units near Shadow Fiend when the souls are released can be damaged by several lines of energy. Any unit damaged by Requiem of Souls will be feared and have its movement speed reduced for %requiem_slow_duration% seconds for each line hit. Lines of energy are created for every soul captured through Necromastery.

Requiem of Souls is automatically cast whenever Shadow Fiend dies, regardless of its cooldown.
5064.lore_loc: The captured souls of those past slain are released to ravage their former allies.
notes_loc: One line is generated from Shadow Fiend for every %requiem_soul_conversion% souls in his possession, for a maximum of 18 lines (23 lines with Scepter).
The movement reductions from Requiem of Souls go through spell immunity.
Fear and movement slow do not apply when if the Requiem was released on death.
5064.scepter_loc: Increases Necromastery Max Souls and causes Requiem of Souls to return back to Shadow Fiend. The wave back to Shadow Fiend deals less damage, but heals Shadow Fiend for all the damage it dealt.

5052.name: morphling_waveform
5052.desc_loc: Morphling dissolves into liquid and surges forward, damaging enemy units in his path.  Morphling is invulnerable during Waveform.
5052.lore_loc: A torrential flood takes enemies by force.

5053.name: morphling_adaptive_strike_agi
5053.desc_loc:
Launches a surge of water toward an enemy unit, dealing base damage plus additional damage based on Morphling's agility times a multiplier.  If Morphling's agility is 50% higher than strength, the maximum agility multiplier is used. 

 Also puts Adaptive Strike (Strength) on a %shared_cooldown% second cooldown.
5053.lore_loc: The Morphling calls upon his elements to crush his opponents with waves.
notes_loc: Projectile moves at %projectile_speed% speed.
5053.shard_loc: Causes Adaptive Strike to have +1 Multishot and increases the stun duration by 1 second. Multishot prioritizes heroes.

7000.name: morphling_adaptive_strike_str
7000.desc_loc:
Launches a surge of water toward an enemy unit, stunning and knocking back the target based on Morphling's strength. If his strength is 50% higher than his agility, the maximum stun/knockback is dealt. 

 Also puts Adaptive Strike (Agility) on a %shared_cooldown% second cooldown.
7000.lore_loc: The Morphling calls upon his elements to crush his opponents with waves.
notes_loc: Projectile moves at %projectile_speed% speed.

5055.name: morphling_morph_agi
5055.desc_loc: Morphling shifts its form, pulling points from Strength and pouring them into Agility. The process is reversible.  Additional points in Attribute Shift increase the rate of stat change.  Passively grants bonus Agility.
5055.lore_loc: Shifting water makes it difficult to discern the nature of Morphling.
notes_loc: Attribute Shift can't convert stats from items.
Leveling up Agility Gain will also level up Strength Gain.

5056.name: morphling_morph_str
5056.desc_loc: Morphling shifts its form, pulling points from Agility and pouring them into Strength. The process is reversible.  Additional points in Attribute Shift increase the rate of stat change.  Passively grants bonus Strength.
5056.lore_loc: Shifting water makes it difficult to discern the nature of Morphling.
notes_loc: Attribute Shift can't convert stats from items.
Leveling up Strength Gain will also level up Agility Gain.

5057.name: morphling_replicate
5057.desc_loc: Morphling changes his form to match the targeted enemy, gaining their basic abilities with reduced mana cost. Can be toggled for the duration of the ability.
5057.lore_loc: Staring into Morphling produces a reflection that mimics the beholder.
notes_loc: You can't target yourself with Morph.
5057.scepter_loc: Allows targeting allied heroes. While Morphed, Morphling gains Cast Range increase.

6840.name: special_bonus_unique_morphling_4
6840.desc_loc: Enemies hit by Waveform are also instantly attacked by Morphling.

5065.name: phantom_lancer_spirit_lance
5065.desc_loc: Sends a magical spirit lance to a target enemy unit that damages and slows, while summoning an illusory phantom to attack the unit.
5065.lore_loc: Azwraith's proficiency at spearing his family's meal of fish is proving quite useful in the battlefield.
notes_loc: Nearby illusions will mimic the cast animation.
5065.shard_loc: Spirit Lance bounces once on an enemy within 750 radius, prioritizing heroes. Increases Spirit Lance illusion damage by +40%%.

5066.name: phantom_lancer_doppelwalk
5066.desc_loc:
Phantom Lancer briefly vanishes from the battlefield. After %delay% second, Phantom Lancer and any of his nearby illusions reappear at a random position within the targeted location, along with two additional doppelgangers. Extends duration of all illusions. The two added doppelgangers have different properties: one takes normal damage and deals none, while the other takes %illusion_2_damage_in_pct%%% bonus damage and deals %illusion_2_damage_out_pct%%% less damage.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
5066.lore_loc: Dread Magus Vorn's death imbued the Phantom Lancer with the ability to bend and fracture all spectrums of light.
notes_loc: This ability can be used to dodge projectiles, and dispell debuffs.
Trees near a reappearing unit will be destroyed.
Phantom Lancer and his allies can see which illusion is the 100% damage illusion.

5068.name: phantom_lancer_phantom_edge
5068.desc_loc: When targetting an enemy for an attack, Phantom Lancer quickly charges into range, gaining a temporary agility boost. Phantom Lancer's illusions also have this ability.
5068.lore_loc: Azwraith knows that on the field of battle, speed can mean everything.
notes_loc: If the attack order is cancelled, the movement speed bonus is lost.
Rush movement speed is %bonus_speed%.

5067.name: phantom_lancer_juxtapose
5067.desc_loc: Phantom Lancer has a chance to fracture his presence, creating an illusion of himself. Illusions also have a chance to fracture further. Illusions created from Phantom Lancer last for %illusion_duration% seconds, while illusions created from other illusions last %illusion_from_illusion_duration% seconds.
5067.lore_loc: Each of Azwraith's lance attacks feels like two from a normal warrior; or three; or four...
notes_loc: Illusions created by Juxtapose will attack the target that the ability was triggered upon.
5067.scepter_loc: Adds Juxtapose active ability. Destroys Phantom Lancer's other juxtapose illusions and quickly creates the max illusions it allows with a bonus 10 seconds of duration.

5069.name: puck_illusory_orb
5069.desc_loc: Puck launches a magic orb that floats in a straight path, damaging enemy units along the way. At any point, Puck may teleport to the orb's location using Ethereal Jaunt.
5069.lore_loc: The playful Faerie Dragon delights in confusing others, vanishing and reappearing where unexpected.
notes_loc: The Illusory Orb grants unobstructed vision around its location while it travels.
Jaunting to the Orb will disjoint projectiles.

5071.name: puck_waning_rift
5071.desc_loc: Puck teleports to the target location and releases a burst of faerie dust that deals damage and silences enemy units nearby.
5071.lore_loc: With a mischievous grin, Puck spreads its enchanted powder which disrupts magical flow.
5071.shard_loc: Waning Rift now deals 70 bonus damage and knocks enemies back 250 distance over 0.4 seconds (non-interrupting). Reveals invisible enemy units and wards in the area for 5 seconds.

5072.name: puck_phase_shift
5072.desc_loc: CHANNELED - Puck briefly shifts into another dimension where it is immune from harm.
5072.lore_loc: With a quip and flash, Puck returns to the alien dimension from whence it came.
notes_loc: Puck retains collision size while under the effects of Phase Shift.
Issuing any action will cancel Phase Shift.
Puck is invulnerable during Phase Shift.

5073.name: puck_dream_coil
5073.desc_loc: Creates a coil of volatile magic that latches onto enemy Heroes, stunning them for %stun_duration% seconds, damaging and leashing them.  If the enemy hero stretches the coil by moving too far away, it snaps, stunning and dealing additional damage.
5073.lore_loc: The Faerie Dragon sows confusion by forcing its enemies to vividly dream about their own mortality.
5073.scepter_loc: Increases damage from coil breaks, increases coil duration, coil break stun goes through spell immunity.

348.name: special_bonus_unique_puck_5
348.desc_loc: Puck instantly attacks all enemies upon casting Phase Shift, within attack range + 200.

6855.name: special_bonus_unique_puck_3
6855.desc_loc: Puck instantly attacks all enemies while affected by Dream Coil, every {s:value} seconds.

5075.name: pudge_meat_hook
5075.desc_loc: Launches a bloody hook toward a unit or location. The hook will snag the first unit it encounters, dragging the unit back to Pudge and dealing damage if it is an enemy.
5075.lore_loc: The Butcher's hook is a symbolic nightmare, its curved blade a frightening reminder of his slaughterous intent.
notes_loc: Interrupts channeling spells of the primary target if it's an enemy.
Meat Hook hits invisible units.
Meat Hook can go through trees, cliffs, buildings, ancient units and Roshan.
Meat Hook can drag friendly units, but they won't be damaged.
Meat Hook can hit and drag runes to Pudge, refunding the Hook's mana cost.

5076.name: pudge_rot
5076.desc_loc: A toxic cloud that deals intense damage and slows movement--harming not only enemy units but Pudge himself.
5076.lore_loc: A foul odor precedes a toxic, choking gas, emanating from the Butcher's putrid, ever-swelling mass.
notes_loc: Using Rot doesn't interrupt channeling.
Rot hits invisible units.
If Pudge is silenced, he can't deactivate Rot if it's activated.
5076.scepter_loc:
Increases Rot radius by %scepter_rot_radius_bonus% and damage by %scepter_rot_damage_bonus%.

Reduces health regen on affected enemies by 25%%.

5074.name: pudge_flesh_heap
5074.desc_loc: Gives Pudge increased magic resistance, as well as bonus strength that increases each time Pudge kills an enemy Hero or it dies in his vicinity.  Flesh Heap is retroactive, meaning it can gain charges before it is skilled, which then become active.
5074.lore_loc: The Butcher gives new meaning to the words 'meat shield.'

322.name: pudge_eject
322.desc_loc: Ejects the swallowed allied hero inside of you.

5077.name: pudge_dismember
5077.desc_loc: CHANNELED - Pudge chows down on an enemy unit, disabling it and dealing damage over time. Pudge gets healed for the same amount he damages. Lasts longer on creeps.
5077.lore_loc: 'When I'm through with these vermin, they'll be fit for a pie!'
notes_loc: If a unit becomes invisible while Dismembered, it will still be under the effects of Dismember.
5077.shard_loc: Allows targeting an ally to swallow them and heal them for %scepter_regen_pct%%% of their max health per second. Reduces cooldown by 10 seconds.

5082.name: razor_plasma_field
5082.desc_loc: Releases a wave of energetic plasma that grows in power as it expands, but also zaps on contraction, slowing and dealing damage to enemy units caught in its path. Damage and slow increases with distance from Razor. The Plasma Field hits each unit twice, once each direction.
5082.lore_loc: The Lightning Revenant rules the Underscape with plasmatic power.

5083.name: razor_static_link
5083.desc_loc: Creates a charged link between Razor and an enemy Hero, stealing damage from the target and giving it to Razor. Allows razor to attack while moving with the link active.
5083.lore_loc: Razor's polarity channels electricity into his being, draining the power of his opposition.
notes_loc: The link is broken when either unit dies or the distance between them becomes %drain_range_buffer% units greater than Static Link's cast range.
Can target Spell Immune units.

5084.name: razor_unstable_current
5084.lore_loc: Merely approaching the Lightning Revenant is rewarded with shock therapy.
5084.shard_loc: Causes Storm Surge to have an 18% chance when attacked, and always when targeted with a spell, to release forked lightning that strikes the target and up to 2 other enemies. Deals 150 Damage and slows them by 50% for 1.5 seconds.

5085.name: razor_eye_of_the_storm
5085.desc_loc: A powerful lightning storm strikes out at enemy units with the lowest health, dealing damage and reducing their armor.
notes_loc: Each blast targets the lowest health enemy unit within range.
Eye of the Storm will prioritize striking static linked heroes.
Successive casts of Eye of the Storm will stack.
5085.scepter_loc: Causes Eye of the Storm to strike two different units instead of one and can damage structures. When striking buildings, it will only target towers, barracks, and the Ancient.

6408.name: special_bonus_unique_razor_2
6408.name_loc: {s:value} Eye of the Storm Strike Interval

5102.name: sandking_burrowstrike
5102.desc_loc: Sand King burrows into the ground and tunnels forward, damaging and stunning enemy units above him as he resurfaces.
5102.lore_loc: Crixalis often lies in wait, burrowing under the surface to ambush his adversaries.
5102.scepter_loc: Adds Caustic Finale poison to heroes hit by Sand King's Burrowstrike and increases its cast range. Does not apply Caustic Finale to illusions.

5103.name: sandking_sand_storm
5103.desc_loc: Sand King creates a fearsome sandstorm that damages enemy units while hiding him from vision.  The effect ends when Sand King leaves the area.
5103.lore_loc: Some say Crixalis is a mirage; his carapace appearing then vanishing between the whirling sands of the Scintillant Waste.
notes_loc: Sand Storm can be used to dodge projectiles.
Sand King briefly becomes visible upon attacking or using spells while in Sand Storm. Sand King will become invisible again in %fade_delay% seconds.

5104.name: sandking_caustic_finale
5104.desc_loc: Sand King's attacks inject a venom that causes enemy units to move more slowly and to violently explode when it dies.
5104.lore_loc: An injection from Crixalis makes one brittle and as dry as the arid wastes, subject to implosive demise.

5105.name: sandking_epicenter
5105.desc_loc: CHANNELED - After channeling for %abilitychanneltime% seconds, Sand King sends a disturbance into the earth, causing it to shudder violently. All enemies caught within range will take damage and become slowed. Each subsequent pulse increases the radius of damage dealt.
5105.lore_loc: Many an explorer was lost to the quicksands of the Scintillant Waste.
notes_loc: The pulses are centered on Sand King, not where he first casted the spell.
The pulses have gradually inreasing radius, ranging from 500 to 725.
5105.shard_loc: Every 700 units moved causes an Epicenter Pulse around Sand King in 475 AoE.

475.name: special_bonus_unique_sand_king_4
475.desc_loc: Enemy units in range of Sand Storm have their movement speed slowed by {s:value}% and miss {s:value}% of their attacks.

5098.name: storm_spirit_static_remnant
5098.desc_loc: Creates an explosively charged image of Storm Spirit that lasts %abilityduration% seconds and will detonate and deal damage if an enemy unit comes near it.
5098.lore_loc: Raijin Thunderkeg's duality allows him to admire himself in shocking fashion.
notes_loc: Remnants take %static_remnant_delay% second to materialize after the spell is cast.
Remnants grant unobstructed vision for their duration.
The explosion actually hits units in a %static_remnant_damage_radius% radius, but will only be triggered in %static_remnant_radius%.

5099.name: storm_spirit_electric_vortex
5099.desc_loc: A vortex that pulls an enemy unit to Storm Spirit's location.
5099.lore_loc: Raijin's thunderous, boisterous energy often draws others into an electrifying situation.
5099.scepter_loc: Electric Vortex affects all enemies within a radius around Storm Spirit.

5100.name: storm_spirit_overload
5100.desc_loc: Casting a spell creates an electrical charge, which is released in a burst on Storm's next attack, dealing damage and slowing nearby enemies.
notes_loc: Using items doesn't trigger Overload.
Overload charges do not stack.
5100.shard_loc: Can be activated to grant Storm Spirit and allied heroes within 750 AoE of him 3 Overload charges. Provides 40 Attack Speed. Lasts up to 12 seconds or until the charges are depleted.

5101.name: storm_spirit_ball_lightning
5101.desc_loc: Storm Spirit becomes volatile electricity, charging across the battlefield until he depletes his mana or reaches his target. The activation mana cost is %ball_lightning_initial_mana_base%+%ball_lightning_initial_mana_percentage%%% of his total mana pool, and the cost per 100 units traveled is %ball_lightning_travel_cost_base%+%ball_lightning_travel_cost_percent%%% of his total mana pool.  Damage is expressed in damage per 100 units traveled.
notes_loc: Abilities and items can be used while traveling.
This ability will destroy trees.
Storm Spirit is invulnerable during Ball Lightning.

6908.name: special_bonus_unique_storm_spirit_4
6908.name_loc: {s:value} Distance Auto Remnant in Ball Lightning
6908.desc_loc: Every {s:value} distance travelled in Ball Lightning creates a Static Remnant.

5094.name: sven_storm_bolt
5094.desc_loc: Sven unleashes his magical gauntlet that deals damage and stuns enemy units in a small area around the target.
5094.lore_loc: The Rogue Knight's iron gauntlet, taken from the school of his father, strikes his foes to their core.
5094.shard_loc: Storm Hammer now applies a dispel on enemies and reduces cooldown by 4 seconds.
5094.scepter_loc: Increases cast range and transports Sven along the storm hammer.

5095.name: sven_great_cleave
5095.desc_loc: Sven strikes with great force, cleaving all nearby enemy units with his attack.
5095.lore_loc: The Vigil Knights still seek to reclaim the stolen Outcast Blade from Sven, a weapon capable of cutting wide swaths through lesser warriors.
notes_loc: Cleave damage goes through spell immunity.
The cleave damages a circular area in front of Sven.

5096.name: sven_warcry
5096.desc_loc: Sven's Warcry heartens his allied heroes for battle, increasing their armor and movement speed. Lasts %duration% seconds.
5096.lore_loc: Calling a few lines from the Vigil Codex fortifies Sven's obedience to his rogue code. So poetic!

5097.name: sven_gods_strength
5097.desc_loc: Sven channels his rogue strength, granting bonus damage for %abilityduration% seconds.
5097.lore_loc: With the strength that shattered the Sacred Helm, the Rogue Knight stands unopposed in melee combat.
notes_loc: The bonus damage is based on base damage and the primary attribute of Sven.

5106.name: tiny_avalanche
5106.desc_loc: Bombards an area with rocks, continously doing small intervals of damage and stun to enemy units. Avalanche does 2.5x damage to units being tossed.
5106.lore_loc: Inanimate rock becomes animate when called by the Stone Giant.

5107.name: tiny_toss
5107.desc_loc: Grabs the nearest unit in a %grab_radius% radius around Tiny, ally or enemy, and launches it at the target unit or rune to deal damage where they land.  If the tossed unit is an enemy, it will take an extra %bonus_damage_pct%%% damage.
5107.lore_loc: Tiny's gargantuan stature allows him to catapult even the sturdiest of warriors.
notes_loc: You can toss allies, but they don't take damage.
Toss deals 33% of its damage to buildings.

5108.name: tiny_tree_grab
5108.desc_loc: Grabs a tree to whack enemies on the head for a limited number of attacks. Grants bonus attack range. Attacks deal more damage and fully splash on units along the way. The tree can be thrown, to deal your attack to a unit at a distance.
5108.lore_loc: Sticks and stones break all the bones, with structures sure to follow.
notes_loc: The cooldown begins when the tree is thrown.
5108.shard_loc: Causes Tree Grab to have no charge limit.

7850.name: tiny_tree_channel
7850.desc_loc: Tiny channels this ability to throw random trees within range towards the targeted aoe. Deals Tiny's attack damage plus a bonus to enemies in that area with each tree thrown.
7850.lore_loc: Sticks thrown from stones are like to shatter many bones.

5109.name: tiny_grow
5109.desc_loc: Tiny gains craggy mass, increasing his attack damage, and armor, while slowing his attack speed.
5109.lore_loc: Watching a hill become a mountain is awe-inspiring - especially if the mountain begins laying waste to adversaries.

6937.name: tiny_toss_tree
6937.desc_loc: Throws the tree at the target unit, proccing your attack on it and splashing damage around the target.
6937.lore_loc: Even enemies can share in Tiny's arbor ardor.

7005.name: special_bonus_unique_tiny_5
7005.desc_loc: Toss can target the ground as well as enemy units.

5122.name: vengefulspirit_magic_missile
5122.desc_loc: Fires a magic missile at an enemy unit, stunning and dealing damage.
5122.lore_loc: A simple Skywrath technique, the magic missile is Shendel's primary tool for vengeance.

5124.name: vengefulspirit_wave_of_terror
5124.desc_loc: Vengeful Spirit lets loose a wicked cry, weakening the armor of enemies and giving vision of the path ahead.
5124.lore_loc: Shendel's haunting voice hints at her approaching vindication.
5124.shard_loc: Wave of Terror steals 20%% of enemy hero base damage and base armor, granting it to Vengeful Spirit for the debuff duration.

5123.name: vengefulspirit_command_aura
5123.desc_loc: Vengeful Spirit's presence increases the damage of nearby friendly heroes.
5123.lore_loc: Although they may not share her undying passion for revenge, allies do draw on her fanaticism in combat.
notes_loc: Vengeance Illusion keeps providing the Vengeance Aura after Vengeful Spirit's death.
Strong Illusions are not instantly killed by spells.
5123.scepter_loc: Upon death, creates a strong illusion of Vengeful Spirit that deals and takes 100%% damage and can cast all of her spells. Illusion has 25%% movement speed bonus. If the illusion is alive when Vengeful Spirit respawn, she will take its place. XP earned by her illusion is given to her.

5125.name: vengefulspirit_nether_swap
5125.desc_loc: Instantaneously swaps positions with a target Hero, friend or enemy.  Nether Swap interrupts channeling abilities on the target.
5125.lore_loc: Martyrdom is a small price to pay for vengeance.
notes_loc: Works on Spell Immune units.
Trees near Vengeful Spirit and the target will be destroyed when the spell is cast.
Channeling spells are interrupted by Nether Swap.

5130.name: windrunner_shackleshot
5130.desc_loc: Shackles the target to an enemy unit or tree in a line directly behind it.  If no unit or tree is present, the stun duration is reduced to %fail_stun_duration%.
5130.lore_loc: Windranger's variety of bow skills includes an arrow with thick ropes attached to encumber any escaping target.
notes_loc: This spell can shackle two enemies together, stunning them both.
Can shackle the target to an enemy unit or tree at most %shackle_distance% behind the target.
Shackleshot can be disjointed.

5131.name: windrunner_powershot
5131.desc_loc: Windranger charges her bow for up to %abilitychanneltime% second for a single powerful shot, which deals more damage the longer it is charged. The arrow damages enemies along its path. For each enemy that Powershot hits, its damage is reduced by %damage_reduction%%%.
5131.lore_loc: During her early years of training, Lyralei learned to fire powerful arrows that cleaved even trees to reach their targets.
notes_loc: Powershot will destroy trees in its area of effect.
5131.shard_loc: Powershot now becomes global, but only hits heroes beyond its default range (max 1 hero). Impacted heroes will be killed if they are under 13% after taking the impact damage. Lowers cooldown by 1.5 seconds.

5132.name: windrunner_windrun
5132.desc_loc: Increases movement speed and adds evasion from all physical attacks, while slowing movement of nearby enemies.
5132.lore_loc: Lyralei enchants gusts of winds to fight incoming attacks.
notes_loc: Activating Windrun will evade incoming projectiles.
5132.scepter_loc: Grants %max_charges% charges to Windrun and grants haste movement speed. Passively provides 30%% Evasion.

5133.name: windrunner_focusfire
5133.desc_loc: Windranger channels the wind to gain %bonus_attack_speed% additional attack speed against a single enemy unit or structure, though with a reduction to her attack damage.  Extra damage from secondary item effects is not reduced.
5133.lore_loc: Lyralei's ability to bombard opponents with a flurry of arrows is unparalleled - even at the expense of accuracy.
notes_loc: Issuing a Hold Position command will pause Windranger's attacks.
Windranger can move while attacking.

5110.name: zuus_arc_lightning
5110.desc_loc: Hurls a bolt of lightning that leaps through nearby enemy units.
5110.lore_loc: Arc Lightning is Zeus' favorite spell to use against puny mortals.

5111.name: zuus_lightning_bolt
5111.desc_loc: Calls down a bolt of lightning to strike an enemy unit, causing damage and a mini-stun. When cast, Lightning Bolt briefly provides unobstructed vision and True Sight around the target in a %sight_radius_night% radius. Can be cast on the ground, affecting the closest enemy hero in %spread_aoe% range.
5111.lore_loc: A shocking punishment for rebellious heathen.
notes_loc: You can interrupt channeling spells and items with this ability.

5112.name: zuus_static_field
5112.desc_loc: Zeus shocks any enemy hit by his abilities, causing damage proportional to their current health.
5112.lore_loc: The air crackles with static when the Thundergod walks the world.
notes_loc: The damage from Static Field is dealt before the damage from the used spell.
Using items doesn't trigger Static Field.
5112.shard_loc: Static Field can be cast to perform a Heavenly Jump, shocking the closest visible enemy (prioritizing heroes) within 2000 range, dealing Static Field damage to them and reducing their movement speed by 100% for 2.5 seconds. If Zeus was moving forward, he will jump towards that direction. Cooldown: 11. Manacost: 100.

6325.name: zuus_cloud
6325.desc_loc: Creates a storm cloud anywhere on the map that automatically casts Lightning Bolt on nearby enemies.
6325.lore_loc: Where the thunder god's ire grows, storm clouds quickly gather.
notes_loc: Grants %cloud_bounty_tooltip% gold if destroyed by an enemy hero.
Affects the closest enemy unit with strikes from Zeus's current level of Lightning Bolt.
Towers and creeps do half damage to the Nimbus.

641.name: zuus_heavenly_jump
641.desc_loc: Jumps forward a distance of %hop_distance% units. Midway through the jump a Arc Lightning is cast on a an enemy within it’s cast range.

5113.name: zuus_thundergods_wrath
5113.desc_loc: Strikes all enemy heroes with a bolt of lightning, no matter where they may be.  Thundergod's Wrath also provides True Sight around each hero struck.  If an enemy hero is invisible, it takes no damage, but the True Sight is still created at that hero's location.
5113.lore_loc: The Lord of Heaven smites all who oppose him, near or far.

5031.name: kunkka_torrent
5031.desc_loc: Summons a rising torrent that, after a short delay, hurls enemy units into the sky, stunning, dealing damage and slowing movement speed.
5031.lore_loc: An ancestral rush of water explodes from the center of the world, called upon by the Admiral.
notes_loc: The initial bubble effect is only visible to allies and provides vision in fog of war.
Units tossed in the air will be stunned and still able to be attacked.

5032.name: kunkka_tidebringer
5032.desc_loc: Kunkka's legendary sword grants increased damage and cleaves a large area of effect in front of him for a single strike.
5032.lore_loc: A lost Claddish soul inhabits Kunkka's trusty Tidebringer, empowering it to destroy demons of the Cataract.
notes_loc: Cleave damage goes through spell immunity.

5033.name: kunkka_x_marks_the_spot
5033.desc_loc: Targets a friendly or enemy Hero, marks their position with an X, and returns them to it after several seconds.  Kunkka can trigger the return at any time during the duration. Lasts twice as long on allied heroes.
5033.lore_loc: The Admiral's set of arcane abilities includes some that can be used for battle as well as entertainment.
notes_loc: If the target becomes Spell Immune after the cast, the target will not return to the X after the duration.
Interrupts channeling spells.

319.name: kunkka_torrent_storm
319.desc_loc: Releases a visible Torrent in a random area around Kunkka once every %torrent_interval% for %torrent_duration% seconds. Spawns within %torrent_max_distance% range of him.
319.lore_loc: A hundred leagues of dry land couldn't keep these seas at bay.

605.name: kunkka_tidal_wave
605.desc_loc: Releases a Tidal Wave that spawns behind Kunkka. Deals %damage% damage and drags enemies along it for %knockback_distance% distance. Enemies cannot attack while being dragged.

5035.name: kunkka_ghostship
5035.desc_loc: Summons a ghostly ship that sails through the battle before smashing apart, damaging and stunning all enemies caught near the wreckage. Allied heroes touched by the Ghostship are given a swig of The Admiral's Rum, receiving bonus movement speed and a delayed reaction to incoming damage.
5035.lore_loc: The final ship of the Claddish Navy is nothing but a phantom, but it is all too real to the enemies of the Admiral.
notes_loc: Damage dealt after Rum wears off is non-lethal and can never kill a hero.
Actual area of effect of ship's collision is larger than the boat itself.
The boat has a movement speed of %ghostship_speed%.

6666.name: special_bonus_unique_kunkka_3
6666.desc_loc: Spawns 3 Ghostships, {s:value} seconds apart, towards the target location.

5040.name: lina_dragon_slave
5040.desc_loc: Lina channels the breath of a dragon, sending out a wave of fire that scorches every enemy in its path.
5040.lore_loc: In the scorched barren of Misrule, Lina learned to manipulate the fiery breath of the Desert Wyrm as a form of entertainment.
notes_loc: Dragon Slave can hit units up to 1225 units away.

5041.name: lina_light_strike_array
5041.desc_loc: Summons a column of flames that damages and stuns enemies.
5041.lore_loc: Lina's essence allows her to focus the sun's energies, causing air to combust at will.
notes_loc: Light Strike Array will destroy trees in its area of effect.

5042.name: lina_fiery_soul
5042.desc_loc: Grants bonus attack and movement speed each time Lina casts a spell. Stacks with itself. Lasts %fiery_soul_stack_duration% seconds.
5042.lore_loc: Dancing flames embody Lina's playful nature, bringing out her true blazing self.
notes_loc: Duration refreshes each time a new spell is cast.
Using items does not trigger Fiery Soul.

5043.name: lina_laguna_blade
5043.desc_loc: Fires off a bolt of lightning at a single enemy unit, dealing massive damage.
5043.lore_loc: The air around Lina becomes so intensely torrid that it scorches a foe that comes too close with white-hot lightning.
notes_loc: Laguna Blade has a %damage_delay% delay before the damage is applied after the spell is cast, allowing certain abilities to avoid the damage.
5043.shard_loc: Increases Laguna Blade's cast range by 250 and causes it to go the full cast length and hit all units along the way. Can be ground targeted.
5043.scepter_loc: Changes Laguna Blade's damage type to Pure, and allows it to slice through spell immunity.

5134.name: lich_frost_nova
5134.desc_loc: Blasts the target enemy unit with damaging frost, dealing area damage and slowing movement and attack rates for %abilityduration% seconds.  The primary target receives both base and area damage.
5134.lore_loc: Frost-mage Ethreain has not forgotten even the simplest of ice manipulation.

5136.name: lich_frost_shield
5136.desc_loc: Applies a magical frost shield around the target, reducing damage from attacks against you. While the shield is active, ice magic will affect nearby enemy units every %interval% seconds, dealing minor damage and slowing them.
5136.lore_loc: First conceived of to protect him in his mortal years, the frost magic that Ethreain weaves around himself has only grown colder with time.
notes_loc: Spell-immune enemies are not affected by the damage or slow.
Frost Shield can be cast on buildings.

7325.name: lich_sinister_gaze
7325.desc_loc: CHANNELED - Hypnotizes an enemy unit, causing it to move towards a point between the two of you and drains a percentage of its current mana.
7325.scepter_loc: Casts Sinister Gaze in a target area.

8028.name: lich_ice_spire
8028.desc_loc:
Creates an icicle at the target spot for %duration% seconds, slowing enemies within %aura_radius% range by %bonus_movespeed%%%. Has 800 health.

Chain Frost can bounce to the Icicle if there are no other enemies in range.

Can cast Frost Shield on it.

5137.name: lich_chain_frost
5137.desc_loc: Releases an orb of frost that bounces between nearby enemy units up to %jumps% times, slowing and damaging each time it hits. Each bounce increases the damage for the subsequent bounces.
5137.lore_loc: Almost universally considered the ultimate in frost magic, Ethreain's orb of frozen death strikes fear into those who dare stand against him.
notes_loc: Chain Frost cannot be disjointed.
Chain Frost has a movement speed of %projectile_speed%.
Chain Frost doesn't bounce to Zombies.

5044.name: lion_impale
5044.desc_loc: Rock spikes burst from the earth along a straight path. Enemy units are hurled into the air, then are stunned and take damage when they fall.
5044.lore_loc: The Demon Witch exercises his demonic covenant, opening a fissure from hell.
notes_loc: The spikes move at %speed% units per second.

5045.name: lion_voodoo
5045.desc_loc: Transforms an enemy unit into a harmless beast, with all special abilities disabled.
5045.lore_loc: Lion is compelled to share his transfiguration, twisting the essence of those who oppose him.
notes_loc: Instantly destroys illusions.
The target will have a base movement speed of %movespeed%, but buffs granting maximum movement speed won't be disabled.

5046.name: lion_mana_drain
5046.desc_loc: CHANNELED - Absorbs the magical energies of a target enemy unit by taking mana from it every second.
5046.lore_loc: Lesser magi are nothing more than a source of magical restoration for the Demon Witch.
notes_loc: Instantly destroys illusions.
5046.shard_loc: Causes Mana Drain to affect up to three enemies. You become Spell Immune while channeling.

5047.name: lion_finger_of_death
5047.desc_loc: Rips at an enemy unit, trying to turn it inside-out. Deals massive damage and grows stronger with each life it consumes.
5047.lore_loc: Lion's disfigured hand is also the source of his greatest power, capable of flooding victims with malefic force.
notes_loc: Finger of Death has a %damage_delay% delay before the damage is applied after the spell is cast, allowing certain abilities to avoid the damage.
Finger of Death only gains damage if the enemy hero dies within %grace_period% seconds of being affected by Finger of Death.
5047.scepter_loc: Increases damage. Decreases cooldown. Finger of Death hits all units in a small area.

781.name: special_bonus_unique_lion_11
781.name_loc: +{s:value} Max Health Per Finger of Death Kill

541.name: special_bonus_unique_lion_8
541.name_loc: +{s:value} Finger of Death Damage Per Kill

5078.name: shadow_shaman_ether_shock
5078.desc_loc: Creates a cone of ethereal energy that strikes multiple enemy units.
5078.lore_loc: Originally used to open shows with the travelling con-man, Rhasta's lightning display shocks adversaries in more ways than one.
notes_loc: Can hit secondary targets up to 1000 distance away.

5079.name: shadow_shaman_voodoo
5079.desc_loc: Transforms an enemy unit into a harmless creature, disabling their attacks and abilities.
5079.lore_loc: Rhasta often ended performances by turning himself into a chicken - now, the humiliation is shared.
notes_loc: Instantly destroys illusions.
The target will have a base movement speed of %movespeed%, but buffs granting maximum movement speed won't be disabled.
Hex disables damage block.

5080.name: shadow_shaman_shackles
5080.desc_loc: CHANNELED - Magically binds an enemy unit so that it cannot move or attack, while dealing damage over time.
5080.lore_loc: A self-defense incantation, Rhasta developed shackles after his master was slain in the Bleeding Hills.
5080.shard_loc: Shackles creates 4 Serpent Wards attacking the target. Increases Shackles cast range by 125. Lasts 7 seconds.

5081.name: shadow_shaman_mass_serpent_ward
5081.desc_loc: Summons %ward_count% Serpent Wards to attack enemy units and structures. The Wards are immune to magic.
5081.lore_loc: Snake charming was a big part of the Shadow Shaman's act; now Rhasta can empower the snakes to do his bidding.
5081.scepter_loc: Causes Serpent Wards to have split shot, attacking two units for full damage. Increases attack range of Serpent Wards.

5114.name: slardar_sprint
5114.desc_loc: Slardar slithers ahead, moving significantly faster and passing through units. Slardar gains movement speed bonus while in the river.
5114.lore_loc: As Slardar has made the transition from the Deeps, it has been necessary to use his powerful tail for sprinting instead of swimming.
notes_loc: Activating this skill doesn't interrupt channeling abilities.
5114.scepter_loc: Provides additional HP Regen, Armor and Status Resistance while in a puddle or in the river.

5115.name: slardar_slithereen_crush
5115.desc_loc: Slams the ground, stunning and damaging nearby enemy land units.  After the stun, the affected units are slowed.
5115.lore_loc: A swift crush of might and water breaks even the toughest of defenses.
5115.shard_loc: Causes Slithereen Crush to apply Corrosive Haze for 5 seconds to units affected. Increases radius by 75.
5115.scepter_loc: Whenever Slardar casts Slithereen Crush, he creates a puddle of water that is considered a river for movement and bonuses.

5116.name: slardar_bash
5116.desc_loc: After %attack_count% attacks, your next attack will bash the target. Deals double damage against creeps.
5116.lore_loc: Thieves of the wealth of the Deep Ones meet the brutality of the Slithereen Guard in melee combat.
notes_loc: Does not stack with Skull Basher.

5117.name: slardar_amplify_damage
5117.desc_loc: Reduces enemy armor to amplify physical damage and provides True Sight and vision of the targeted unit, revealing invisibility.
5117.lore_loc: Even the strongest armor counts for little when left to the brine of the sea.

5118.name: tidehunter_gush
5118.desc_loc: Summons a gush of water to damage an enemy unit, reducing their movement speed and armor.
5118.lore_loc: During his championship of the Sunken Isles, Leviathan gained mastery over the open sea.
5118.scepter_loc: Gush becomes a ground targeted wave ability that affects enemy units in a line.  Decreases cooldown.

5119.name: tidehunter_kraken_shell
5119.desc_loc:
Thickens Tidehunter's hide to passively block a portion of any incoming physical attack damage. The hide also removes negative status effects if the damage taken crosses a threshold.

Does not stack with items that provide Damage Block.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
5119.lore_loc: Claddish navymen tell tales of a mighty sea-faring beast that suffered spear and sword but continued to lay waste to the fleet.
notes_loc: Only damage from player owned sources is counted towards debuff removal.
The counter will reset if no player owned damage is taken for %damage_reset_interval% seconds.
Kraken Shell removes most debuffs, even if they are generally not purgable.

5120.name: tidehunter_anchor_smash
5120.desc_loc: Tidehunter swings his mighty anchor to attack and deal bonus damage to nearby enemies and reduce their attack damage.
5120.lore_loc: Stolen from one of Admiral Kunkka's flagships, Leviathan's heavy anchor proves useful as a melee weapon.
notes_loc: Anchor Smash works on all Ancient creeps except for Roshan.
5120.shard_loc: Increases Anchor Smash damage by 90 and causes it to affect buildings. Reduces cooldown by 1 second.

5121.name: tidehunter_ravage
5121.desc_loc: Slams the ground, causing tentacles to erupt in all directions, damaging and stunning all nearby enemy units.
5121.lore_loc: Calling to the abyssal god Maelrawn has resulted in entire armadas being lost at sea.
notes_loc: Ravage will hit invisible units.
Ravage waves move outwards at a speed of %speed%.

5138.name: witch_doctor_paralyzing_cask
5138.desc_loc: Launches a cask of paralyzing powder that ricochets between enemy units, stunning and damaging those it hits.
5138.lore_loc: The Witch Doctor recycles the bones of fallen friends and foes, using the powder as part of his arsenal of charms and alchemy.
notes_loc: Targets can be hit multiple times, as long as another unit is struck in between the bounces.

5139.name: witch_doctor_voodoo_restoration
5139.desc_loc: Witch Doctor focuses his magic to heal nearby allied units, costing Witch Doctor mana every second Voodoo restoration is active.
5139.lore_loc: Zharvakko's hocus pocus is not limited only to hexxing his opponents and is quite adept at curing ailments.
notes_loc: Healing is done in %heal_interval% second intervals.
Can heal Spell Immune units.

5140.name: witch_doctor_maledict
5140.desc_loc: Curses all enemy Heroes in a small area, causing them to take a set amount of damage each second, as well as bursts of damage every 4 seconds based on how much health they have lost since the curse began.
5140.lore_loc: Certain voodoo magics can make an enemy regret engaging the Witch Doctor.
notes_loc: If an affected hero's health has increased above the amount they had when Maledict was cast, the burst damage will be 0.

632.name: witch_doctor_voodoo_switcheroo
632.desc_loc: Turns Witch Doctor into a Death Ward for 2 seconds. Death Ward has -30 Attack Speed. He is hidden during this time.

5141.name: witch_doctor_death_ward
5141.desc_loc: CHANNELED - Summons a deadly ward to attack enemy heroes within it's attack range. Lasts a maximum of %abilitychanneltime% seconds.
5141.lore_loc: Witch Doctor performs a ritualistic dance, one that haunts the dreams of those who live to recount it.
notes_loc: The Death Ward is invulnerable, and is only destroyed if Witch Doctor is interrupted or its duration expires.
The Death Ward can be controlled, and made to attack a specific target.
Death Ward attacks once every 0.22 seconds.
5141.scepter_loc: Death Ward attacks have True Strike and bounce between nearby enemies.

5142.name: riki_smoke_screen
5142.desc_loc: Throws down a smoke bomb, silencing enemies, and causing them to miss attacks.
5142.lore_loc: Since his escape during the night of his betrayal, Riki has valued the use of a simple smoke screen to confuse his opponents.
notes_loc: Can be cast during Tricks of the Trade.
Doesn't prevent the use of active items.

5143.name: riki_blink_strike
5143.desc_loc: Teleports behind the target unit, striking for bonus damage if it is an enemy.
5143.lore_loc: The Stealth Assassin's agile movement makes him impossible to escape.
notes_loc: Riki's first attack after Blink Strike will be a backstab.
Blink Strike's damage is dealt before the next attack.
You can Blink Strike to allies, but no damage is dealt.

5145.name: riki_tricks_of_the_trade
5145.desc_loc: Riki phases out of the world while striking random enemy units from behind in an area around him.
5145.lore_loc: The Stealth Assassin is not afraid to fight dirty, and specializes in attacking his opponents from behind.
notes_loc: Moving while phased out will cancel the ability.
5145.scepter_loc: Increases cast range and allows you to target an allied hero, hiding inside them for the duration.

550.name: riki_poison_dart
550.desc_loc: Fires a dart at the target enemy, putting them to sleep for %duration% seconds or if they take 200 damage. At the end of the duration, the target wakes up and takes %damage% damage, and is slowed by %movement_slow%%% for %debuff_duration% seconds.

5144.name: riki_backstab
5144.desc_loc: Riki fades into the shadows, becoming invisible. Every time Riki strikes his enemy from behind, he deals bonus damage based on his Agility. When Riki attacks, he becomes visible.
notes_loc: Illusions of Riki will play Backstab animations, but not deal any bonus damage.
Bonus damage from Backstab can't be evaded.

5146.name: enigma_malefice
5146.desc_loc: Focuses Enigma's power on a target, causing it to take damage and become repeatedly stunned for multiple instances.  An instance strikes every %tick_rate% seconds.
5146.lore_loc: Strange gravities pull at the core of those who would oppose you, holding them in place.

5147.name: enigma_demonic_conversion
5147.desc_loc: Transforms a creep into three fragments of Enigma himself.  These eidolons are all under Enigma's control, and repeated successful attacks cause them to multiply.  When this happens, the eidolons have their health restored.
5147.lore_loc: Enigma is capable of drawing aspects of himself from other dimensions - the result is a trio of dark eidolons that hunt the corporeal plane.
notes_loc: Converted enemy units will give gold bounty and experience.
Converted allied units will be denied.

5148.name: enigma_midnight_pulse
5148.desc_loc: Steeps an area in dark resonance, damaging enemy units based on their max HP.
5148.lore_loc: A section of the world slowly descends into the void.
notes_loc: Damage goes through spell immunity.
This ability destroys trees in its area.
Multiple instances of Midnight Pulse will stack.

5149.name: enigma_black_hole
5149.desc_loc: CHANNELED - Summons a vortex that sucks in nearby enemy units.  Enemies affected by Black Hole cannot move, attack, or cast spells.
5149.lore_loc: The ground trembles as Enigma channels his ultimate vortex of destruction, a singularity with the power to end worlds.
notes_loc: Disables enemies through spell immunity.
5149.shard_loc: Black Hole does a non-interrupting pull towards it in a 1200 AoE. Pulls at a rate of 175.
5149.scepter_loc: Adds the current level of Midnight Pulse to Black Hole.

5150.name: tinker_laser
5150.desc_loc: Fires an intense energy beam, dealing damage and blinding the target, causing it to miss all physical attacks.
5150.lore_loc: Boush perfected this rock cutting laser in his subterranean laboratory, never considering its combat utility.
5150.scepter_loc: Upgrades Tinker's Laser into a Shrink Ray, granting +400 cast range and reducing the enemy hero's size and current health by 15% (stacking). The laser bounces once on the farthest target up to 700 range from the primary one, prioritizing heroes.

5151.name: tinker_heat_seeking_missile
5151.desc_loc: Launches rockets at the nearest visible enemy heroes within %radius% range.
5151.lore_loc: The last contraption Boush was able to save was a retrofitted rocket launcher with a homing mechanism.

5152.name: tinker_march_of_the_machines
5152.desc_loc: Enlists an army of robotic minions to destroy enemy units in an area around Tinker.
5152.lore_loc: Even though the laboratory has since been sealed off, the ability to radio in robotic drones is still in working order.
notes_loc: Robots spawn at a rate of %machines_per_sec% per second.

650.name: tinker_defense_matrix
650.desc_loc: Targets an allied unit, applying a barrier to them that blocks the next %damage_absorb% damage and provides %status_resistance%%% Status Resistance. Barrier lasts up to %barrier_duration% seconds.

5153.name: tinker_rearm
5153.desc_loc: CHANNELED - Resets the cooldown on most of Tinker's items and abilities.
5153.lore_loc: A new battery here, another set of rockets there, Boush continually improves on existing technology.
notes_loc: Rearm works on all items except Aeon Disk, Arcane Boots, Black King Bar, Hand of Midas, Helm of the Dominator, Linken's Sphere, Meteor Hammer, Necronomicon, Pipe of Insight, Tome of Knowledge, and Refresher Orb.

5154.name: sniper_shrapnel
5154.desc_loc: Consumes a charge to launch a ball of shrapnel that showers the target area in explosive pellets. Enemies are subject to damage and slowed movement. Reveals the targeted area. Shrapnel charges restore every %abilitychargerestoretime% seconds.
5154.lore_loc: Kardel's modular rifle also fires incendiary rounds, useful for assaulting entrenched locations.
notes_loc: Damage is dealt 11 times, immediately at spell effect then every second.
Does not damage buildings.
Provides vision in the targeted area.

5155.name: sniper_headshot
5155.desc_loc: Sniper increases his accuracy, giving him a chance to deal extra damage and briefly knocks back his enemies.
5155.lore_loc: Taking potshots at steepstalkers in his childhood has been thoroughly refined into perfect leads on enemy combatants.
notes_loc: Works on allied creeps.

5156.name: sniper_take_aim
5156.desc_loc: Extends the attack range of Sniper's rifle. Can be activated to provided True Strike and +30%% Headshot chance for 4 seconds. Slows you by 30%% for the duration.
5156.lore_loc: Kardel always takes it upon himself to stay as far from harm as he can while still performing his role - taking perfect aim.

694.name: sniper_concussive_grenade
694.desc_loc: Grants Concussive Grenade. Deals 125 damage, knocking enemies back 425 distance, slowing them by 50%% and disarming them for 3 seconds. Radius: 375. Knocks you back 450 units on cast.

5157.name: sniper_assassinate
5157.desc_loc: Sniper locks onto a target enemy unit and, after a short aiming duration, fires a devastating shot that deals damage at long range and mini-stuns the target.
5157.lore_loc: In order to fulfill the prophecy and return to his home town, Kardel must make another shot as perfect as the one on the day of his ancient test.
notes_loc: Crosshair effect is only visible to allies.
Invisibility doesn't disjoint the projectile.
Interrupts channeling spells, including on Spell Immune units.
5157.scepter_loc: Causes Assassinate to fire quicker and disable the enemy target.

5158.name: necrolyte_death_pulse
5158.desc_loc: Necrophos releases a wave of death around him, dealing damage to enemy units and healing allied units.
5158.lore_loc: Poor souls who succumb to Rotund'jere's plagues are recycled for future use.
notes_loc: Death Pulse can't be disjointed.
Can heal Spell Immune units.

5160.name: necrolyte_sadist
5160.desc_loc: Necrophos slips into the realm that separates the living from the dead. Unable to attack or be attacked, he emits an aura that slows enemies around him. He takes additional magic damage in this form, but his restorative powers are amplified.
5160.lore_loc: Rotund'jere uses the souls of his victims as bridge from life to afterlife.

5159.name: necrolyte_heartstopper_aura
5159.desc_loc: Necrophos stills the hearts of his opponents, causing nearby enemy units to lose a percentage of their max health over time. Passively provides regen for %regen_duration% seconds for each unit Necrophos kills.
5159.lore_loc: Those who come within a short distance of Necrophos can feel pestilence and plague in the air.
notes_loc: Damage won't disable items like Blink Dagger.
Does not affect ancient creeps.
5159.scepter_loc: Increases Heartstopper Aura damage while Ghost Shroud is active.

661.name: necrolyte_death_seeker
661.desc_loc: Spawns a fast moving large Death Pulse towards the target enemy or ally, causing the target to become ethereal for 2.5 seconds. Reduces enemy magic resistance by 25%. Spreads towards nearby enemies and allies after impact.

5161.name: necrolyte_reapers_scythe
5161.desc_loc: Stuns the target enemy hero, then deals damage based on how much life it is missing. Heroes killed by Reaper's Scythe will have %respawn_constant% seconds added to their respawn timer. Any kill under this effect is credited to Necrophos.
5161.lore_loc: The amount of death and suffering in the air increases the power of Necrophos's plague magic.
notes_loc: Damage is dealt at the end of the stun.

5162.name: warlock_fatal_bonds
5162.desc_loc: Binds several enemy units together, causing a percentage of the damage dealt to one of them to be felt by the others.
5162.lore_loc: An ancient incantation that links the vital energies of multiple lifeforms into one collective body.
notes_loc: The shared damage type is the same as the type of damage inflicted.

5163.name: warlock_shadow_word
5163.desc_loc: Warlock whispers an incantation, healing a friendly unit or damaging an enemy unit over time.
5163.lore_loc: Demnok's arcane arts have a myriad of uses, allowing them to be powerful friendly enchantments or damaging curses.
5163.shard_loc: Turns Shadow Word into a 450 AoE Spell. Grants 10%% movement speed bonus to allies and slows enemies by 10%%.

5164.name: warlock_upheaval
5164.desc_loc: CHANNELED - A powerful slowing current that grows stronger as it's channelled. Lasts up to %abilitychanneltime% seconds.  Enemies are slowed for %duration% seconds after leaving the area or the spell ends.
5164.lore_loc: Demnok manipulates space-time, impairing entire armies.
notes_loc: The slow increase is based on length of the channel, not the duration an enemy was standing in the area.

5165.name: warlock_rain_of_chaos
5165.desc_loc: Summons a Golem from the depths, stunning enemies for one second. The Golem lives %golem_duration% seconds, takes reduced damage from spells, has Permanent Immolation and Flaming Fists on attack.
5165.lore_loc: Demnok unleashes the captive spirit in his Dreadwood staff, causing destruction in enemy ranks.
notes_loc: Spell Immune units will be stunned.
This ability destroys trees in its area of effect.
5165.scepter_loc: Calls %number_of_golems_scepter% Golems with reduced stats and bounty.

6053.name: special_bonus_unique_warlock_1
6053.name_loc: 80% Magic Resistance for Chaotic Offering Golems

5168.name: beastmaster_wild_axes
5168.desc_loc: Beastmaster sends his axes flying and calls them home again, slicing through enemy units and trees along their path.  Each axe can hit an enemy once, and amplifies subsequent damage from Beastmaster and his units.
5168.lore_loc: While learning to maneuver in nature alone, the Beastmaster also mastered the use of a pair of tomahawks, adept at cutting down trees as well as adversaries.
notes_loc: This ability destroys trees.
5168.scepter_loc: Causes Wild Axes to have no cooldown and can be used again once they come back.

7230.name: beastmaster_call_of_the_wild_boar
7230.desc_loc: Beastmaster calls forth a Boar to aid in the battlefield.
7230.lore_loc: After befriending the strange beast of his childhood, Beastmaster has learned to call to animals in times of need.

7231.name: beastmaster_call_of_the_wild_hawk
7231.desc_loc: Beastmaster sends an invisible Hawk to scout an area.
7231.lore_loc: After befriending the strange beast of his childhood, Beastmaster has learned to call to animals in times of need.
7231.shard_loc: Reduces Hawk cooldown by 15 seconds. Hawks gains Dive Bomb. Channels for 1 second, revealing itself, and then flies towards the target enemy, dealing 250 damage and stunning them for 2 seconds, killing the hawk. Cast Range: 1200.

5172.name: beastmaster_inner_beast
5172.desc_loc: Untaps the inner fury of nearby allies, passively increasing their attack speed.
5172.lore_loc: Beastmaster's ability to incite the innate strength of animals was seen in the mauling of the king of Slom.

5177.name: beastmaster_primal_roar
5177.desc_loc: Beastmaster lets loose a deafening roar that stuns, and shoves open a path to its target. All units in the path of the roar are damaged, while units shoved aside by the roar have their movement and attack speed slowed. Additionally, Beastmaster and his units gain %movement_speed%%% movement speed for 3 seconds.
5177.lore_loc: The Beastmaster has learned to channel his primal instincts into an animalistic roar, causing devastation in the ranks of enemies.
5177.shard_loc: Causes anyone that attacks a Primal Roar target to deal 1.3x Critical Strike.

901.name: special_bonus_unique_beastmaster_9
901.name_loc: +{s:value}% Wild Axes Damage Amp Per Stack

5173.name: queenofpain_shadow_strike
5173.desc_loc: Hurls a poisoned dagger which deals large initial damage, and then deals damage over time. The poisoned unit has its movement speed slowed for %abilityduration% seconds.  An instance of damage is dealt every %damage_interval% seconds.
5173.lore_loc: Akasha's envenomed dagger allows her to delight in the drawn out suffering of her victims.
notes_loc: The affected unit slowly regains its original movement speed every second during the duration.
Units afflicted by Shadow Strike can be denied by their allies when their HP drops below 25% of their maximum health.

5174.name: queenofpain_blink
5174.desc_loc: Short distance teleportation that allows Queen of Pain to move in and out of combat.
5174.lore_loc: The Secret Queen lives up to her title, making her pain impossible to escape.
notes_loc: You can use Blink to dodge incoming projectiles.
5174.shard_loc: Releases a sonic boom when Queen of Pain blinks, at both her starting and ending locations. Deals 175 damage in a 300 AoE and silences for 1.75 seconds.

5175.name: queenofpain_scream_of_pain
5175.desc_loc: The Queen of Pain lets loose a piercing scream around her, damaging nearby enemies.
5175.lore_loc: The sultry voice of Akasha beckons her opponents while stealing their souls.
notes_loc: Scream Of Pain will hit invisible units.
Scream Of Pain cannot be disjointed.

5176.name: queenofpain_sonic_wave
5176.desc_loc: Creates a gigantic wave of sound in front of Queen of Pain, dealing heavy damage to all enemy units in its wake and pushing them back.
5176.lore_loc: Her most exquisite of all of torments, Akasha's Sonic Wave puts her poor foes out of their misery.
notes_loc: Sonic Wave can hit units up to 1150 units away.

5178.name: venomancer_venomous_gale
5178.desc_loc: Launches a ball of venom in a line, poisoning enemy units so that they take both initial damage and damage over time, as well as suffering slowed movement.  Venomous Gale deals damage every 3 seconds over its duration.
5178.lore_loc: A concoction of various stings, poisons, and toxins gathered from the jungles of Jidi Isle, victims surviving it are rare.
notes_loc: Venomous Gale can be lethal. Units afflicted by Venomous Gale can be denied when their HP drops below 25%.
Duration damage is dealt every %tick_interval% seconds.
Slow starts at %movement_slow%%%, and decreases as time passes.
5178.shard_loc: Causes Venomous Gale to summon two Plague Wards when it impacts an enemy hero. Increases travel range by 400.

5179.name: venomancer_poison_sting
5179.desc_loc: Adds poison damage to Venomancer's normal attacks and slowing movement speed.
5179.lore_loc: The paralytic sting of the creature which caused his transformation now belongs to the Venomancer.
notes_loc: Poison Sting damage can be lethal.
Damage from Poison Sting does not interrupt healing from items, nor does it activate the cooldown on Blink Dagger.

5180.name: venomancer_plague_ward
5180.desc_loc: Summons a plague ward to attack enemy units and structures. The ward is immune to magic. Wards gain the Poison Sting level from Venomancer, dealing 50% of the full damage.
5180.lore_loc: A mixture of his old herbalist talents and newfound toxic mastery creates a living embodiment of plague.

5181.name: venomancer_poison_nova
5181.desc_loc: A spreading ring of poison that does damage over time to enemy units around Venomancer.  Poison Nova cannot deal lethal damage; targets will be left with at least 1 health.
5181.lore_loc: In the Acid Jungles, creatures releasing noxious poison to their attackers is common; Venomancer spreads this plague beyond the Jidi Isle.

5182.name: faceless_void_time_walk
5182.desc_loc: Rushes to a target location while backtracking any damage taken the last %backtrack_duration% seconds.
5182.lore_loc: Darkterror tears a hole in time, passing through Claszureme, and appearing back in an instant.
notes_loc: Faceless Void is invulnerable while using Time Walk.
5182.shard_loc: Grants Reverse Time Walk and increases Time Walk cast range by 400.
5182.scepter_loc: Applies a Time Lock proc to all units at the landing destination.

5691.name: faceless_void_time_dilation
5691.desc_loc: Faceless Void traps all nearby enemies in a time dilation field for %duration% seconds, extending their cooldowns and slowing their movement and attack speed by %slow%%% for each cooldown extended. Deals damage per second for each cooldown.
5691.lore_loc: For those facing off against Darkterror, each moment seems to stretch into eternity.
notes_loc: Does not affect item cooldowns.

5184.name: faceless_void_time_lock
5184.desc_loc: Adds the chance for an attack to lock an enemy unit in time while attacking it a second time.
5184.lore_loc: The strike of the Faceless Void lands with dimension shifting force.

8030.name: faceless_void_time_walk_reverse
8030.desc_loc: Replaces Time Walk with Reverse Time Walk for 1.5 seconds after landing. If used in this period, you will reverse your time walk back to your previous cast location. Does not affect health or proc scepter hits.

5185.name: faceless_void_chronosphere
5185.desc_loc: Creates a blister in spacetime, trapping all units caught in its sphere of influence and causes you to move very quickly inside it.  Only Faceless Void and any units he controls are unaffected.  Invisible enemies in the sphere will be revealed.
