5185.lore_loc: When a rift opens to Claszureme, all poor souls caught within will likely never return.
notes_loc: Pauses all units and buildings, friendly or enemy, except those owned by Faceless Void.
Faceless Void is never affected by Chronospheres with any owner.

7001.name: special_bonus_unique_faceless_void_4
7001.desc_loc: Grants a {s:dodge_chance_pct}% chance to avoid damage entirely.

5086.name: skeleton_king_hellfire_blast
5086.desc_loc: Wraith King sears an enemy unit with spectral fire, dealing damage and stunning, then dealing damage over time and slowing the target.
5086.lore_loc: Ostarion calls on his damned lineage, laying waste to his opponents.
notes_loc: If Wraith King has summoned skeletons, casting Wraithfire Blast on a target will order all of the skeletons to attack that target.

5087.name: skeleton_king_vampiric_aura
5087.desc_loc: Restore health based on the damage Wraith King deals when attacking enemy units. Can be cast to summon skeletons with Vampiric Spirit. Every two kills on an enemy unit adds a skeleton charge. Skeletons respawn once when killed.
5087.lore_loc: Wraith King's blade drains his enemy's essence to feed his aura.

5088.name: skeleton_king_mortal_strike
5088.desc_loc: Wraith King passively deals bonus damage on an attack with a cooldown.
5088.lore_loc: One blow to crush a foe.
notes_loc: Summoned skeletons will automatically attack any unit targeted by Wraithfire Blast.

5089.name: skeleton_king_reincarnation
5089.desc_loc: Wraith King's form regroups after death, allowing him to resurrect when killed in battle.  Upon death, enemy units in a %slow_radius% radius will be slowed.
5089.lore_loc: Conspirators against the Wraith King wonder why he never stays dead.
notes_loc: Wraith King won't revive if he doesn't have enough mana.
If Wraith King has an Aegis and Reincarnation off cooldown, Reincarnation will trigger first.
Revives with full HP and Mana.
Credit for allies whose death was delayed will go to whoever struck the original killing blow.
Wraith Delay affects Wraith King's actual deaths, not Reincarnate deaths.
5089.shard_loc: Causes Reincarnation to have no mana cost and spawn three skeletons to attack each nearby enemy hero when Reincarnation is triggered.
5089.scepter_loc: If a nearby allied hero is slain, they will be transformed into a wraith and have their death delayed for %scepter_duration% seconds. Buffs the transformed units with +70 attack speed and +25%% movement speed.

6566.name: special_bonus_unique_wraith_king_4
6566.desc_loc: Instead of being slowed, all enemy units within 900 range have the current level of Wraithfire Blast cast on them when Reincarnation triggers.

5090.name: death_prophet_carrion_swarm
5090.desc_loc: Sends a swarm of winged beasts to savage enemy units in front of Death Prophet.
5090.lore_loc: Krobelus' many trips to the grave gather a flock of the damned.
notes_loc: Can hit units up to 1110 range away.

5091.name: death_prophet_silence
5091.desc_loc: Prevents enemy units in a target area from casting spells.
5091.lore_loc: Peering into the veil of her opponent's demise, Krobelus sees a silent future.
notes_loc: Doesn't prevent usage of items.

5685.name: death_prophet_spirit_siphon
5685.desc_loc: Creates a spirit link between Death Prophet and an enemy unit, draining %damage% + %damage_pct%%% Max HP per second from the enemy.
5685.lore_loc: Krobelus willingly shows others the path she alone cannot follow.
notes_loc: Cannot cast multiple on same target.
5685.shard_loc: Increases Spirit Siphon charges by 1 and causes enemies to be feared for 2 seconds if they are siphoned for 4 seconds consecutively.

5093.name: death_prophet_exorcism
5093.desc_loc: Unleashes evil spirits to drain the life of nearby enemy units and structures. At the end of the spell's duration, Death Prophet is healed in proportion to the damage dealt. Lasts %abilityduration% seconds.
5093.lore_loc: Over time, the banshee remnants of her previous lives return to haunt the present.
notes_loc: Radius represents the area in which the spirits will acquire targets around Death Prophet.
Spirit damage isn't reduced by damage block abilities.
5093.scepter_loc: Whenever an enemy is affected by Death Prophet's spells or when she attacks an enemy, a ghost will fly out, slow and hit the enemy for bonus its usual damage then return to her with life.

5190.name: phantom_assassin_stifling_dagger
5190.desc_loc: Throws a dagger slowing the enemy unit's movement speed, dealing %base_damage%+%attack_factor_tooltip%%% of Phantom Assassin's attack damage as physical damage and applying attack effects from items and abilities.
5190.lore_loc: The first skill learned by the Sisters of the Veil often signals an incoming hit.
notes_loc: If an attack effect is chance-based, the chance of its application will be the same as its chance to occur.
Spell-immune enemies are not affected by Stifling Dagger's slow.

5191.name: phantom_assassin_phantom_strike
5191.desc_loc: Teleports to a unit, friendly or enemy, and grants bonus attack speed while attacking if it's an enemy unit.
5191.lore_loc: Mortred's silken veil is the last thing her unfortunate target sees.

5192.name: phantom_assassin_blur
5192.desc_loc:
Phantom Assassin focuses inward, increasing her ability to evade enemy attacks. Can be activated to blur her body, causing her to be impossible to see until near enemy heroes.

Stacks diminishingly with other sources of Evasion.
5192.lore_loc: Meditation allows a Veiled Sister to carefully anticipate her opponents in combat.
5192.shard_loc: Increases your movement speed by 40% while in Blur's active.
5192.scepter_loc: Causes Blur to have instant cast time and applies a dispel. Anytime Phantom Assassin gets a hero kill, her abilities are refreshed. Reduces Blur cooldown and increases Fade Time to 0.75.

662.name: phantom_assassin_fan_of_knives
662.desc_loc: Phantom Assassin releases sharp blades around her in a 550 AoE, dealing 16% of a victim's max health on impact and applying break for 3 seconds.

5193.name: phantom_assassin_coup_de_grace
5193.desc_loc: Phantom Assassin refines her combat abilities, gaining a chance of delivering a devastating critical strike to enemy units. Stifling Dagger shares the same critical strike chance.
5193.lore_loc: A divine strike, Mortred honors her opponent by choosing them for death.

6192.name: special_bonus_unique_phantom_assassin
6192.desc_loc: Launches a two extra Stifling Daggers towards random visible enemies within the cast range.

5186.name: pugna_nether_blast
5186.desc_loc: An exploding pulse deals damage to enemies and structures in the area.  Deals half damage to structures.
5186.lore_loc: The Arts of Oblivion include a deafening blast of emerald flames from the Nether Reaches.
notes_loc: Damage is delayed by %delay% seconds.

5187.name: pugna_decrepify
5187.desc_loc: A powerful banishing spell that slows a unit and renders it unable to attack or be attacked. Afflicted units take extra magic damage.
5187.lore_loc: A now-mastered relic from his childhood, Pugna delights in banishing others into the Nether Realm, whether for good, evil, or simple enjoyment.
notes_loc: Only magical and pure damage can affect a unit under the effects of Decrepify.
Doesn't slow allied units.
Can be used on your Nether Ward.

5188.name: pugna_nether_ward
5188.desc_loc: Pugna places a Nether Ward at the target location. The ward causes nearby enemy heroes to lose a percentage of their max mana every second, and will fire at any enemy hero who casts a spell. Nether Ward deals base damage plus the damage multiplier of the mana spent by the enemy hero.
5188.lore_loc: While at the lamasery for the Arts of Oblivion, Pugna learned to dominate his classmates with a simple ward charged with Nether magic.
notes_loc: Nether Ward deals damage before the actual spell is cast, so if the caster dies the spell will have no effect.
Nether Ward can be decrepified.
Illusions and creeps deal 25% damage to Nether Ward.

5189.name: pugna_life_drain
5189.desc_loc:
CHANNELED - When cast on an enemy, Pugna drains health from the target enemy unit to heal himself and granting vision over the target. If Pugna has full HP, and the enemy target is a Hero, Life Drain will restore mana instead.

When cast on an ally, Pugna will drain his own health into his ally.
5189.lore_loc: Pugna has truly become more powerful than even the grandmaster of Oblivion.
notes_loc: Health gained depends on the actual damage dealt.
Illusions are destroyed on the first tick of damage.
5189.shard_loc: For every 1.5 seconds of channel, another secondary Life Drain is created targeting another random enemy hero.

5194.name: templar_assassin_refraction
5194.desc_loc: Templar Assassin becomes highly elusive, avoiding damage and gaining a bonus to her damage.  The damage and avoidance effects are separate, and have a limited number of instances.
5194.lore_loc: Manipulating her psionic veil, Lanaya bends nature's law to her will.
notes_loc: Damage as HP Removal bypasses Refraction (it won't reduce the charges).
Only instances of %damage_threshold% or more damage will trigger Refraction.
Refraction is visible to enemies.

5195.name: templar_assassin_meld
5195.desc_loc: Templar Assassin conceals herself, becoming invisible as long as she remains still.  If Meld's invisibility is broken by attacking an enemy, Lanaya will deal bonus damage to the enemy and reduce their armor for %abilityduration% seconds.
5195.lore_loc: Lanaya is as elusive as her covenant with the Hidden Temple.
notes_loc: Meld is broken by any action other than staying in position.
Meld's armor reduction does not work against towers.

5196.name: templar_assassin_psi_blades
5196.desc_loc: Templar Assassin's psi blades slice through the attacked unit, splitting and damaging enemy units directly behind it, while gaining bonus attack range.
5196.lore_loc: Her blades pierce the skin as much as the mind, furthering her understanding of the mystery that is reality.
notes_loc: Split damage hits invisible units.
Attack effects like Bash will only be applied to the main target.

7853.name: templar_assassin_trap_teleport
7853.desc_loc: Allows Templar Assassin to teleport to any Psionic Trap after a brief channel. Does not break meld. Detonates the Psionic Trap on arrival.
7853.lore_loc: In reward for her service, Lanaya has been granted access to secrets that unlock new techniques for her psionic gifts.

5197.name: templar_assassin_psionic_trap
5197.desc_loc: Templar Assassin places mystical traps that invisibly monitor enemy movement. When sprung at her command, they exert a slowing influence of %movement_speed_min%%% in the area. Traps charge up to slow %movement_speed_max%%% after %trap_max_charge_duration% seconds. Deals bonus damage when fully charged.
5197.lore_loc: Calling upon the reach of the Hidden Temple, none escape the eye of the Templar.
notes_loc: Traps last indefinitely.
They have invisibility that fades in over %trap_fade_time% seconds, spell immunity, and 100 HP.
Traps have 400/400 vision range and don't prevent neutral camps from spawning.
5197.shard_loc: Causes Psionic Traps to silence enemies for up to 3.5 seconds based on how long the trap has been charged. Increases max trap count by 4 and vision by 125.

6939.name: special_bonus_unique_templar_assassin_4
6939.desc_loc: Applies a basic dispel to Templar Assassin.

5218.name: viper_poison_attack
5218.desc_loc: Intensifies Viper's venom, adding an effect to his normal attack that applies a stacking movement speed slow and magic resistance deduction while dealing damage over time. Stacks up to %max_stacks% times.
5218.lore_loc: The Netherdrake's inborn toxic breath quickly drains the vitality of its afflicted.
5218.shard_loc: Causes Poison Attack to lower armor by 1 per stack and allows it to affect buildings for 40% poison damage. Increases max stacks by 3.

5219.name: viper_nethertoxin
5219.desc_loc: Viper releases a Nethertoxin at the targeted area. Units in that area take an increasing damage over time based on how long they remain in it. Disables passives of affected units.
5219.lore_loc: Poison from the Nether Reaches turns wounds into fatalities, and fatigue into death.

5220.name: viper_corrosive_skin
5220.desc_loc: Viper exudes an infectious toxin that damages and slows the attack speed of any enemy that damages it in a %max_range_tooltip% radius. The acid exudate also increases Viper's resistance to magic.
5220.lore_loc: It is not unusual for sword and shield alike to corrode in the very hands of those who attack the Netherdrake.
notes_loc: Stacks multiplicatively with other magic damage resistance sources.

5221.name: viper_viper_strike
5221.desc_loc: Viper slows the targeted enemy unit's movement and attack speed while also dealing poison damage over time.  The slowing effect reduces over the duration of the poison.
5221.lore_loc: Once used to slay his sadistic summoner, the most powerful of Netherdrake infections spreads through the veins of those foolish enough to cross Viper.
5221.scepter_loc: Decreases mana cost and cooldown. Increases cast range.

5222.name: luna_lucent_beam
5222.desc_loc: Calls a beam of lunar energy down upon an enemy, damaging and briefly stunning them.
5222.lore_loc: Selemene smites those who encroach upon the Nightsilver Woods.
5222.shard_loc: Allows Lucent beam to be ground targeted with a 325 target search radius. Also releases attacks on up to two random targets within 500 range of the Lucent Beam. Reduces mancost by 50.

5223.name: luna_moon_glaive
5223.desc_loc: Empowers Luna's glaives, causing her attacks to bounce between enemy units. Deals less damage with each bounce.
5223.lore_loc: Carefully sharpened, Luna's boomerang-like weapon cuts a wide swath through enemy numbers.
notes_loc: Moon Glaives do not proc any attack modifier except Critical Strikes.

5224.name: luna_lunar_blessing
5224.desc_loc: Increases the attack damage for Luna and nearby allied heroes. Luna is also blessed with increased vision range at night.
5224.lore_loc: The Goddess of the Moon smiles upon her kin.

5225.name: luna_eclipse
5225.desc_loc: Showers random nearby enemies with strikes from Luna's current level of Lucent Beam. These beams do not stun their targets, and there is a maximum number of times that a single target can be struck. Also turns day into night for %night_duration% seconds.
5225.lore_loc: In times of great need, Selemene herself descends into the world, blocking out the light and hope of the opposed.
notes_loc: Eclipse doesn't work if Luna doesn't have any points in Lucent Beam.
Beams will stop if Luna is killed.
Will not hit invisible units.
There is a %beam_interval% seconds gap between beams, %beam_interval_scepter% seconds with scepter.
5225.scepter_loc: Allows Luna to cast Eclipse on an allied unit or herself and have its effects follow them, or cast it on an area. Also increases total beams and duration, removes the limit on beams per unit, and makes the beams appear twice as fast.

5226.name: dragon_knight_breathe_fire
5226.desc_loc: Unleashes a breath of fire in front of Dragon Knight that burns enemies and reduces the damage their attacks deal.
5226.lore_loc: Knight Davion's breath has become that of the mighty Eldwurm Slyrak, remembered for burning numerous other knights to a crisp.
notes_loc: Hits units up to 900 away.

5227.name: dragon_knight_dragon_tail
5227.desc_loc: Dragon Knight smites an enemy unit in melee range with his shield, stunning it while dealing minor damage.  When in Elder Dragon Form, the cast range increases to %dragon_cast_range%.
5227.lore_loc: Davion's combination of dragon talents and knightly skills makes him a vicious opponent in melee combat.

5228.name: dragon_knight_dragon_blood
5228.desc_loc: The life blood of the Dragon improves health regeneration and strengthens armor.
5228.lore_loc: Slyrak's blood still courses through Davion's veins, giving him twice the vitality of an ordinary knight.

660.name: dragon_knight_fireball
660.desc_loc: Ignites a %radius% AoE area for %duration% seconds, dealing %damage% damage per second to enemies in it. Has reduced cast range when melee.

5229.name: dragon_knight_elder_dragon_form
5229.desc_loc:
Dragon Knight takes the form of one of three powerful elder dragons, increasing his speed, and Dragon Tail's range, while granting him new powers.
<font color="#9acd32">LEVEL 1 Green Dragon</font> - Corrosive Breath: attacks deal %corrosive_breath_damage% poison damage per second for %corrosive_breath_duration% seconds. Works on structures.
<font color="#ff0000">LEVEL 2 Red Dragon</font> - Splash Attack: attacks damage all enemy units in a %splash_radius% radius for %splash_damage_percent%%% damage, with Corrosive Breath added to the targets.
<font color="#87ceeb">LEVEL 3 Blue Dragon</font> - Frost Breath: slows movement speed by %frost_bonus_movement_speed%%% and attack speed by %frost_bonus_attack_speed% of enemy units in Splash Attack range for %frost_duration% seconds, with Corrosive Breath added to the targets.
5229.lore_loc: The dormant dragon power springs forth from within Davion, combining the powers of a legendary knight with a legendary Eldwurm.
notes_loc: Corrosive Breath poison damage is lethal.
Cooldowns of items that are different for ranged and melee units will be based on which form Dragon Knight was in when the item was used.
5229.shard_loc: Grants Elder Dragon Form the Fireball ability.
5229.scepter_loc: Increases the level of Dragon Knight's ultimate. Adds a 4th level, Black Dragon. Black Dragon has bonus Corrosive Damage, Splash Damage and Slow amount, increased Magic Resistance and free pathing.

742.name: special_bonus_unique_dragon_knight_8
742.name_loc: +{s:value} AoE Dragon Tail During Elder Dragon Form

5233.name: dazzle_poison_touch
5233.desc_loc: Releases a cone of poison that strikes multiple enemy units. Deals damage over time and slows the targets. Anytime the targets get attacked, the debuff duration is refreshed.
5233.lore_loc: One of the few Dezun rites used for offensive purposes, the paralytic enchantment often proves useful.
notes_loc: The damage is not reduced by damage block abilities.
5233.shard_loc: Causes Poison Touch to hex affected targets for 1.25 seconds.

5234.name: dazzle_shallow_grave
5234.desc_loc: An ally blessed with Shallow Grave, no matter how close to death, cannot die while under its protection.
5234.lore_loc: Only a seasoned acolyte of the Shadow can properly perform the rite of preventing death.
notes_loc: HP cannot go below 1 while under the effects of Shallow Grave, but Axe's Culling Blade will still kill the hero.

5235.name: dazzle_shadow_wave
5235.desc_loc: Sends out a bolt of power that arcs between allies, healing them while damaging any units standing nearby.  Dazzle is always healed by Shadow Wave.
5235.lore_loc: While it is a simplistic and routine rite among Shadow Priests, the Shadow Wave is also the most critical for success.
notes_loc: Prioritizes allied heroes over creeps.
If enemies are near multiple allied units affected by Shadow Wave, they will take multiple instances of damage.
5235.scepter_loc: Causes Shadow Wave to dispel allies. Increases heal by +100 and damage by +100.

7304.name: dazzle_bad_juju
7304.desc_loc: Passively reduces cooldowns on Dazzle's abilities and items. Anytime he casts a spell, all nearby enemies will have their armor reduced. Debuff stacks and refreshes duration.
7304.lore_loc: Each invocation of the Nothl realm helps it further permeate the surroundings of our own.
7304.shard_loc: Causes Dazzle to launch an attack at the three closest enemies within 1200 range each time he casts an ability.

5237.name: rattletrap_battery_assault
5237.desc_loc: Discharges high-powered shrapnel at random nearby enemy units, dealing minor magical damage and ministun.
5237.lore_loc: Some of Rattletrap's contraptions don't quite work correctly, so detonating them proves useful as an offensive maneuver.
notes_loc: Deals damage every %interval% seconds.
Remains active if Clockwerk is disabled.

5238.name: rattletrap_power_cogs
5238.desc_loc: Forms a barrier of energized cogs around Clockwerk, trapping any units that are near.  Enemies outside the trap that touch a cog are knocked back, losing health and mana. Once a cog has delivered a shock, it will power down.  Cogs can be destroyed by enemy attacks, but Clockwerk can destroy them with just one.
5238.lore_loc: One of Clockwerk's inventions of which he is most proud is the power cog - though it is sometimes despised by his allies.
notes_loc: Cogs can shock invisible units.

5239.name: rattletrap_rocket_flare
5239.desc_loc: Fires a global range flare that explodes over a given area, damaging enemies and providing vision for %duration% seconds.
5239.lore_loc: What started as a festive display has become a useful scouting and bombardment tool.

321.name: rattletrap_overclocking
321.desc_loc: Resets Clockwerk's ability cooldowns and grants him bonus movement and attack speed for a duration. Clockwerk becomes stunned after the duration runs out.
321.lore_loc: Rattletrap understands the limitations of his armor. Just as he understands the risks of pushing past them in times of need.

630.name: rattletrap_jetpack
630.desc_loc: Rises up, granting Clockwerk flying vision, flying movement, and a %bonus_speed%%% bonus movement speed. Clockwerk has a severely-limited turn rate during this time and cannot attack. Lasts up to %duration% seconds or until he casts Hookshot.

5240.name: rattletrap_hookshot
5240.desc_loc: Fires a grappling device rapidly at the target location.  If the hook hits a unit, Clockwerk launches himself into the target, stunning and dealing damage.  Any enemies Clockwerk collides with along the way are damaged and stunned.
5240.lore_loc: A somewhat unwieldy device, the Hookshot sends the otherwise clunky Clockwerk armor flying through the air.
notes_loc: Hookshot will latch and take Clockwerk to allies, but not damage or disable them.

5241.name: leshrac_split_earth
5241.desc_loc: Splits the earth under enemies. Deals damage and stuns for a short duration.
5241.lore_loc: Twisting nature to his vile will, the shifting earth consumes those unlucky enough to cross Leshrac's path.
notes_loc: Split Earth will destroy trees in its area of effect.
There is a %delay% second delay before the effect is applied.
5241.shard_loc: Causes Split Earth to repeat in the same location three additional times, with a 5 second delay between each one. Each time the radius increases by 75. Split Earth echo location is visible to both teams.

5242.name: leshrac_diabolic_edict
5242.desc_loc: Saturates the area around Leshrac with magical explosions that deal physical damage to enemy units and structures.  The fewer units available to attack, the more damage those units will take.  Deals %tower_bonus%%% more damage to towers.  Lasts %abilityduration% seconds.
5242.lore_loc: Chronoptic energy bursts from one plane to the other, evaporating anything it touches.
notes_loc: Damage is not reduced by damage block.
The explosions will continue even if Leshrac is killed.
Can damage buildings, Spell Immune units, and invisible units.

5243.name: leshrac_lightning_storm
5243.desc_loc: Summons a lightning storm that blasts the target enemy unit, then strikes any nearby enemy units. Struck enemies are slowed.
5243.lore_loc: The Tormented Soul's mastery of the elements is evident in the massive storms that strike down armies before him.

539.name: leshrac_greater_lightning_storm
539.desc_loc: Causes all nearby enemies in %radius% AoE to turn ethereal, preventing them from attacking, causing them to take %magic_amp%%% more magic damage and be slowed by %slow%%% for %duration% seconds. Increases Leshrac's speed rather than reducing it. Does not cause you to take amplified damage.

5244.name: leshrac_pulse_nova
5244.desc_loc: Creates waves of damaging energy around Leshrac, one per second, to damage nearby enemy units. Drains Leshrac's mana with each pulse.
5244.lore_loc: If necessary, the Tormented Soul can manipulate space time itself, ravaging lesser beings.

5245.name: furion_sprout
5245.desc_loc: Sprouts a ring of trees around a unit, trapping it in place, and providing vision in a %vision_range% radius.
5245.lore_loc: Verdant overgrowth is a common ailment reported by Nature's Prophet's attackers.
notes_loc: Sprout can be cast on any unit, or the ground.
Trees created by Sprout have the same interactions with abilities as regular trees.
5245.shard_loc: Causes the first two trees destroyed with Sprout to summon Greater Treants. Can only have two Greater Treants alive.

5246.name: furion_teleportation
5246.desc_loc: Teleports to any point on the map.
5246.lore_loc: The Prophet keeps his sentinel over the forest, protecting it when in need.
notes_loc: Mana and cooldown take effect when the cast is completed.  Nature's Prophet will not use any mana or waste the cooldown if the spell is interrupted while casting.
When the cast begins, an effect is created at the target location, which is visible to allies and enemies.

5247.name: furion_force_of_nature
5247.desc_loc: Converts an area of trees into Treants under the command of Nature's Prophet.
5247.lore_loc: Verodicia bestowed the Prophet with the ability to summon the Treant Guard, a mythical sentient army of the wild.
notes_loc: Nature's Call can only create as many treants as there are trees in the target area.

5248.name: furion_wrath_of_nature
5248.desc_loc: Damaging energy bounces around the map, striking enemies close to the cast point that are in vision. Each enemy hit beyond the first adds damage. Enemies that die under this spell grant you bonus damage for %kill_damage_duration% seconds.
5248.lore_loc: Nature's Prophet calls Verodicia's fury to strike down those who might ravage the wilderness.
notes_loc: Wrath of Nature will not hit units out of vision.
Can be cast through the minimap; the nearest valid target will be selected.
5248.scepter_loc: Lowers cooldown from 85 to 60. Entangles all enemies it hits. Duration scales from 2 up to 3.8 seconds at max bounce.

5249.name: life_stealer_rage
5249.desc_loc:
Launch into a maddened rage, becoming Spell Immune, and gaining increased movement speed.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
5249.lore_loc: The madness and brutality of N'aix makes him a vicious and unrelenting foe in combat.
notes_loc: Upon casting, many buffs and debuffs will be removed.

5250.name: life_stealer_feast
5250.desc_loc: Lifestealer's attacks deal damage and provide heal for a percentage of his target's max health.
5250.lore_loc: After escaping from his cell in Devarque, N'aix subsisted on flesh and bones of those unfortunate to cross his path.
notes_loc: Does not affect Roshan.
Affects Spell Immune units.
The heal is independent of the damage.
Stacks additively with other sources of Lifesteal.

631.name: life_stealer_ghoul_frenzy
631.desc_loc: Passively causes Lifestealer's attacks to significantly slow enemy movement speed for %duration% seconds. Grants you Attack Speed.

5251.name: life_stealer_open_wounds
5251.desc_loc: Lifestealer rends an enemy unit, slowing the victim's movement speed and allowing all allies to regain health for a percentage of the damage they deal to that unit. All damage dealt will steal life, including damage from spells. The victim recovers movement speed over the duration. Deals 2% of the target's max health per attack on the target from real heroes.
5251.lore_loc: Fresh wounds and the scent of blood often draw out the scavengers to finish the job.
notes_loc: Open Wounds slows over 8 different steps: 50% / 50% / 40% / 30% / 20% / 10% / 10% / 10%, with the slow decreasing one step per second.
Stacks additively with other sources of Lifesteal.

5252.name: life_stealer_infest
5252.desc_loc:
Lifestealer infests the body of a target unit, becoming undetectable, and healing for a portion of his max hitpoints every second while inside. He can then explode from the host body, dealing damage to nearby enemies. If the infested unit is an enemy creep or a neutral creep, he can take control of the unit's ability to move and attack. Does not work on enemy heroes.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
5252.lore_loc: With this infestation, N'aix consumes the life blood of the host, restoring him back to full unholy power.
notes_loc: If the infested unit dies before Lifestealer consumes it, no health is gained.
Lifestealer gains experience while under the effects of Infest.
Creeps that are controlled while Infested share Lifestealer's movement speed.
Infest Level 2 and 3 can be used on Ancient creeps.
5252.scepter_loc: Allows Infesting enemy heroes for 5 seconds, attacking their insides once every 1.25 seconds and doubling Lifestealer's regen rate. Increases cast range to 500 and reduces cooldown to 20 seconds.

5255.name: dark_seer_vacuum
5255.desc_loc: Dark Seer creates a vacuum over the target area that sucks in enemy units, disrupting them and dealing damage.
5255.lore_loc: Ish'Kafel modifies the center of gravity to a place of his choosing.
notes_loc: This ability interrupts channeling.
Pulls units over %duration% seconds before dealing damage.
Trees near the center of the vacuum will be destroyed.

5256.name: dark_seer_ion_shell
5256.desc_loc: Surrounds the target unit with a bristling shield that damages enemy units in an area around it.
5256.lore_loc: The Dark Seer slices holes into the 'Land Behind the Wall,' causing prismatic energy to seep forth.
notes_loc: Deals small amounts of damage in %tick_interval% second intervals.
Doesn't damage the target it is cast on.
If cast on a unit that already has Ion Shell, the new Shell replaces the old one.
5256.scepter_loc: Causes Ion Shell to have 2 Charges, increases duration by 20 seconds and provides +300 Health.

5257.name: dark_seer_surge
5257.desc_loc: Charges a target friendly unit with power, giving it a brief burst of movement speed and removes unit collisions. Allows the unit to reach maximum movement speed and cannot be slowed.
5257.lore_loc: Ish'Kafel once used his speed of mind to navigate the maze between the walls.
notes_loc: Units with Surge cannot be slowed unless the Surge effect is removed.

687.name: dark_seer_normal_punch
687.desc_loc: Grants Normal Punch. Passive cooldown attack. Causes Dark Seer's next attack on a hero to knock an illusion out of the victim and stun them for up to 2.25 seconds, 350 distance and 250 damage based on how far Dark Seer has moved in the past 3 seconds. Max power is reached after 900 distance moved. Illusions lasts for 5 seconds. Cooldown: 14

5258.name: dark_seer_wall_of_replica
5258.desc_loc: Raises a wall of warping light that slows and creates replicas of any enemy hero who crosses it. Enemy replicas serve at the Dark Seer's will. Replicas last until they are destroyed, or until the wall's duration ends.
5258.lore_loc: The Dark Seer, while unable to return to his natural realm, can channel part of the prismatic wall with powerful strength of mind, sowing confusion amongst enemy ranks.
notes_loc: Doesn't create illusions from other illusions.
There cannot be more than one illusion per player per wall.
Wall of replica will not slow spell-immune enemies.

7046.name: special_bonus_unique_dark_seer_4
7046.desc_loc: A second Wall of Replica is created {s:value} units behind the first wall.  Illusions are independent for each Wall.

5259.name: clinkz_strafe
5259.desc_loc: Clinkz nimbly attacks with a barrage of arrows. Gains 100% evasion from ranged attackers and dramatically increases attack speed for a short time.
5259.lore_loc: It's hard to say whether the blur around the Bone Fletcher is from his flaming heart or his speed with the quiver.

5260.name: clinkz_searing_arrows
5260.desc_loc: Imbues Clinkz's arrows with fire for extra damage.
5260.lore_loc: Clinkz simply lights his arrows from his flaming essence for quite the destructive effect.
notes_loc: Searing Arrows deal damage to structures.
The damage is directly added to Clinkz' attack damage, as physical damage.

5261.name: clinkz_wind_walk
5261.desc_loc: Clinkz moves invisibly through units until the moment he attacks or uses items.
5261.lore_loc: With a burst of fire and puff of smoke, the Bone Fletcher was nowhere to be seen.
notes_loc: Will not break most channeling of spells or items upon activation.
Has a fadetime of %fade_time% seconds.
5261.shard_loc: Causes Skeleton Walk to create two Burning Army Skeletons.

7319.name: clinkz_burning_army
7319.desc_loc: Clinkz summons an army of fiery ranged skeleton archers. Archers are immobile and die with 2 attacks from a hero. Skeletons deal a percentage of Clinkz' damage, use his current Searing Arrows ability and attack only heroes. Attack range is equal to Clinkz's attack range.
7319.lore_loc: Existing on the brink of life and death, Clinkz has learned to temporarily bridge the gap between the two.

5262.name: clinkz_death_pact
5262.desc_loc: Clinkz consumes the target enemy unit or friendly unit, gaining max health and damage based on its current health.
5262.lore_loc: Sutherex' bond of life and death has become a part of Clinkz, and his old bones are refreshed with repetition of the pact on lesser beings.
notes_loc: If the target is an enemy, Clinkz will gain the correct experience and gold.
Increases Clinkz' current and max HP.
When the duration ends, max HP returns to normal, but current HP stays the same.

6620.name: special_bonus_unique_clinkz_3
6620.desc_loc: When using Searing Arrows, a second Searing Arrow targets a random enemy within the spell's range.

5263.name: omniknight_purification
5263.desc_loc: Instantly heals a friendly unit and damages all nearby enemy units.
5263.lore_loc: Priests of the Omniscience are adept at removing impurities from fellow warriors.

5264.name: omniknight_repel
5264.desc_loc:
Creates a divine barrier around an ally which grants them increased Status Resistance, Strength and Health Regeneration.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
5264.lore_loc: When faced with the pit of sacrifice, Purist's resilience to magic was tested and affirmed.

5265.name: omniknight_degen_aura
5265.desc_loc: Greatly degenerates the movement capabilities of enemy units that stray too near.
5265.lore_loc: The holy embodiment of Purist Thunderwrath is enough to weaken those of lesser faith.
notes_loc: Does not affect Spell Immune units.

656.name: omniknight_hammer_of_purity
656.desc_loc: Causes Omniknight's next attack to deal bonus pure damage based on %bonus_damage% plus %base_damage%%% of his base damage. He is healed for the same amount of pure damage. Cooldown: 4

5266.name: omniknight_guardian_angel
5266.desc_loc: Omniknight calls upon a Guardian Angel that grants allies immunity from physical damage.
5266.lore_loc: The All Seeing One casts down his protection over those that Purist calls friend.
notes_loc: Affects allies with spell immunity.
Can be purged.
5266.scepter_loc: Increases duration, provides HP regen, radius becomes global and affects buildings.

5270.name: enchantress_impetus
5270.desc_loc: Places an enchantment on each attack while activated, causing it to deal additional damage based on how far away the target is.  The farther the target, the greater the damage dealt.
5270.lore_loc: While Aiushtha favors peaceful means, she is capable of a magical onslaught from a distance, her spears gaining energy from the natural life around her.
notes_loc: The damage is capped at %distance_cap% distance.
Distance to target is measured when the projectile hits.

5268.name: enchantress_enchant
5268.desc_loc:
Enchantress charms an enemy. If the enemy is a hero, they are slowed. If the enemy is a creep, she brings it under her control, increasing it's attack damage and max health.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
5268.lore_loc: A true steward of the forest, Aiushtha befriends all within it - from lowly trolls to powerful centaurs.
notes_loc: Illusions can be converted.

5269.name: enchantress_natures_attendants
5269.desc_loc: A cloud of wisps heals Enchantress and any friendly units nearby. Lasts %abilityduration% seconds.
5269.lore_loc: Whimsical spirits of the woods possess a healing power that is quite subtle, but gains strength in numbers.
notes_loc: Units with full HP will not be selected for the heal.
Can heal units with spell immunity.
5269.shard_loc: Adds 3 permanent Nature's Attendants that follow Enchantress around.

320.name: enchantress_bunny_hop
320.desc_loc: Leaps backward, dodges incoming projectiles, and launches an Impetus attack on the 3 furthest enemy units within Enchantress' attack range + 200.

5267.name: enchantress_untouchable
5267.desc_loc: Enchantress beguiles her enemies, slowing their attacks when she is attacked.
5267.lore_loc: After attacking Aiushtha, most opponents are overwhelmed with guilt having attacked such a natural beauty.
notes_loc: All units who directly attack Enchantress will get slowed.
The slow is applied on the attacking unit when the attack starts, not when damage is applied.

7300.name: huskar_inner_fire
7300.desc_loc: In a fiery rage, knocks all nearby enemies away from you to a fixed distance, dealing damage and disarming them.
7300.lore_loc: Not even Huskar's own flesh can contain the unending expansion of his life force.
7300.shard_loc: Causes Inner Fire to reduce healing and regeneration by 50%% and applies a 40%% movement speed slow. Lowers cooldown by 3 seconds. Can be cast while disabled.

5272.name: huskar_burning_spear
5272.desc_loc: Huskar sets his spears aflame, dealing damage over time with his regular attack.  Multiple attacks will stack additional damage.  Each attack drains some of Huskar's health.  Lasts %abilityduration% seconds.
5272.lore_loc: The Sacred Warrior ignites his weaponry after marking it with his own blood - causing far greater pain than he himself feels.
notes_loc: Burning Spear stacks additively when used multiple times on one target.  There is no cap.
Huskar cannot kill himself with this skill.

5273.name: huskar_berserkers_blood
5273.desc_loc: Huskar's injuries feed his power, giving increased attack speed and health regen based on missing health. Health regen is a percentage of your strength.
5273.lore_loc: After losing his birthright, Huskar gained a lethality in physical combat that is only heightened as his own blood is spilled.
notes_loc: Bonuses are provided linearly, no bonus at Full HP and full bonus at strictly less than %hp_threshold_max%%% HP.

5274.name: huskar_life_break
5274.desc_loc:
Huskar draws upon his health to break an enemy's life, leaping at a target within attack range to shatter a percentage of that hero's current health, and slowing them.  While leaping, Huskar is Spell Immune.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
5274.lore_loc: No matter the danger, Huskar thrusts himself into melees that only he can survive.
notes_loc: If Huskar is disabled during the charge or the target moves more than 1400 units in 0.015 seconds, the charge stops.
Slow works on Spell Immune units.
Life Break cannot be disjointed.
5274.scepter_loc: Forces the enemy target to attack Huskar and increases cast range.

5275.name: night_stalker_void
5275.desc_loc: Creates a damaging void that slows an enemy unit and deals damage.  Void also mini-stuns, interrupting channeling abilities. The slowing effect lasts longer at night.
5275.lore_loc: Balanar creates a vortex of infinite night, tearing opponents violently into the eternal darkness that once was.
notes_loc: Void does not ministun enemies during the day.
5275.scepter_loc: Causes Void to be an AoE ability. Increases the ministun duration.

5276.name: night_stalker_crippling_fear
5276.desc_loc: Night Stalker horrifies all nearby enemies, causing them to become silenced while near him.  The effect lasts longer at night.
5276.lore_loc: A vision of the twisted maw of Balanar etches itself into the minds of the poor souls unlucky enough to cross his path.

5277.name: night_stalker_hunter_in_the_night
5277.desc_loc: Night Stalker is in his element at night, attacking and moving with great swiftness.
5277.lore_loc: The hunting prowess of Balanar improves as the night beckons.
5277.shard_loc: Night Stalker can cast Hunter in the Night. Consumes a creep, instantly killing it and restoring 35% of Night Stalker's maximum HP and and 25% of maximum mana. Cannot target ancients during the daytime. Cooldown: 20

5278.name: night_stalker_darkness
5278.desc_loc: Night Stalker smothers the sun and summons instant darkness, so that he might use his powers at their fullest. Nightstalker gains flight and bonus damage during this time. Has unobstructed vision.
5278.lore_loc: It is a humbling sight to see when the mightiest of warriors become afraid of the dark.

503.name: special_bonus_unique_night_stalker_5
503.name_loc: +{s:value}% Hunter In The Night Movement Speed

6704.name: special_bonus_unique_night_stalker_2
6704.name_loc: +{s:value} Hunter In The Night Attack Speed

5282.name: broodmother_insatiable_hunger
5282.desc_loc: A violent lust for vital fluids increases Broodmother's attack damage and gives her a vampiric attack.
5282.lore_loc: While most of her prey is wrapped in silken cocoons and saved for her young, the Broodmother herself has a taste for wandering heroes.
notes_loc: Fully stacks with other sources of lifesteal.

5280.name: broodmother_spin_web
5280.desc_loc: Spins a large web that grants Broodmother a passive movement speed increase, gives free movement, and boosts regeneration while in its vicinity. Spin Web charges restore every %charge_restore_time% seconds. Spin Web can be cast from anywhere as long as the new web touches an existing web. Webs never expire, and can be manually destroyed. When the maximum limit of webs is exceeded, the oldest web disappears.
5280.lore_loc: Weaving a bed of silken fibers, Arachnia's web both protects her and her offspring, as well as giving advancing opponents a sense of forboding.
notes_loc: Also affects Spiderling and Spiderites.
If free movement is disabled, you will destroy nearby trees.
5280.scepter_loc: Increases movement speed, and increases Spin Web max count

639.name: broodmother_silken_bola
639.desc_loc: Slows the target enemy, causes them to miss and deals impact damage. Units that attack the target deal bonus magic damage.
639.shard_loc: Causes Silken Bola to be a 550 AoE spell and increases the miss chance to 80%

5279.name: broodmother_spawn_spiderlings
5279.desc_loc: Broodmother injects her young into an enemy unit, dealing damage. The spiderlings will hatch if the target is killed while under this influence.
5279.lore_loc: Black Arachnia continues to raise her young, even amidst the field of combat.  The brood quickly learns how to support their mother.
notes_loc: If the target is killed within %buff_duration% seconds of being hit with this skill, the Spiderlings will spawn.
Units killed by Spiderlings will then give birth to Spiderites, smaller and less powerful versions of the Spiderlings.

5285.name: bounty_hunter_shuriken_toss
5285.desc_loc: Hurls a deadly shuriken at an enemy unit, dealing damage and mini-stunning the target.  The shuriken will bounce to any Tracked units who are within a %bounce_aoe% radius of each other.
5285.lore_loc: While the shuriken may be small, Gondar's precise aim can cause critical damage.
notes_loc: This spell interrupts channeling abilities.
5285.scepter_loc: Upgrades Shuriken Toss. Applies Jinada to it, reduces cooldown and increases cast range.

5286.name: bounty_hunter_jinada
5286.desc_loc: Bounty Hunter plans his next hit, dealing bonus damage and stealing some unreliable gold.
5286.lore_loc: Gondar's vast experience ensures he never walks away from a transaction empty-handed.

5287.name: bounty_hunter_wind_walk
5287.desc_loc: Bounty Hunter becomes invisible and gains the ability to move through other units until he attacks or uses an ability.  If he breaks the invisibility with an attack, that attack will slow the target's movement speed.
5287.lore_loc: The court jesters present during King Goff's assassination can recount no other image than a dancing shadow.
notes_loc: Will not break most channeling of spells upon activation.
5287.shard_loc: Shadow Walk now grants you 35% damage reduction while invisible. Attacking out of invisibility stuns the target for 1 second. Lowers cooldown by 5 seconds.

5288.name: bounty_hunter_track
5288.desc_loc: Tracks an enemy hero, granting True Sight of the target, and information on how much gold it is carrying. Bounty Hunter moves fast when near the tracked unit and deals critical strikes when attacking it. If the target dies, Bounty Hunter and nearby heroes collect a bonus bounty of gold. Casting Track does not take you out of invisibility.
5288.lore_loc: Using his elevated senses of sight and smell, Gondar's hits have quite a good chance of success.
notes_loc: Bounty Hunter will get the bonus gold if the target dies while Track is active, regardless of how it died.
Track's effect is only visible to allies.
You can see the amount of gold the target is carrying by mousing over the debuff icon above the target's ability bar.
Bonus gold is reliable gold.
5288.shard_loc: Allows Track to be ground targeted, creating a Bear Trap. After 3 seconds, the trap becomes invisible and active. Walking over the trap applies Track. Traps have 400 vision. Max Traps: 8. Ground targeting with Track has bonus 1200 range.

5289.name: weaver_the_swarm
5289.desc_loc: Weaver launches a swarm of %count% young Weavers that latch on any enemy unit in their path, attacking and reducing armor until it is killed.
5289.lore_loc: Skitskurr opens a gap in the space time fabric, allowing young Weavers to slip through and aid him in combat.
notes_loc: When a beetle latches on a target, it will remain there until it is killed or the duration expires.
Beetles are Spell Immune, but can be killed in %destroy_attacks% attacks from a hero. Other units deal half damage.
Beetles provide vision and will even latch onto and reveal invisible heroes.
5289.shard_loc: Reduces cooldown by 4 seconds. Causes The Swarm to latch onto and reveal invisible units. Causes Geminate attack to launch on other enemies within 1200 range of the target that have Beetles attached to them.

5290.name: weaver_shukuchi
5290.desc_loc: Weaver shifts out of visibility, gaining max movement speed --doing harm to any enemies it passes through.
5290.lore_loc: As the Weavers worked in the fabric of creation, small wormholes allowed them to slip through time to better work their craft.
notes_loc: Can only damage the same unit once per cast.

5291.name: weaver_geminate_attack
5291.desc_loc: Allows Weaver to dispatch two attacks at once.
5291.lore_loc: Skitskurr's relationship with time is somewhat variable, causing his actions to be witnessed - and felt - more than once.
notes_loc: Additional attacks leave Weaver %delay% seconds after the previous one, and have no range limit.

5292.name: weaver_time_lapse
5292.desc_loc:
Weaver warps backward to whatever position it was in five seconds earlier--regaining the HP and mana from that time. No effect on cooldown, gold or experience.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
5292.lore_loc: If Skitskurr does not deem the current reality of the world to fit his desires, he simply crawls back in time to right what was wronged.
notes_loc: Removes most negative buffs from Weaver.
Time Lapse disjoints projectiles.
5292.scepter_loc: Reduces cooldown, and allows Weaver to cast Time Lapse on an ally.

5297.name: jakiro_dual_breath
5297.desc_loc: An icy blast followed by a wave of fire launches out in a path in front of Jakiro. The ice slows enemies, while the fire delivers damage over time.
5297.lore_loc: Pyrexae dragons have tremendously dangerous breath for each branch of the species; combining them is unimaginable.
notes_loc: Can hit units up to 1025 range away.
Has a %fire_delay% second interval between each breath.

5298.name: jakiro_ice_path
5298.desc_loc: Creates a path of ice that stuns and damages enemies that touch it.
5298.lore_loc: Jakiro's cunning right head calls upon its frozen heritage, glazing the earth with blistering cold.
notes_loc: It takes %path_delay% seconds for the path to reach its full extent.

5299.name: jakiro_liquid_fire
5299.desc_loc: Jakiro burns his enemies in an area of effect with fire added to his attack, while slowing their attacks.
5299.lore_loc: The left maw of Jakiro opens, laying waste to any in its path.
notes_loc: Works on both units and buildings.

553.name: jakiro_liquid_ice
553.desc_loc: Stuns enemies for %stun_duration% seconds and applies a frost debuff that slows enemy movement speed by %movement_slow%%% and take %base_damage% plus %pct_health_damage%%% of their max health per second as damage for %duration% seconds.

5300.name: jakiro_macropyre
5300.desc_loc: Jakiro exhales a wide line of lasting flames, which deals damage per second to any enemy units caught in the fire.
5300.lore_loc: Ice and fire combine to rip the battlefield to shreds with extreme temperatures.
notes_loc: Units hit by Macropyre will continue to be affected after they leave the area for %linger_duration% additional seconds.
5300.scepter_loc: Increases Macropyre distance by +400 range, duration by +20 seconds and causes it to become Pure damage and pierce Spell Immunity.

5320.name: batrider_sticky_napalm
5320.desc_loc: Drenches an area in sticky oil, amplifying damage from Batrider's attacks and abilities and slowing the movement speed and turn rate of enemies in the area.  Additional casts of Sticky Napalm continue to increase damage, up to %max_stacks% stacks.
5320.lore_loc: It's not uncommon to hear the Rider cackle while he increases the flammability of his opponents.
notes_loc: All damage from Batrider gets amplified, except for Radiance, Orb of Venom, Urn of Shadows, and Spirit Vessel.
Sticky napalm does not require turning to cast.

5321.name: batrider_flamebreak
5321.desc_loc: Hurls an explosive cocktail that explodes when it reaches the target location, knocking back, and dealing damage over time to enemies in the area.
5321.lore_loc: A molotov cocktail is the weapon of choice for Batrider.
5321.shard_loc: Causes Flamebreak to have two charges and apply a Sticky Napalm charge on impact.

5322.name: batrider_firefly
5322.desc_loc: Batrider takes to the skies, laying down a trail of flames from the air.  The fire damages any enemies it touches, and destroys trees below Batrider. Batrider has bonus day/night vision while Firefly is active.
5322.lore_loc: When an enemy escapes into the Yama Raskav Jungle, most would cut through the brush to find the fugitive.  Batrider just chooses to destroy the jungle along with his foes.
notes_loc: During this the Batrider can fly above units, trees and impassable terrain.
If duration ends when above impassable terrain, the Batrider can get stuck.
The trail persists through Batrider's death.

5323.name: batrider_flaming_lasso
5323.desc_loc: Lassoes an enemy and drags them in Batrider's wake.  Victims cannot be dragged over impassable terrain. Dragged units cannot move, attack, or use abilities.  Teleporting or blinking will break the lasso.
5323.lore_loc: Few dare to ask to ride on the bat, as Batrider gives them free of charge.
notes_loc: Killing the target or the Batrider will break the lasso before its expiration.
If Batrider moves more than 400 units in 0.05 seconds the lasso breaks.
Batrider cannot attack while using Flaming Lasso.
5323.shard_loc: Allows Flaming Lasso to be cast on an allied hero, granting them 80%% damage reduction. Has 20 second cooldown when used on allies.
5323.scepter_loc: Flaming Lasso grabs both its target, as well as the target's nearest allied hero within range. The secondary target is tethered to the first.

5328.name: chen_penitence
5328.desc_loc: Forces an enemy unit to move slower and for allies to attack it more quickly.
5328.lore_loc: Although Chen's brand of animal enthrallment isn't quite strong enough to control the minds of enemy heroes, it still tests their resolve in combat.

5330.name: chen_holy_persuasion
5330.desc_loc:
Chen takes control of an enemy or neutral creep. If the persuaded creep's base health is naturally below the health minimum, its base health will be raised to the health minimum. Converted creeps will have increased movement speed and bonus damage. 

Can be cast on converted creeps to teleport them to Chen. If cast on Chen, all units controlled by Chen will be teleported to him. Taking damage will dispel the buff.
5330.lore_loc: Although they may not be knights, Chen incorporates beasts into the Fold in the same way he himself was converted.
notes_loc: Persuading a new creep above max unit count causes the oldest persuaded creep to die.
Can target Ancient Creeps when Chen has Aghanim's Scepter.
The health of creeps already under Chen's control does not update to the new level upon leveling Holy Persuasion further.
Fully restores the creep's mana upon converting.
5330.scepter_loc: Allows Holy Persuasion to target Ancient Creeps.

7306.name: chen_divine_favor
7306.desc_loc: Passively provides an aura that grants increased health regeneration and amplifies all health restore by a percentage.
7306.lore_loc: Chen's zeal is infectious, blessing his allies with vitality and compelling them to his side.
7306.shard_loc: Allows Divine Favor to be cast on allies, teleporting them back home after %teleport_delay% seconds. Cannot target Spell Immune Allies. Cast Range: 600

5331.name: chen_hand_of_god
5331.desc_loc: Heals all allied heroes on the map as well as all units under Chen's control.
5331.lore_loc: Using the mental link with his thralls, Chen calls down restoration and well-being to those who share his fanaticism.
notes_loc: Can heal invulnerable and hidden/banished allies.

6259.name: special_bonus_unique_chen_1
6259.name_loc: +{s:value} Holy Persuasion Max Units and Charges

5334.name: spectre_spectral_dagger
5334.desc_loc: Spectre flings a dagger to draw a Shadow Path, dealing damage and slowing the movement speed of any enemies along the trail. Units hit by the dagger also trail a Shadow Path. While treading the path, Spectre phases through otherwise impassable terrain.
5334.lore_loc: Mercurial's dagger eclipses the physical plane in shadow, a state in which mortals cower, but spectres thrive.
notes_loc: There is a %dagger_grace_period% second grace period after leaving the path where no collision is preserved.

5335.name: spectre_desolate
5335.desc_loc: Deals bonus damage whenever Spectre attacks an enemy that does not have any allied units within a %radius% radius around them.
5335.lore_loc: Often times, warriors find themselves alone with a vision of Mercurial - the fated question is if it is the true Spectre.
notes_loc: Damage is dealt before Spectre's attack.
Spectre's illusions also have Desolate.

5336.name: spectre_dispersion
5336.desc_loc: Damage done to Spectre is reflected on her enemies, leaving her unharmed. The effect lessens with distance.
5336.lore_loc: A daunting task lies before enemies of Mercurial - killing a shadow with blade and magic.
notes_loc: The reflected damage is not dealt to Spectre.
Illusions don't get this ability.
Damage is reflected before reductions, and is returned as the same damage type.
5336.shard_loc: Can cast Dispersion on a hero that damaged you in the last 8 seconds.  Illusion lasts 5 seconds. Cooldown: 25

7851.name: spectre_haunt_single
7851.desc_loc: Allows Spectre to perform a single target unit Haunt. Casts a Spectral Dagger on the target.
7851.lore_loc: With great focus of will, Mercurial can sometimes limit the extent of her division.

5337.name: spectre_haunt
5337.desc_loc:
Creates a spectral nemesis to attack each enemy hero. At any moment during the duration, Spectre can use Reality to exchange places of a given haunt.

Haunt illusions are uncontrollable, take extra damage, and deal less damage than Spectre herself.  They ignore terrain.
5337.lore_loc: At the height of combat, Mercurial's physical manifestation shatters, and the shadowy pieces haunt those who still cling to life.

5339.name: doom_bringer_devour
5339.desc_loc: Consumes an enemy or neutral creep, acquiring any special abilities that it possessed. If autocast is deactivated, Doom will not acquire the creep's abilities. Duration is equal to the cooldown.
5339.lore_loc: Lucifer's appetite and greed are never sated.
notes_loc: Gives Doom the original bounty of the creep, along with the bonus gold.
If you devour a creep without abilities, you'll keep the abilities you had previously.
5339.shard_loc: Allows Devour to be cast on enemy heroes, reducing their maximum health by 15%  for the duration of the devour and provides Doom with a passive basic ability they have.

5340.name: doom_bringer_scorched_earth
5340.desc_loc: Carpets the nearby earth in flames which damage enemies, while also granting him increased movement speed.
5340.lore_loc: The Fallen One spreads destruction in his wake, sparing none from the flame which sustains him.
notes_loc: Scorched Earth follows Doom, centered on his location.

5341.name: doom_bringer_infernal_blade
5341.desc_loc: Doom swings his burning sword, igniting the enemy. Stuns for %ministun_duration% seconds and applies a %burn_duration% second burn that deals a base damage plus a percentage of the target's Max HP as damage per second.
5341.lore_loc: Lucifer shares the fire branding bestowed upon him at the time of his exile.
notes_loc: Interrupts channeling abilities.
5341.shard_loc: Infernal Blade stun duration is increased from 0.6 to 1.2 seconds. If the enemy's level is a multiple of 3, or above level 24, they will be stunned for an additional 0.6 seconds and take 150 bonus damage.

5342.name: doom_bringer_doom
5342.desc_loc:
Inflicts a curse that dispels an enemy Hero and prevents an them from casting spells or using items, while taking damage over time.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
5342.lore_loc: When a name is tolled from the bell of Vashundol, doom is sure to follow.
notes_loc: Units afflicted by Doom can be denied when their HP drops below 25%.
5342.scepter_loc: Doom applies Break and increases duration by 6 seconds.

5345.name: ancient_apparition_cold_feet
5345.desc_loc: Places a frozen hex on an enemy unit that deals damage over time, but can be dispelled by moving away from the initial cast point.  If the enemy unit doesn't move outside of the given range, it will be stunned and frozen in place after 4 seconds.
5345.lore_loc: Kaldr's presence draws those around him into a frozen void, threatening to lock them in an icy prison for eternity.
notes_loc: Deals damage every second.

5346.name: ancient_apparition_ice_vortex
5346.desc_loc: Creates a vortex of icy energy that slows and increases magic damage done to enemies in its range.
5346.lore_loc: Frozen, caustic winds are at the whim of Kaldr, chilling the field of battle.
notes_loc: Provides vision in a small area where it is placed.
5346.shard_loc: Causes Ice Vortex to deal 40 DPS and reduces attack speed by 20.

5347.name: ancient_apparition_chilling_touch
5347.desc_loc: Enhances Ancient Apparition's attack with increased range, heavy magic damage, and movement slow.
5347.lore_loc: The Ancient Apparition's eternal knowledge brings a frigid enchantment to his attacks.
5347.scepter_loc: Removes cooldown and reduces manacost by half.

5348.name: ancient_apparition_ice_blast
5348.desc_loc: Launches a tracer toward any location on the battlefield, which must be triggered again to mark the area to be blasted by a damaging explosion of hail. The further the tracer travels, the larger the explosion will be. Enemies caught in the explosion, or who touch the icy ball of hail as it travels, are Frostbitten, taking damage and prevented from regenerating or healing. If a Frostbitten unit's health drops below a certain percentage, they will instantly shatter.
5348.lore_loc: Ice storms from ages past flow through Kaldr's frosty limbs, crashing into the world and turning its inhabitants into monuments to his eternal power.
notes_loc: Upon cast, this ability is replaced by Release, used to stop the tracer on the target area.
The area of effect is %radius_min% + %radius_grow%*TimeTraveled, capped at %radius_max%.  The freeze area along the path is %path_radius%.
Kill will be granted to the source of the damage that triggers the shatter.
The shatter effect doesn't work on illusions.
The HP Freeze prevents most kinds of healing, including the fountain, except Sunder, Time Lapse and Supernova.

5357.name: ursa_earthshock
5357.desc_loc: Ursa leaps forward %hop_distance% units and slams the earth, causing a powerful shock to damage and slow all enemy units in a nearby area for %abilityduration% seconds.
5357.lore_loc: The very steps of a male ursine shake the ground as well as the resolve of opposing warriors.
5357.shard_loc: Causes Earthshock to apply a 1.5 second Enrage buff on yourself. Reduces cooldown by 1 seconds.

5358.name: ursa_overpower
5358.desc_loc: Using his skill in combat, Ursa gains increased attack speed for a number of subsequent attacks.
5358.lore_loc: For a behemoth of his size, Ursa is deceptively nimble.
notes_loc: Overpower isn't removed by Black King Bar.
Missing an attack still consumes a charge of Overpower.

5359.name: ursa_fury_swipes
5359.desc_loc: Ursa's claws dig deeper wounds in the enemy, causing consecutive attacks to the same enemy to deal more damage.  If the same target is not attacked after %bonus_reset_time% seconds, the bonus damage is lost.
5359.lore_loc: In nature, the wounded rarely survive the attacks of hungry predators.

5360.name: ursa_enrage
5360.desc_loc:
Ursa goes into a frenzy, providing damage reduction and status resistance. Removes any existing debuffs.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
5360.lore_loc: Ulfsaar succumbs to his ancient spirit, becoming the most ferocious creature on the battlefield.
5360.scepter_loc: Reduces cooldown and allows Ursa to use Enrage while disabled.

5353.name: spirit_breaker_charge_of_darkness
5353.desc_loc: Spirit Breaker fixes his sight on an enemy unit and starts charging through all objects.  All enemy units passed through and the targeted unit will be hit by a Greater Bash.  If the targeted unit dies, Spirit Breaker will change his target to the nearest enemy unit to that location.
5353.lore_loc: Barathrum erupts from the darkness with unwieldy force.
notes_loc: Spirit Breaker passes through trees, cliffs, and units.
The charge indicator is visible only to allies.
Spirit Breaker gains shared vision of the target.
5353.scepter_loc: Increases Charge of Darkness movement speed and reduces cooldown.

7301.name: spirit_breaker_bulldoze
7301.desc_loc: Spirit Breaker gains movement speed and status resistance to ram through enemies. Can be used while charging.
7301.lore_loc: Barathrum warps the fabric of reality around him, lessening its influence on his physical form.

5355.name: spirit_breaker_greater_bash
5355.desc_loc: Gives a chance to stun and knockback an enemy unit on an attack. Deals a percentage of movement speed as damage.
5355.lore_loc: The signature strike of Barathrum's ghostly ball and chain.
notes_loc: Does not stack with Skull Basher.

5356.name: spirit_breaker_nether_strike
5356.desc_loc: Spirit Breaker slips into the nether realm, reappearing next to his hapless victim. Upon reappearing, a Greater Bash of the current level occurs and deals bonus damage. Knocks back for double the normal distance.
5356.lore_loc: Barathrum temporarily returns to the realm from where he came, bringing with him the retribution of both worlds.
notes_loc: Spirit Breaker appears behind the target to deliver the bash.
5356.shard_loc: Causes Nether Strike to deal 200 extra damage, and apply a 4-second break. Grants you Spell Immunity for 2 seconds.

5361.name: gyrocopter_rocket_barrage
5361.desc_loc: Launches a salvo of rockets at nearby enemy units in a radius around the Gyrocopter.  Lasts %abilityduration% seconds.
5361.lore_loc: Aurel's new craft has an increased payload for rockets, enhancing their rapid-fire capabilities.
notes_loc: Rocket Barrage can't hit units Gyrocopter has no vision over.
5361.shard_loc: Rocket Barrage hits an extra target and increases duration by 1 second.

5362.name: gyrocopter_homing_missile
5362.desc_loc: Fires a homing missile to seek the targeted enemy unit. The missile gains speed over time, dealing damage and stunning when it impacts the target. Enemy units can destroy the missile before it reaches its target.
5362.lore_loc: The biggest missile Aurel could possibly attach to his craft, The Bomb™ has carefully calculated aerodynamics and explosives for maximum impact.
notes_loc: Towers do half damage to the missile.
The crosshair effect is visible to allies only.
The missile will follow and hit invisible units.

5363.name: gyrocopter_flak_cannon
5363.desc_loc: Gyrocopter's attacks hit all enemy units in an area around it for a limited number of attacks.  Only the main target of attacks will receive attack bonuses such as Critical Strike.  Lasts %abilityduration% seconds or until the attacks are used.
5363.lore_loc: This newly revamped Gyrocopter has attached enough armaments to assault in a 360 degree radius.
notes_loc: Attack range for the primary attack is unchanged.
5363.scepter_loc: Adds a Side Gunner that at random attacks enemy units near Gyrocopter. Prioritizes furthest unit away within its range.

5364.name: gyrocopter_call_down
5364.desc_loc: Call down an aerial missile strike on enemy units in a target area. After %missile_delay_tooltip% seconds, two missiles arrive in succession, with %missile_delay_tooltip% seconds between them.
notes_loc: The visual indicator is visible to allies only.

5365.name: alchemist_acid_spray
5365.desc_loc: Sprays high-pressure acid across a target area. Enemy units who step across the contaminated terrain take damage per second and have their armor reduced.
5365.lore_loc: Using traditional Alchemy from the Darkbrew family, Razzil concocts an acid that dissolves even the toughest metals.

5366.name: alchemist_unstable_concoction
5366.desc_loc: Alchemist brews up an unstable concoction that he can throw at an enemy hero, to stun and deal damage in an area around the explosion. The longer the concoction brews, the more damage it deals and the longer the stun. After %brew_time% seconds, the brew reaches its maximum damage and stun time. However, after %brew_explosion% seconds, the concoction will explode on Alchemist himself if not thrown.
5366.lore_loc: A silver lining to the failure of turning a mountain into gold, this volatile solution has destructive potential.
notes_loc: While brewing, this ability is replaced by Unstable Concoction Throw.  Alchemist can move and act normally while brewing.
A timer above Alchemist's head will indicate the remaining brew time. This timer is visible to enemies.
You can deny yourself with this skill.
Unstable Concoction cannot be disjointed.
Once thrown, Unstable Concoction stops brewing.

5368.name: alchemist_goblins_greed
5368.desc_loc: Alchemist synthesizes additional gold from his enemies and bounty runes. With each kill, Alchemist earns base bonus gold and extra bonus gold. If Alchemist kills another unit which yields gold within the next %duration% seconds, an additional instance of Extra Bonus Gold is added to the total. Additionally, causes bounty runes to yield more gold.
5368.lore_loc: While it is not a mountain, Razzil has mastered the conversion of smaller compounds to line his pockets.

642.name: alchemist_berserk_potion
642.desc_loc:
Alchemist throws a potion at an ally, applying a basic dispel and giving them %attack_speed% Attack Speed and %hp_regen% HP regen.

Lasts %duration% seconds.

5369.name: alchemist_chemical_rage
5369.desc_loc:
Alchemist causes his Ogre to enter a chemically induced rage, reducing base attack cooldown and increasing movement speed and health regeneration.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
5369.lore_loc: The brew Razzil gave to the Ogre during their prison bust has become a useful potion in the midst of combat.
notes_loc: Has a %transformation_time% second transformation time, which can be used to dodge projectiles and stuns.
5369.scepter_loc: Alchemist melts down Aghanim's Scepter to grant an allied hero all Aghanim's Scepter upgrades. When you have a Scepter of your own, you will gain bonus damage and spell amplification for each gifted Scepter.

5370.name: invoker_quas
5370.desc_loc: Allows manipulation of ice elements. Each <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font> instance provides increased health regeneration.
notes_loc: Invoker can only have 3 of any instance.
5370.shard_loc: Quas provides +10% Spell Lifesteal per instance.

5371.name: invoker_wex
5371.desc_loc: Allows manipulation of storm elements. Each <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font> instance provides increased attack speed and movement speed.
notes_loc: Invoker can only have 3 of any instance.
5371.shard_loc: Wex provides +100 Cast Range per instance.

5372.name: invoker_exort
5372.desc_loc: Allows manipulation of fire elements. Each <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font> instance provides increased attack damage.
notes_loc: Invoker can only have 3 of any instance.
5372.shard_loc: Exort provides +5% Spell Amplification per instance.

5375.name: invoker_invoke
5375.desc_loc:
Combines the properties of the elements currently being manipulated to create a new spell for Invoker to use. Invoke cooldown is reduced by %cooldown_reduction_per_orb% seconds for each orb level.

Click the help button to see the list of possible spells.
5375.lore_loc: So begins a new age of knowledge.
notes_loc: The arrangement of instances does not matter.
Invoke will not cost mana or go on cooldown if the only effect is to swap the positions of existing spells.

5376.name: invoker_cold_snap
5376.desc_loc: Invoker draws the heat from an enemy, chilling them to their very core for a duration based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>. The enemy will take damage and be briefly frozen. Further damage taken in this state will freeze the enemy again, dealing bonus damage. The enemy can only be frozen so often, but the freeze cooldown decreases based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>.
notes_loc: The freeze stun only triggers on damage greater than %damage_trigger% after reductions.

5381.name: invoker_ghost_walk
5381.desc_loc: Invoker manipulates the ice and electrical energies around him, rendering his body invisible. The elemental imbalance created as a consequence slows nearby enemies based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>, and slows Invoker as well based on the level of <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font>.
notes_loc: The slow effect does not work on Spell Immune enemies.

5382.name: invoker_tornado
5382.desc_loc:
Unleashes a fast moving tornado that picks up enemy units in its path, suspending them helplessly in the air shortly before allowing them to plummet to their doom. Travels further based on the level of <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font>. Holds enemies in the air for a duration based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>. Deals base damage plus added damage based on levels in <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font>.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
notes_loc: Units are invulnerable while affected by Tornado, and the damage is dealt when landing.

5383.name: invoker_emp
5383.desc_loc: Invoker builds up a charge of electromagnetic energy at a targeted location which automatically detonates after %delay% seconds. The detonation covers an area, draining mana based on the level of <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font>. Deals damage for each point of mana drained.  If EMP drains mana from an enemy hero, Invoker gains 50% of the mana drained.
notes_loc: Will not affect cycloned units (Tornado or Eul's Scepter of Divinity).

5384.name: invoker_alacrity
5384.desc_loc: Invoker infuses an ally with an immense surge of energy, increasing their attack speed based on the level of <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font> and their damage based on the level of <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font>.

5385.name: invoker_chaos_meteor
5385.desc_loc: Invoker pulls a flaming meteor from space onto the targeted location. Upon landing, the meteor rolls forward, constantly dealing damage based on the level of <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font>, and rolling further based on the level of <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font>. Units hit by the meteor will also be set on fire for a short time, receiving additional damage based on the level of <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font>.
notes_loc: Deals main damage to enemy units under meteor every %damage_interval% seconds and burns enemies for smaller damage over %burn_duration% seconds.
The meteor moves at a speed of %travel_speed%.
5385.shard_loc: Causes two extra Chaos Meteors to land alongisde the primary cast at slight angles. Reduces cooldown by 15 seconds.

5386.name: invoker_sun_strike
5386.desc_loc: Sends a catastrophic ray of fierce energy from the sun at any targeted location, incinerating all enemies standing beneath it once it reaches the earth. Deals damage based on the level of <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font>, however this damage is spread evenly over all enemies hit.
notes_loc: Gives vision of the target area before the strike.
Invoker gains experience with kills made from Sun Strike, even if made from outside of experience range.
5386.scepter_loc: Creates a Cataclysm when Sun Strike is double tapped. Puts it on a 90 second cooldown. Creates 2 visible Sun Strikes within 160-200 range of each enemy hero.

5387.name: invoker_forge_spirit
5387.desc_loc: Invoker forges a spirit embodying the strength of fire and fortitude of ice. Damage and armor are based on the level of <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font> while attack range, health, and duration are based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>. The elemental's scorching attack is capable of melting the armor of enemy heroes. Spawns two spirits when Quas and Exort are at least level 4.
notes_loc: Casting this ability will replace currently summoned Forged Spirits.

5389.name: invoker_ice_wall
5389.desc_loc: Generates a wall of solid ice directly in front of Invoker for a duration based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>. The bitter cold emanating from it greatly slows nearby enemies based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font> and deals damage each second based on the level of <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font>.
notes_loc: The slow will still affect Spell Immune enemies if their spell immunity was created after being affected by Ice Wall.
5389.shard_loc: Allows Ice Wall to be a Vector Target ability with 1100 cast range. Increases wall length by 320.

5390.name: invoker_deafening_blast
5390.desc_loc: Invoker unleashes a mighty sonic wave in front of him, dealing damage to any enemy unit it collides with based on the level of <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font>. The sheer impact from the blast is enough to knock those enemy units back for a duration based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>, then disarm their attacks for a duration based on the level of <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font>.

6098.name: special_bonus_unique_invoker_2
6098.desc_loc: Releases 12 Deafening Blasts around Invoker in a circular pattern.  An enemy can only be hit once per cast.

5377.name: silencer_curse_of_the_silent
5377.desc_loc: Curses the target area, causing enemy heroes to take damage and slowing their movement speed. Anytime affected enemies cast a spell, the duration is increased.
5377.lore_loc: Nortrom's lack of incantations is less of a problem for him than it is for his adversaries.
notes_loc: If an enemy hero affected by Arcane Curse is silenced, Arcane Curse will pause the duration.
Affects creeps.

5378.name: silencer_glaives_of_wisdom
5378.desc_loc: Silencer enchants his glaives with his wisdom, dealing additional damage based on his Intelligence. Silencer temporarily steals his target's Intelligence with each hit.
5378.lore_loc: Although lacking in traditional incantations, Nortrom's pedigree of the Aeol Drias gives him uncanny wisdom, which he applies to physical combat.
5378.shard_loc: Causes Glaives to bounce once towards the closest enemy unit, dealing 50%% of Silencer's attack damage. Bounce range is 600.

5379.name: silencer_last_word
5379.desc_loc: Enchants a target, providing vision of them and causing them to be damaged and silenced if they cast a spell or if the enchantment timer expires. Deals extra damage based on the difference in intelligence between Silencer and the target.
5379.lore_loc: Nortrom ensures that spells uttered by his opponents will be their last.
notes_loc: Channeling abilities will trigger this effect once the caster finishes its channel.
5379.scepter_loc: Causes Last Word to become an AoE ability.

5380.name: silencer_global_silence
5380.desc_loc: Silencer stops all sound, preventing enemy heroes and units on the map from casting spells.
5380.lore_loc: With a shock to the ground, all magic and sound pauses, and Nortrom fulfills his prophecy.
notes_loc: This skill works on invisible and Spell Immune units, but gaining spell immunity will remove its effect.

5391.name: obsidian_destroyer_arcane_orb
5391.desc_loc: Adds extra pure damage to Outworld Destroyer's attacks, based on his remaining mana pool.
5391.lore_loc: Harbinger's outworldly knowledge allows it to tap into the ebb and flow of all spiritual energy, infusing it into his being.
notes_loc: The damage is calculated after the mana cost is spent.

5392.name: obsidian_destroyer_astral_imprisonment
5392.desc_loc: Places a target unit into an astral prison. The hidden unit is invulnerable and disabled. When the astral prison implodes, it deals damage to the target and steals a percentage of their max mana.
5392.lore_loc: Locked away in the pocket between this world and the Outworld, victims realize their infantile knowledge and mortality.
notes_loc: Imprisoned units can still be hit by Sanity's Eclipse.
Max mana steal does not increase Outworld Destroyer's current mana values or directly reduce the victim's mana values.
5392.scepter_loc: Grants charges to Astral Imprisonment, increases damage by 140 and applies the damage in an area.

5684.name: obsidian_destroyer_equilibrium
5684.desc_loc: Passively grants you a chance to restore a percentage of your max mana each time you cast an ability.
5684.lore_loc: The Outworld is awash in arcane energy, inclined to diffuse through any of Harbinger's rifts.
5684.shard_loc: Essence Flux becomes castable ability with 0.75 cast time. Swaps Outworld Destroyer's current Life and Mana totals. Cooldown: 45

5394.name: obsidian_destroyer_sanity_eclipse
5394.desc_loc: Unleashes a psychic blast that deals to enemies based on the difference between your mana and the target's mana. Sanity's Eclipse can hit units trapped by Astral Imprisonment.
5394.lore_loc: When an Outworld crystal ruptures, cataclysmic energies are released, and the reverberations of this power are felt interdimensionally.
notes_loc: Does not damage creeps or neutral units.

5395.name: lycan_summon_wolves
5395.desc_loc: Summons two wolves to fight for Lycan.  Level 3-4 wolves have Permanent Invisibility, and level 4 wolves have Cripple.
5395.lore_loc: The very enchantment that twisted his being also summons canine familiars.
5395.shard_loc: Causes one of your creep waves to include one uncontrollable wolf that moves with the wave.

5396.name: lycan_howl
5396.desc_loc: Strikes fear into enemies, reducing armor and attack damage to all enemies within %radius% range of Lycan and his wolves.
5396.lore_loc: Blood-curdling wolf cries signal to opponents that Banehallow is among them.

5397.name: lycan_feral_impulse
5397.desc_loc: Increases the HP regeneration and damage of Lycan and all units under his control.
