5397.lore_loc: His animalistic symbiosis with canine kind gives Banehallow enhanced reflexes and hunting capabilities.

333.name: lycan_wolf_bite
333.desc_loc: Lycan bites an ally, granting them Shapeshift properties. Lycan and the bitten target gain %lifesteal_percent%%% Lifesteal and share %lifesteal%%% Lifesteal with each other as long as they are within %lifesteal_range% range of each other.

5398.name: lycan_shapeshift
5398.desc_loc: Lycan assumes his lupine form, granting him and his units critical strikes and added vision at night. During Shapeshift, Lycan and all units under his control move at increased speed, cannot be slowed and have a %crit_chance%%% chance to deal a critical strike doing %crit_multiplier%%% damage.
5398.lore_loc: Forever a slave to his lycanthropy, Banehallow has come to accept his curse, and embrace his own savagery.
notes_loc: Hex doesn't remove Lycan's movement speed.
Lycan has a smaller collision size in this state.

5400.name: brewmaster_thunder_clap
5400.desc_loc: Slams the ground, dealing damage and slowing the movement speed and attack rate of nearby enemy units.
5400.lore_loc: A slam of Mangix' mighty keg starts the festivities.

7310.name: brewmaster_cinder_brew
7310.desc_loc: Drenches an area in alcohol, causing enemy units to move slower and ignited once they take any spell damage. Duration is increased by %extra_duration% seconds when ignited.
7310.lore_loc: The Order of the Oyo's solution to all problems - another round!

5402.name: brewmaster_drunken_brawler
5402.desc_loc: Brewmaster passively gains a chance to evade physical attacks and deal critical damage when attacking.  When activated, Brewmaster goes into a drunken brawler state, granting him increased chance to evade or deal critical damage. Brewmaster moves with a varying amount of movement speed, alternating between %min_movement%%% slower and %max_movement%%% faster. Lasts %duration% seconds.
5402.lore_loc: When Mangix won his title as the Brewmaster of the Order of Oyo, he also claimed his place in the mastery of inebriation.
notes_loc: Stacks diminishingly with other sources of Evasion.

5403.name: brewmaster_primal_split
5403.desc_loc: Splits Brewmaster into elements, forming 3 specialized warriors, adept at survival, each with their own abilities. If any of them survive until the end of their summoned timer, the Brewmaster is reborn.
5403.lore_loc: It isn't clear whether Mangix is consciously aware of his potent bond with nature, as it often occurs in the midst of a drunken stupor.
notes_loc: The Earth Element will carry all auras that the Brewmaster has, as well as True Sight.
The Fire Element has phased movement.
When the spell ends, Brewmaster will take the place of an element in this order, assuming they are alive: Earth, Storm, Fire.
5403.shard_loc: Primal Split now creates a Void brewling. Has Astral Pulse ability, affecting enemies in 500 AoE. Applies a 20/30/40% slow and Disarm for 2 seconds.
5403.scepter_loc: Primal Split has 2 charges and can be canceled at any time. Charge replenish time is equal to the normal cooldown.

5421.name: shadow_demon_disruption
5421.desc_loc: Banishes the targeted unit from the battlefield for a short duration.  Upon returning, two illusions of the banished unit are created under Shadow Demon's control.
5421.lore_loc: The pain of deception comes not while it happens, but when it is revealed.

5422.name: shadow_demon_soul_catcher
5422.desc_loc: Captures the soul of enemy units in an area, causing them to lose a percentage of their current health. When the debuff is removed, the units gain half of the lost health back. Units under the effect of Disruption can still be affected by Soul Catcher.
5422.lore_loc: Trying to resist the Shadow Demon's corruption is mostly a useless endeavor.

5423.name: shadow_demon_shadow_poison
5423.desc_loc: Deals damage in a line, and afflicts enemy units with a poison effect. The poison deals 1/2/4/8/16 times the stack damage based on the number of stacks on the target, up to %max_multiply_stacks% stacks. Additional stacks cause %bonus_stack_damage% damage each.  This deferred damage is dealt when Shadow Poison's duration is expired, or the Release sub-ability is used.
5423.lore_loc: The ever growing influence of the Shadow Demon can pollute the most valiant and pure of heroes.
notes_loc: Shadow Poison can affect units under Disruption.

5425.name: shadow_demon_demonic_purge
5425.desc_loc:
Purges the target enemy unit, removing positive buffs, and slowing the target for the duration.  The unit slowly regains its speed until the end of the duration, upon which damage is dealt.  Units under the effect of Disruption can still be affected by Demonic Purge.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
5425.lore_loc: Once Shadow Demon no longer has any need for his collected cultist, he releases it from its subservience - and its life.
notes_loc: The slow starts at %max_slow%%% decreases over time to %min_slow%%%.
Positive buffs are continously removed from the target for the duration of the Purge.
5425.shard_loc: Allows Demonic Purge to be cast on allies, continuously dispelling them and healing for its damage values. Does not slow allies.
5425.scepter_loc: Cooldown is removed, replaced with %max_charges% charges that replenish every %charge_restore_time_tooltip_scepter% seconds. Also causes Demonic Purge to break its target's passive abilities while active.

5412.name: lone_druid_spirit_bear
5412.desc_loc:
Summons a powerful Spirit Bear companion that can equip items.  If the bear moves 1100 distance away from the Lone Druid, it cannot attack.  Lone Druid suffers %backlash_damage%%% of his max health as backlash damage if the Spirit Bear dies. Spirit Bear does not benefit from attributes.
Spirit Bear has the Return, Demolish and Entangling Roots abilities.
5412.lore_loc: Sylla's lifelong companion is symbiotic with his spirit and heart, coming to aid him in any time of need.
notes_loc: Most spells interact with the Spirit Bear in the same way as they do with heroes.
5412.scepter_loc: Allows Spirit Bear to attack at any range from Lone Druid, and to survive if Lone Druid dies.

7309.name: lone_druid_spirit_link
7309.desc_loc: Links Lone Druid and the Spirit Bear, increasing the attack speed of both and causing damage dealt by the Spirit Bear to heal Lone Druid.
7309.lore_loc: Sylla is emboldened by the presence of his companion, his vitality replenished with each swipe of the Spirit Bear's claws.

5414.name: lone_druid_savage_roar
5414.desc_loc: Lone Druid and the Spirit Bear roar fiercely causing nearby enemies to flee towards their base in terror. Their movement speed is increased by %bonus_speed%%%.
5414.lore_loc: Sylla studies and masters the arts of the lost Bear Clan, enhancing his attunement with the wild.
notes_loc: An entangled hero will not be able to move.
Cooldown is shared with Spirit Bear.
5414.shard_loc: Savage Roar now empowers allies in 700 AoE with +20% Movement Speed and +60 Attack Speed for 5 seconds. Applies a basic dispel. Replicates between Lone Druid and Spirit Bear regardless of castability on the other.

5415.name: lone_druid_true_form
5415.desc_loc: Lone Druid learns to morph himself into a raging bear, losing his ranged advantage, but gaining increased resistance, Entangling Roots and Demolish.
5415.lore_loc: The mighty bear is the king of the forest, possessing the throne through raw power.
notes_loc: Cooldowns of items that are different for ranged and melee units will be based on which form Lone Druid was in when the item was used.

6680.name: special_bonus_unique_lone_druid_7
6680.name_loc: +{s:value} True Form and Spirit Bear Health

5426.name: chaos_knight_chaos_bolt
5426.desc_loc: Throws a mysterious bolt of energy at the target unit. It stuns for a random duration and deals random damage.
5426.lore_loc: Even Chaos Knight cannot predict this manifest of unholy energy.
notes_loc: The stun duration and damage values dealt are inversely related.
Nearby illusions will mimic the cast animation.
5426.shard_loc: Chaos Bolt creates a Phantasm illusion attacking the target for 6 seconds. Increases cast range by 300.

5427.name: chaos_knight_reality_rift
5427.desc_loc: Teleports Chaos Knight, any images he has, and the target unit to a point along the line between him and the target. Reduces armor of the enemy unit for %duration% seconds.
5427.lore_loc: Armageddon rides between the planes, bringing Chaos Knight to his victim wherever he may hide.
notes_loc: Chaos Knight and the target unit are made to face each other, and Chaos Knight and his phantasms are issued an attack order against the target.
5427.shard_loc: Allows Reality Rift to be cast on any enemy hero that is within 1200 range of you or one of your illusions. Gathers all of your illusions and your hero and teleports them to the target enemy.

5428.name: chaos_knight_chaos_strike
5428.desc_loc: Chaos Knight's attacks have a chance to deal a critical strike of varying strength, in addition to a lifesteal for percentage of the damage.
5428.lore_loc: Chaos Knight's unwieldy power bludgeons those who stand before him, crushing the thickest of armors.

5429.name: chaos_knight_phantasm
5429.desc_loc:
Summons several phantasmal copies of the Chaos Knight from alternate dimensions. The phantasms are strong illusions that deal %outgoing_damage_tooltip%%% damage, but take %incoming_damage_tooltip%%% damage.
DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
5429.lore_loc: Drawing on his battles fought across many worlds and many times, phantasms of the Chaos Knight rise up to quell all who oppose him.
notes_loc: Removes most negative buffs from Chaos Knight.
Chaos Knight is invulnerable for %invuln_duration% seconds when casting, allowing him to dodge stuns and damage.
Strong Illusions are not instantly killed by spells.
5429.scepter_loc: Creates an illusion of allied heroes. Creates an additional illusion for Chaos Knight as well.

5430.name: meepo_earthbind
5430.desc_loc: Tosses a net at the target point, rooting down all enemy units in an area around it.
5430.lore_loc: Catching dinner in the Riftshadow Ruins can be quite the task.
notes_loc: Affects invisible units, revealing them.
Does not work on Spell Immune units or Roshan.

5431.name: meepo_poof
5431.desc_loc: Drawing mystical energies from the earth, a Meepo can teleport to another Meepo or itself after channeling for %abilitycastpoint% seconds, dealing damage in both the departure and arrival locations.
5431.lore_loc: Sometimes breaking one of the Riftshadow Crystals can be just the trick for getting yourself out of a bind.  Or your other self.
notes_loc: Can be cast through the minimap.
Can teleport to Meepo illusions.
5431.shard_loc: Allows you to Poof to allies within 2000 range.

7318.name: meepo_ransack
7318.desc_loc: Steals health from the enemy with each strike and heals all other Meepos for that amount.
7318.lore_loc: So you gonna need that, or...?
7318.shard_loc: Ransack now has a 30%% chance on hit to apply a Geostrike debuff, slowing enemies by 20%% and dealing 20 DPS for 4 seconds. Instances from multiple Meepos stack.

547.name: meepo_petrify
547.desc_loc: Channels for 0.75 seconds and digs into the ground for 3.5 seconds, dispelling Meepo and causing him to be come invulnerable and untargetable for %duration%. Restores %hp_restore%%% of his max health over that duration. Can’t be cast while rooted.

5433.name: meepo_divided_we_stand
5433.desc_loc: Meepo summons an imperfect, semi-autonomous duplicate of himself, which can gain gold and experience as he does and shares his experience, attributes and abilities. However, the clones cannot wield any items but the boots that Meepo himself wears.  If any of the clones die, they all die.
notes_loc: Clones can't use Arcane Boots, Guardian Greaves.

338.name: treant_natures_grasp
338.desc_loc: Creates vines towards the target location. Vines slow down and deal damage to enemies that walk through. Vines deal 50% more damage if they touch a tree. Does half damage to creeps.
338.lore_loc: The Protectors don't often come into vision; their natural state being nestled within their leafy brethren.

5435.name: treant_leech_seed
5435.desc_loc: Treant plants a life-sapping seed in an enemy unit, draining its health, while simultaneously slowing it. The seed heals friendly units around it.
5435.lore_loc: Rooftrellen nurtures the beings under his stewardship, sustained by the lifeforce of trespassers into his sacred ground.

5436.name: treant_living_armor
5436.desc_loc: Infuses the target hero or structure with a protective coating which heals the target and provides bonus armor.
5436.lore_loc: The roots and tendrils of the Treant Protectors are far-reaching, stimulating the growth and rejuvenation of all of nature.

5649.name: treant_eyes_in_the_forest
5649.desc_loc: Treant Protector enchants a tree, which grants him unobstructed vision in that location. If Overgrowth is cast, units within a radius of an enchanted tree will be entangled and damaged. Passively causes all trees to respawn much faster.
5649.lore_loc: One can never be too certain who, or what, might need protecting.
notes_loc: Being entangled by Overgrowth through enchanted trees from Eyes of the Forest does damage.
If the enemy has True Sight, they will be able to see which trees are enchanted.

5434.name: treant_natures_guise
5434.desc_loc: Provides Treant with Tree Walking whenever he hasn't taken damage for %cooldown_time% seconds. While active, Treant gains movement speed bonus and amplified healing and regeneration on himself.
5434.lore_loc: The Protectors don't often come into vision; their natural state being nestled within their leafy brethren.
notes_loc: While affected by Nature's Guise, Treant can move unobstructed through other trees .
5434.shard_loc: Causes you to become invisible with Nature's Guise and root enemies upon attacking. Roots them for 1 second and deals a total of 200 damage. Lasts an extra second when attacking near a tree. Increases movement speed bonus by 15%%%.

5437.name: treant_overgrowth
5437.desc_loc: Summons an overgrowth of vines and branches around Treant that deal damage to afflicted enemies and prevent them from moving, blinking, going invisible, or attacking.
5437.lore_loc: Rooftrellen calls the ancestral spirit of nature, releasing its power through all of his kin.
notes_loc: Works on Spell Immune units, but if units gain spell immunity after the effect starts, they'll break free.

5438.name: ogre_magi_fireblast
5438.desc_loc: Blasts an enemy unit with a wave of fire, dealing damage and stunning the target.
5438.lore_loc: The Ogre Magi is easily amused, entertained for hours by playing with fire.
notes_loc: When Multicast, Fireblast hits the same target each time with a %multicast_delay% seconds interval.

5439.name: ogre_magi_ignite
5439.desc_loc: Drenches the target and another random unit in volatile chemicals, causing it to burst into flames. The target is in immense pain, taking damage and moving more slowly.
notes_loc: Multicast makes this spell have a chance to cast multiple times at random enemy units with 1400 area of effect.
Ignite hitting an already affected unit adds to the burn duration.

5440.name: ogre_magi_bloodlust
5440.desc_loc: Incites a frenzy in a friendly unit, increasing its movement speed and attack speed. Gives bonus attacks speed if cast on Ogre himself. Can be cast on towers.
5440.lore_loc: 'Running's not as fun as hitting... Not one bit fun.'
notes_loc: When multicast, nearby allies will be selected randomly in an %multicast_bloodlust_aoe% area of effect to receive Bloodlust.

5466.name: ogre_magi_unrefined_fireblast
5466.desc_loc: Blasts an enemy unit with a wave of fire, dealing damage and stunning the target. Its mana cost is %scepter_mana%%% of Ogre Magi's current mana.
5466.lore_loc: The 'who-casts-spell-first' argument between himself is solved simply by both casting at once.
notes_loc: When Multicast, Unrefined Fireblast hits the same target each time with a %multicast_delay% seconds interval.

648.name: ogre_magi_smash
648.desc_loc:
Creates a shield around the target ally, absorbing 85%% of the damage of next %attacks% attacks. Launches fireballs at the attacker, dealing %damage% damage.

Lasts %duration% seconds.

5441.name: ogre_magi_multicast
5441.desc_loc: Enables Ogre Magi to cast his abilities and items multiple times with each use.
5441.lore_loc: Despite being largely incapacitated by his IQ, the Ogre Magi's success in battle is attributed to pure skill.
notes_loc: Only targeted abilities and items have a chance to be multicast.
Targeted abilities and items apply to additional enemies and neutrals in an AoE around Ogre. Fireblast and Unrefined Fireblast hit the same target multiple times.

5442.name: undying_decay
5442.desc_loc: Undying steals strength from all enemy heroes in an area, dealing base damage as he claims the enemy's strength for himself.
5442.lore_loc: The strength of the living is simply borrowed from the strength of the dead.
notes_loc: The strength stolen stacks, but can't cause a hero to have strength below 1.
The strength steal takes effect before the damage is dealt.
Affects invisible units.
5442.shard_loc: Increases Decay radius by 100 and spawns a zombie around each hero target.

5443.name: undying_soul_rip
5443.desc_loc: Undying rips health away from all nearby units and uses it to heal an ally, or damage an enemy. Soul Rip can also be used to heal Tombstone.
5443.lore_loc: Even allies feel despair in Undying's presence.
notes_loc: Can heal Tombstone, but can't heal or damage other buildings.
Does not rip from invisible units.

5444.name: undying_tombstone
5444.desc_loc: Summons a tombstone at the target point.  Zombies will frequently spawn next to every enemy unit in the area around the Tombstone, and attack them.  Zombies have the Deathlust ability, which causes their attacks to slow the target, and if the target reaches below a certain amount of health, increases the attack and movement speed of the zombie.
5444.lore_loc: Dirge calls on his fallen brothers to fight for the Dead God.
notes_loc: Tombstone is Spell Immune, but can be healed by Soul Rip.
Zombies and Tombstone are Spell Immune.
If their initial target dies or goes out of vision, the Zombie will die.

5447.name: undying_flesh_golem
5447.desc_loc: Undying transforms into a horrifying flesh golem. Gains a percentage increase to strength and imbues attacks with a slow and damage amplification.
5447.lore_loc: The flesh of the recently dead add to the power of Dirge's plague.

5448.name: rubick_telekinesis
5448.desc_loc: Rubick uses his telekinetic powers to lift the enemy into the air briefly and then hurls them back at the ground. The unit lands on the ground with such force that it stuns nearby enemies.
5448.lore_loc: Even the Grandest Magus may use his powers for enjoyment.
notes_loc: While the target is in the air, Rubick may use a secondary ability to throw the enemy in a targeted direction.
When the unit lands, it isn't affected by the area of effect stun.
The farthest you can throw an enemy is 375.
5448.shard_loc: Allows you to target yourself or allies with Telekinesis. Throw range is 85% longer and cooldown is reduced by 30%% when targeting allies. Throw delay reduced to 0.5 seconds.

5450.name: rubick_fade_bolt
5450.desc_loc: Rubick creates a powerful stream of arcane energy that travels between enemy units, dealing damage and reducing their attack damage. Each jump deals less damage.
5450.lore_loc: Rubick's favorite spell for dispatching would-be assassins is a rather simple conjuration.

7320.name: rubick_arcane_supremacy
7320.desc_loc: Rubick's mastery of the arcane allows him to have a larger cast range and increased potency.
7320.lore_loc: Not every magus can be a Grand Magus...

5452.name: rubick_spell_steal
5452.desc_loc: Rubick studies the trace magical essence of one enemy hero, learning the secrets of the last spell the hero cast. Rubick can use this spell as his own for several minutes or until he dies, and stolen spells last longer on enemies.
5452.lore_loc: ...but even their lesser magics can be a source of much utility.
notes_loc: Cannot steal item abilities.
5452.scepter_loc: Decreases cooldown, increases cast range and upgrades the spell to the Scepter level.

5458.name: disruptor_thunder_strike
5458.desc_loc: Repeatedly strikes the targeted unit with lightning.  Each strike damages nearby enemy units in a small radius and slows enemy movement and attack speed by %slow_amount%%% for %slow_duration% seconds.  Provides vision of its target.
5458.lore_loc: Disruptor's charged coils occasionally overload, and a singed armor plate or tuft of fur is the enemy's result.
5458.shard_loc: Allows Thunder Strike to be cast on allies, follows the ally and deals damage around them. Each strike gives a short 1.25 second buff that provides +50%% Movement Speed and +75 Attack Speed. Increases radius to 650.

5459.name: disruptor_glimpse
5459.desc_loc: Teleports the target hero back to where it was 4 seconds ago.  Instantly kills illusions.
5459.lore_loc: Playing with electricity can have unexpected results.
notes_loc: The travel time is a function of the distance the target will travel.

5460.name: disruptor_kinetic_field
5460.desc_loc: After a short formation time, creates a circular barrier of kinetic energy that enemies can't pass.
5460.lore_loc: The stryder is immune to the gale-force winds that will consume its adversaries.
notes_loc: Spell Immune units can travel through the field.

5461.name: disruptor_static_storm
5461.desc_loc: Creates a damaging static storm that also silences all enemy units in the area for the duration.  The damage starts off weak, but increases in power over the duration.
5461.lore_loc: A summer squall in Druud is a hardship that only an Oglodi can survive.

5462.name: nyx_assassin_impale
5462.desc_loc: Rock spikes burst from the earth along a straight path. Enemy units are hurled into the air, then are stunned and take damage when they fall.
5462.lore_loc: All zealot scarabs possess intimate knowledge of underground pathways, using them to their advantage.
notes_loc: The spikes move at %speed% units per second, over %length% range.
Impale cannot be blocked by Linken's Sphere.

5463.name: nyx_assassin_mana_burn
5463.desc_loc: Destroys the target hero's mana equal to a multiplier of its Intelligence, and deals damage equal to the mana burned.
5463.lore_loc: The tome in Ultimyr describes one scarab with the ability eat away at the mind of lesser beings.

5464.name: nyx_assassin_spiked_carapace
5464.desc_loc:
When activated while above ground, Spiked Carapace reflects and negates damage dealt to Nyx Assassin (max once from each source), as well as stunning the source of the damage. Activating Spiked Carapace will not break Vendetta invisibility.

While Burrowed, Spiked Carapace instantly stuns nearby enemies when cast.
5464.lore_loc: While their carapace is relatively thin, it's guarded by a retractable field of razor-sharp spikes.
notes_loc: The damage is calculated after all reductions.
Spiked Carapace will only trigger on damage from other player controlled units.
The damage reflected will have the same damage type as it had when it was dealt to Nyx.

5666.name: nyx_assassin_burrow
5666.desc_loc: Nyx Assassin buries himself beneath the battlefield over a short duration. Once burrowed, Spiked Carapace instantly stuns nearby enemies when cast, the range of Mana Burn and Impale is increased, and Impale's cooldown is decreased. While burrowed, Nyx Assassin is stationary, unable to attack, and invisible. His health and mana regeneration are also increased, and he gains damage reduction from all damage sources.
5666.lore_loc: Some castes of zealot scarab are known to create small burrows to lie in wait, ready to ambush their prey.
notes_loc: Casting Vendetta will cancel burrow.

5465.name: nyx_assassin_vendetta
5465.desc_loc: Allows Nyx Assassin to become invisible and gain a speed bonus.  If Nyx Assassin attacks to break the invisibility, massive bonus damage is dealt with the attack.
5465.lore_loc: The scarab kills for the glory of his queen.
notes_loc: Has a %fade_time% second fadetime.
If a spell is used to break the invisibility, or the invisibility expires, the bonus damage is lost.
While the invisibility cannot be dispelled, the Break can be.
5465.shard_loc: Causes Nyx's Vendetta attack to reduce enemy magic resistance by 20%% for 4 seconds. Also increases Vendetta movement speed by 25%.

5467.name: naga_siren_mirror_image
5467.desc_loc:
Creates multiple images of Naga Siren under her control.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
5467.lore_loc: Slithice, while being strong in her own right, is notoriously hard to track down.
notes_loc: Naga Siren is invulnerable for %invuln_duration% seconds when casting, allowing her to dodge stuns and damage.
Upon casting, most effects are removed from Naga Siren.
Upon casting, existing Mirror Image illusions are destroyed.

5468.name: naga_siren_ensnare
5468.desc_loc: Interrupts the target and traps them in place, preventing movement or blinking.
5468.lore_loc: The only way to escape the onslaught of a Slithereen is to never oppose one in the first place.
5468.scepter_loc: Allows Ensnare to target Spell Immune or sleeping units. Reduces the Ensnare cooldown by 6 seconds and increases cast range by 400.

5469.name: naga_siren_rip_tide
5469.desc_loc: The Naga Siren and her images have a chance on attack to hit all nearby units with a damaging wave of water that lowers armor for %duration% seconds.
5469.lore_loc: A torrent from the Deep Ones crushes the defenses of the Siren's enemies.
5469.shard_loc: Adds 20% slow and increases the base armor reduction by 4.

5470.name: naga_siren_song_of_the_siren
5470.desc_loc: All enemies in range of the Naga Siren are put into a magical stasis where they cannot act or be attacked. Using Song of the Siren again will end the duration early.
5470.lore_loc: Slithice's powerful voice enchants leagues of opponents, while calling her Slithereen kin in a time of need.
notes_loc: Units affected by Song of the Siren are invulnerable and cannot take damage from any source.
Doesn't affect Spell Immune units.
The area of the song follows Naga, so if she moves far enough away from affected units, they will wake up.

5471.name: keeper_of_the_light_illuminate
5471.desc_loc: Channels light energy, building power the longer it's channeled.  Once released, a wave is sent forth that deals damage and gives vision in its path.  The longer it is channeled, the more damage is dealt.
5471.lore_loc: Ezalor's hidden light reveals itself in marvelous fashion.
notes_loc: Gives increasing vision over the channeling time.
5471.shard_loc: Causes Illuminate to heal for 40% of its damage during daytime.

532.name: keeper_of_the_light_radiant_bind
532.desc_loc: Weakens an enemy's magical resistance, and applies a slow that increases in strength the more the target moves.

5473.name: keeper_of_the_light_chakra_magic
5473.desc_loc: Restores mana to the target unit and reduces cooldowns of all abilities currently on cooldown by a fixed amount.
5473.lore_loc: In the same vein, Ezalor bestows his harmony among others.
notes_loc: Chakra Magic does not reduce the cooldown of Ultimate abilities

5476.name: keeper_of_the_light_blinding_light
5476.desc_loc: A blinding light flashes over the targeted area, knocking back and blinding the units in the area, causing them to miss some attacks. Knockback is %knockback_distance% range over %knockback_duration% seconds,
5476.lore_loc: The Primordial light turns the tides of battle in favor of Ezalor and his allies.
notes_loc: Upon landing, units will destroy trees in a 150 radius.

7316.name: keeper_of_the_light_will_o_wisp
7316.desc_loc: Summons Ignis Fatuus at the targeted area. Alternates on and off, drawing enemies closer with its mesmerising flicker.
7316.lore_loc: Though he would not claim to 'know' them, Ezalor holds an uncanny influence over many powerful creatures always willing to come to his aid.

5474.name: keeper_of_the_light_spirit_form
5474.desc_loc: Ezalor temporarily turns his body luminescent, gaining bonus movement speed, cast range, grants the Blinding Light ability, and allows Illuminate to be channeled by a separate spirit and heal allies during the day.
5474.lore_loc: In a flash of light, Ezalor reveals his true nature.

5479.name: keeper_of_the_light_spirit_form_illuminate
5479.desc_loc: Channels light energy, building power the longer it's channeled.  Once released, a wave is sent forth that deals damage and gives vision in its path.  The longer it is channeled, the more damage is dealt.
5479.lore_loc: Ezalor's hidden light reveals itself in marvelous fashion.
notes_loc: Gives increasing vision over the channeling time.

5475.name: keeper_of_the_light_recall
5475.desc_loc: After a short delay, teleports the targeted friendly hero to your location.  If the targeted friendly hero takes player based damage during this time, the ability is interrupted.
notes_loc: If Keeper of the Light dies, the spell effect is interrupted.
Recall will interrupt channeling spells.
You can disable help to prevent Keeper from casting this spell on you.
Can be cast through the minimap, choosing the nearest friendly hero.

5485.name: wisp_tether
5485.desc_loc: Tethers Io to an allied unit, granting bonus movement speed to both. When Io restores health or mana, tethered units target gains a larger portion of that amount. The tether breaks when the allied unit moves too far away, or Io cancels the tether.
5485.lore_loc: The benevolent touch of Io brings strength from between the planes.
notes_loc: If you try to tether a unit that is 700 distance or further away from Io, he will latch on and pull himself closer to the tethered unit (to a distance of 300).
The tethered unit will heal faster and will heal even if Io is at full health.
Io's movement speed matches the tethered unit's.
5485.shard_loc: Tether stuns enemies touching it for 1.75 seconds and deals 150 damage. Does not affect the same unit more than once every 7 seconds. Increases movement speed bonus by 10%%.

5486.name: wisp_spirits
5486.desc_loc: Summon five particle spirits that dance in a circle around Io. If a particle collides with an enemy hero, it explodes, damaging all enemy units in an area around it.  Creeps take minor damage from touching a particle spirit, but do not cause them to explode.  When its duration ends, any remaining Spirits explode.
5486.lore_loc: Io twists the particles of the universe with its unimaginable capabilities.
notes_loc: After summoning, Io can call the spirits in and out.
5486.scepter_loc: Spirits now passively spawn around Io constantly every second. Max of 5.

5487.name: wisp_overcharge
5487.desc_loc: Io gains bonus attack speed, spell amplification, and HP Regen based on max health.  If Io is Tethered to an ally, that unit also gains the bonuses.
5487.lore_loc: Drawing on the energy of matter from all worlds, Io begins the unravelling of time.

5490.name: wisp_spirits_in
5490.desc_loc: Sends the spirits closer to you. Can be toggled on and off.

5493.name: wisp_spirits_out
5493.desc_loc: Sends the spirits farther away from you. Can be toggled on and off.

5488.name: wisp_relocate
5488.desc_loc: Teleports Io and any tethered ally to any location. After the spell expires Io and any tethered ally will return to their original location. Double-click to teleport to your team's base fountain.
5488.lore_loc: Io is the embodiment of the mystery of the universe.
notes_loc: Enemies receive a visual indicator in the world and on the minimap of the target location during the cast delay.
If Io is disabled during the cast delay, Relocate is cancelled.
If an allied hero is Tethered, that hero will teleported along with you. You can break the tether at any time to prevent that hero from teleporting with you.

6808.name: special_bonus_unique_wisp_4
6808.desc_loc: While tethered to a friendly Hero, each time that Hero attacks, Io will attack the same target automatically.

5480.name: visage_grave_chill
5480.desc_loc: Visage drains the movement and attack speed of the targeted unit, gaining it for itself.
5480.lore_loc: The warmth of the sun is never felt in the dark cold of the Narrow Maze.
notes_loc: The two buffs can be removed separately by purge.
The speed gained is independent of the speed lost on the target.
Familiars within %radius% range of Visage will also receive bonuses from Grave Chill.

5481.name: visage_soul_assumption
5481.desc_loc: Visage gathers charges of soul essence each time nearby heroes take more than %damage_limit% damage. When the essence is released, it deals base damage as well as damage for each gathered soul charge.
5481.lore_loc: The collected souls of the dead reach out to bring another into their fold.
notes_loc: Charges are only gained for damage greater than %damage_min% and less than %damage_max% that is dealt by a player or Roshan.  Self-damage or Soul Assumption damage isn't counted.
Soul Assumption cannot be disjointed.

5482.name: visage_gravekeepers_cloak
5482.desc_loc: Visage generates a layered barrier that protects him from damage.  If he receives damage from a player, one layer is removed, and takes time to recover.
5482.lore_loc: Visage's tough scales share equal properties of ghost and stone, making it nearly impervious to blade and magical assault.
notes_loc: Each time Visage receives damage greater than the Minimum Damage that was not self-inflicted and was from a player owned source, a layer is removed.
Familiars within %radius% range of Visage will receive the current damage reduction from Gravekeeper's Cloak.
5482.shard_loc: Grants Visage the ability to cast Stone Form. Restores up to 35% of your health. Cooldown: 60. Manacost: 125.

683.name: visage_silent_as_the_grave
683.desc_loc: Turns Visage and familiars invisible, granting Visage 20%% movement speed and upgrading its movement type to flying. When Visage or its familiars leave invisibility they deal %bonus_damage%%% more damage for %bonus_duration% seconds. Lasts %invis_duration% seconds. Invisibility ends when attacking or casting.

5483.name: visage_summon_familiars
5483.desc_loc: Conjures two blind Familiars to fight for Visage.  Familiars possess the Stone Form ability, that allows them to turn into stone, stunning enemies upon landing.  While in Stone Form, Familiars are invulnerable, and rapidly regenerate their health.  Familiars grant high bounty when killed.
5483.lore_loc: Guardians of the Narrow Maze, Necro'lic's Familiars stand watch over his domain.
notes_loc: Casting Summon Familiars will replace any existing Familiars.
Familiars within range of Visage will receive bonuses from Gravekeeper's Cloak and Grave Chill.

6522.name: special_bonus_unique_visage_3
6522.desc_loc: A second Soul Assumption is launched towards a random enemy unit within the cast range, prioritizing Heroes.

5494.name: slark_dark_pact
5494.desc_loc:
After a short delay, Slark sacrifices some of his life blood, purging most negative debuffs and dealing damage to enemy units around him and to himself.  Slark only takes 50% of the damage.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
5494.lore_loc: Slithereen are capable of quickly regrowing appendages, in case of critical injury, to save their own lives.
notes_loc: %delay% seconds after cast, a series of %total_pulses% pulses separated by %pulse_interval% seconds deal the damage.
Each pulse also removes debuffs from Slark.
You can't kill yourself with this skill.
The pulses stop if Slark dies.

5495.name: slark_pounce
5495.desc_loc: Slark leaps forward, grabbing the first hero he connects with.  That unit is leashed, and can only move a limited distance away from Slark's landing position.
5495.lore_loc: Time in the Dark Reef made Slark a dangerous assassin; aggressive and fearless.
notes_loc: On cast, Slark leaps forward at a speed of %pounce_speed%, stopping when he latches onto an enemy hero or has traveled %pounce_distance% distance.
Spell Immune units cannot be leashed.
Trees will be destroyed around Slark's landing location.
5495.scepter_loc: Provides %max_charges% charges and increases pounce range.

5496.name: slark_essence_shift
5496.desc_loc: Slark steals the life essence of enemy heroes with his attacks, draining each of their attributes and converting them to bonus Agility. If Slark kills an affected enemy hero, he permanently steals %stat_loss% Agility.
5496.lore_loc: With each strike at his adversaries, Slark's knowledge of their weaknesses improves.
notes_loc: Attributes cannot be dropped below 1.
Essence Shifted stats are returned to normal on death. The stat return for Slark and for the affected hero are separate.
To permanently steal Agility, Slark doesn't need to land the killing blow, as long as the enemy hero is killed within 300 range of Slark while having the Essence Shift debuff.

729.name: slark_depth_shroud
729.desc_loc: Creates a 300 AoE cloud at the target location for %duration% seconds. All allies inside the radius are hidden and affected by Shadow Dance. Cast Range: 800. Cooldown: 75

5497.name: slark_shadow_dance
5497.desc_loc: When used, Slark hides himself in a cloud of shadows, becoming immune to detection. Attacking, casting spells, and using items will not reveal Slark.  Passively, when not visible to the enemy team, Slark gains bonus movement speed and health regeneration.
5497.lore_loc: The hidden Thirteenth is a slippery foe.
notes_loc: If Slark is damaged by a neutral unit, the passive movement and health regeneration bonuses are lost for %neutral_disable% seconds.
The passive movement and health regeneration bonuses have a %activation_delay% second activation and deactivation delay.

5504.name: medusa_split_shot
5504.desc_loc:
Medusa magically splits her shot into several arrows. These arrows deal a lower percent of her normal damage.

The extra targets will not receive other attack effects (such as critical strike).
5504.lore_loc: All who encounter the cursed Gorgon will feel her rage.
notes_loc: Secondary targets will be the closest enemy units excluding the primary target.
If illusions of Medusa are created while Split Shot is active, they will also have this ability.

5505.name: medusa_mystic_snake
5505.desc_loc: A mystic snake made of energy jumps from target to target dealing damage. After it reaches its last target, it returns to Medusa to replenish her with mana. The snake deals more damage per jump and returns %snake_mana_steal%%% mana based on the targets' total mana.
5505.lore_loc: The Gorgon's curse is her greatest strength.
notes_loc: Mystic Snake cannot be disjointed.
5505.scepter_loc: Causes Mystic Snake to turn enemies hit into stone. Stone duration increases with each bounce of the Mystic Snake.

5506.name: medusa_mana_shield
5506.desc_loc: Creates a shield that absorbs %absorption_pct%%% of incoming damage in exchange for Medusa's mana. Provides bonus mana capacity.
5506.lore_loc: While Medusa was not gifted with eternal life upon birth, her curse bestowed her with impressive defensive powers.
notes_loc: Absorbs damage before any damage reduction takes place, meaning that armor will not reduce the amount of mana needed to absorb damage.

701.name: medusa_cold_blooded
701.desc_loc: When Medusa is targeted with a spell, a single-target Mystic Snake is sent back towards the enemy. Cooldown: 12.

5507.name: medusa_stone_gaze
5507.desc_loc: Any enemy units looking at Medusa will have their movement and attack speed slowed.  If %face_duration% seconds of total time is accumulated looking at Medusa while Stone Gaze is active, that unit will turn to stone.  Petrified units are stunned, and take bonus physical damage.
5507.lore_loc: The beauty of Medusa is legendary.
notes_loc: Regardless of when a unit receives the Stone Gaze buff while the ability is active on Medusa, it will still receive the full debuff duration.

6182.name: special_bonus_unique_medusa
6182.desc_loc: The duration of the stun is not affected.

6803.name: special_bonus_unique_medusa_4
6803.desc_loc: Allows on-hit effects to apply to the secondary attacks from Split Shot.

5508.name: troll_warlord_berserkers_rage
5508.desc_loc:
While active, Troll Warlord swaps from using ranged to melee attacks. Melee attacks have a chance to ensnare, preventing the target from moving or using mobility spells. Berserker's Rage also grants additional movement speed, armor, and decreases base attack time.

Whirling Axes has different functionality while Berserker's Rage is active.
5508.lore_loc: Like his anger, Troll Warlord's supply of axes is infinite.
notes_loc: Cooldowns of items that are different for ranged and melee units will be based on which form Troll Warlord was in when the item was used.

5509.name: troll_warlord_whirling_axes_ranged
5509.desc_loc: Troll hurls a fistful of five axes in a cone shape over %axe_range% range, slowing and damaging enemy units.
5509.lore_loc: Only axes fueled by hate whirl with such a deadly spin.
notes_loc: Does not affect Roshan.
5509.scepter_loc: Causes Ranged Axes to dispel enemies. Reduces cooldown and manacost.

5510.name: troll_warlord_whirling_axes_melee
5510.desc_loc: Troll hurls two axes around him in a close range area of effect, damaging enemy units and causing them to miss some attacks.
notes_loc: Does not affect Roshan.
5510.scepter_loc: Causes Melee Axes to dispel Troll Warlord. Reduces cooldown and manacost.

5511.name: troll_warlord_fervor
5511.desc_loc: With each continuous blow on the same target, Troll gains increased attack speed.  If Troll changes targets, the stacks drop to zero.
5511.lore_loc: If at first you don't succeed, strike, strike again.

728.name: troll_warlord_rampage
728.desc_loc: Global active. Grants all allied heroes %attack_speed% Attack Speed or %status_resistance%%% Status Resistance for %duration% seconds based on whichever stance Troll is currently in. Ranged provides attack speed and melee provides status resistance.

5512.name: troll_warlord_battle_trance
5512.desc_loc: Troll unleashes a powerful battle trance, that forces you to continuously attack the closest enemy unit within %range% range, prioritizing heroes. Damage does not kill you during this mode. Grants you bonus lifesteal, attack speed and movement speed. Applies a Basic Dispel.
5512.lore_loc: An adrenaline rush of pure hatred quickens your blades.
notes_loc: Troll can still use his abilities while affected by Battle Trance.
Troll can still be killed with Axe's Culling Blade.
5512.shard_loc: Casting Battle Trance now gives Troll Warlord a global aura that gives allied heroes (including himself) +60 Attack Speed.

6960.name: special_bonus_unique_troll_warlord_4
6960.desc_loc: Can be cast while stunned and applies a strong dispel to Troll Warlord.

5514.name: centaur_hoof_stomp
5514.desc_loc: Slams the ground, stunning and damaging nearby enemy units.
5514.lore_loc: When the mighty hoof of the Warrunner touches soil, the tremors are felt far and wide.

5515.name: centaur_double_edge
5515.desc_loc: Centaur strikes a mighty blow at melee range, damaging both himself and a small area around the target. Deals extra damage based on your strength. Centaur cannot die from Double Edge.
5515.lore_loc: In the spurs of combat, Bradwarden's vicious strikes sometimes cause self-inflicted collateral damage.
notes_loc: Double Edge deals magic type damage to both the targets and himself.
5515.shard_loc: Causes Double Edge to increase Centaur's strength by 15%% per hero hit for 15 seconds. Duration refreshes per stack. Max 5 Stacks. Slows enemies by 25%% for 2 seconds.

5516.name: centaur_return
5516.desc_loc: Centaur counters all attacks, dealing damage back to the attacker. Returns a fixed amount plus a percentage of your strength. Deals half damage to towers.
5516.lore_loc: Bradwarden has no need to parry his opponent's attacks; his armor-like hide does it for him.
notes_loc: Retaliate triggers when the attack hits.
Retaliate deals damage to towers.

5517.name: centaur_stampede
5517.desc_loc: Centaur leads all allies into a vicious charge causing them to move through units at max speed and stop any enemy units they trample. Trampled enemies take damage based on Centaur Warrunner's strength. Each enemy can be trampled once.
5517.lore_loc: The great belt of Omexe, which labels Bradwarden as the greatest warrior of his kind, incites his fellow gladiators to follow him into barbarous combat.
5517.scepter_loc: Heroes affected by Stampede take reduced damage, and are able to run through obstructions, including trees and up cliffs. Increases duration by 1 second.

6322.name: special_bonus_unique_centaur_1
6322.desc_loc: Allied heroes within 1200 range of Centaur gain the Return Damage aspect of Retaliate.

5518.name: magnataur_shockwave
5518.desc_loc: Magnus sends out a wave of force, damaging enemy units in a line, pulling them towards him and slowing them for a brief period.
5518.lore_loc: Mt. Joerlak was a somewhat unstable mass, and Magnus has learned to channel its reverberations.
5518.scepter_loc: Magnus releases 3 Shockwaves traveling away from him at 30-degree angles. After reaching their limit, the Shockwaves return to their origin, dealing 75%% damage and pulling a second time.

5519.name: magnataur_empower
5519.desc_loc: Gives an allied unit bonus damage and cleave on attack. Magnus receives %self_multiplier%%% larger bonus.
5519.lore_loc: With a deep bellow, Magnus displays his true power.
notes_loc: The bonus damage is based only on base damage and damage from primary attributes.
Cleave damage goes through spell immunity.
Ranged units cannot Cleave.

5520.name: magnataur_skewer
5520.desc_loc: Magnus rushes forward, goring enemy units on his massive tusk. Heroes hit on the way will be dragged to the destination, then damaged and affected by slowed movement and attack speed.
5520.lore_loc: Magnoceros horns are valuable in direct proportion to their danger to prospective merchants.
notes_loc: Doesn't affect Spell Immune units.

649.name: magnataur_horn_toss
649.desc_loc: Magnus tosses any enemies in front of him, launching them to his rear. Enemies spend %air_duration% seconds in the air, then take %damage% damage and are stunned for %stun_duration% seconds upon landing.

5521.name: magnataur_reverse_polarity
5521.desc_loc: Magnus changes properties of matter, sucking all nearby enemies in front of him and stunning them with a powerful slam and dealing damage.
5521.lore_loc: Magnus fights with the fury of the erupting Mt. Joerlak.

5524.name: shredder_whirling_death
5524.desc_loc: Timbersaw whirls extremely sharp edges, damaging enemies and destroying trees around him in an area.  If an enemy hero is affected, it loses some of its primary attribute for a short duration.  Whirling Death will deal bonus damage per tree destroyed.
5524.lore_loc: In the case that Rizzrack gets surrounded by the vines and plants of his nightmares, he has an immediate chainsaw defense.

5525.name: shredder_timber_chain
5525.desc_loc: Timbersaw fires a chain that embeds itself in the first tree it hits, pulling him towards it.  Any enemy in the path takes damage.
5525.lore_loc: You never know when you might need to escape from malevolent saplings.

5526.name: shredder_reactive_armor
5526.desc_loc: Each time Timbersaw is attacked, he gains increased health regen and armor.
5526.lore_loc: The saw-suit is equipped to react to the slightest touch with fortified defenses.

5645.name: shredder_chakram_2
5645.desc_loc: Fires a secondary saw blade at the target location where it will spin in place, dealing damage in an area around it.  Additionally, for each 5% of health missing, enemies caught in the saw blade move more slowly. The blade deals damage and cuts down trees in its path when fired and retracted.  While active the ability costs mana, and Timbersaw loses the ability to attack.
5645.lore_loc: Cut cut cut cut cut cut cut cut cut cut cut!
notes_loc: The Chakram will return if Timbersaw runs out of mana or moves over %break_distance% distance away.
Slow effects from two chakrams do not stack.

651.name: shredder_flamethrower
651.desc_loc: Releases a %width% width flame that extends %length% range in the direction Timbersaw is facing. Applies a debuff that deals %damage_per_second% damage per second and slows by 30%%. Affects buildings for 40%% damage. Lasts %duration% seconds. Debuff lingers for 2 seconds.

5527.name: shredder_chakram
5527.desc_loc: Fires Timbersaw's main saw blade at the target location where it will spin in place, dealing damage in an area around it.  Enemies caught in the saw blade will move more slowly for every %slow_health_percentage%%% of health missing. The blade deals damage and cuts down trees in its path when fired and retracted.  While active the ability costs mana, and Timbersaw loses the ability to attack.
notes_loc: The Chakram will return if Timbersaw runs out of mana or moves over %break_distance% distance away.

5548.name: bristleback_viscous_nasal_goo
5548.desc_loc: Covers a target in snot, causing it to have reduced armor and movement speed.  Multiple casts stack and refresh the duration.
5548.lore_loc: Having caught a cold while stuck in the snow, Bristleback turns it to his advantage.
5548.scepter_loc: Viscous Nasal Goo becomes a no target area of effect ability, applying to all enemies within range. Increases Stack Limit to %stack_limit_scepter%.

5549.name: bristleback_quill_spray
5549.desc_loc: Sprays enemy units with quills dealing damage in an area of effect around Bristleback.  Deals bonus damage for every time a unit was hit by Quill Spray in the last %quill_stack_duration% seconds.
5549.lore_loc: An enforcer's honor can be a prickly thing.  So can his quills.
notes_loc: Quill Spray damage is not reduced by damage block abilities.

5550.name: bristleback_bristleback
5550.desc_loc: Bristleback takes less damage if hit on the sides or rear.  If Bristleback takes %quill_release_threshold% damage from the rear, he releases a Quill Spray of the current level.
5550.lore_loc: Turning his back to a fight might be just the thing.
notes_loc: Bristleback's rear is considered to be within 70 degrees from the back.
Bristleback's side is considered to be within 110 degrees from the back.

643.name: bristleback_hairball
643.desc_loc: Coughs a quill-packed hairball towards the target location. Erupts at the location, hitting enemies in a 700 radius with Goo and 2 Quills.

5551.name: bristleback_warpath
5551.desc_loc: Bristleback works himself up into a fury every time he casts a spell, increasing his movement speed and damage.
5551.lore_loc: 'Temper, temper,' his mum always chided.  But in a fight, a temper can come in handy.
notes_loc: Bristleback's illusions will receive the bonuses.
Items will not trigger Warpath.

5565.name: tusk_ice_shards
5565.desc_loc: Tusk compresses shards of ice into a ball of frozen energy that damages all enemies it comes in contact with. When the ball reaches its target destination the shards are released, creating a barrier that lasts for %shard_duration% seconds.
5565.lore_loc: In the frozen tundra near the Barrier, after the last sun of autumn has set, ice can form with alarming speed.
notes_loc: Creates an impassable barrier.

5566.name: tusk_snowball
5566.desc_loc: Tusk begins rolling into a snowball. Allies within a %snowball_grab_radius% radius can also be added to the snowball by right-clicking on them, even while the snowball is moving. Once launched, any enemies caught in the snowball's path will be stunned and take damage. Each allied Hero in the snowball will add to its damage.
5566.lore_loc: Tales are still told of the wild feat that ended the grand brawl at White Fields.
notes_loc: The snowball will break apart a maximum of 3 seconds after launch.
The snowball can be launched early by pressing using the Launch Snowball ability.
Doesn't carry illusions, but will carry Meepo clones and other units that Tusk controls.
Each Meepo clone added to the snowball will add its own bonus damage and speed.
Allies can click on a snowball to add themselves to it.

7322.name: tusk_tag_team
7322.desc_loc: Temporarily applies a negative debuff aura around you, causing enemies that are attacked under it to take bonus physical damage and reduced movement speed. Lasts %debuff_duration% seconds.
7322.lore_loc: Even far from Cobalt, Tusk carries the 'Barrier Chill' in his very bones.
notes_loc: Affects attacks from allied heroes, Tusk or any of his units.

5672.name: tusk_walrus_kick
5672.desc_loc: Kicks the closest enemy unit in a targeted direction, stunning and damaging them.
5672.lore_loc: Tusk may have made his name with his fists, but the wise enemy is wary of any and all limbs.

5567.name: tusk_frozen_sigil
5567.desc_loc: Summons a flying Sigil that slows movement speed by -40% for enemies within 650 radius. Lasts 25 seconds. Cooldown: 30
notes_loc: If no order is given, the Sigil will follow Tusk.

The Sigil has unobstructed movement, has a 310 movement speed, requires 3/3/4/4 hero attacks to destroy and 12/12/16/16 creep attacks to destroy, provides 400/400 vision, and gives a 90/100/110/120 gold bounty.
Heroes deal 1 damage to the sigil, while non-hero units deal 0.25 damage.

5568.name: tusk_walrus_punch
5568.desc_loc: Tusk connects with his mighty Walrus Punch, a critical strike so powerful it launches its victim into the air. The victim is slowed upon landing.
5568.lore_loc: It never matters who throws the first punch, only who throws the last.
notes_loc: Walrus PUNCH has true strike.

6962.name: special_bonus_unique_tusk_4
6962.desc_loc: Walrus Punch gains a chance to be triggered on normal attacks, independent of mana cost or cooldown.

5581.name: skywrath_mage_arcane_bolt
5581.desc_loc: Skywrath Mage launches a slow-moving bolt of arcane magic, dealing damage to an enemy unit based on Skywrath Mage's intelligence.
5581.lore_loc: Within the Ghastly Eyrie's endless intrigue, only the clever and calm can hope to survive.
notes_loc: The projectile moves very slowly (500 ms), providing 325 vision around it.  Upon impact, it will reveal the target area for 3.34 seconds.
Arcane Bolt cannot be disjointed.
5581.scepter_loc: When Skywrath Mage casts Arcane Bolt, a different random target within %scepter_radius% range willl be hit with the same ability. Heroes will take priority.

5582.name: skywrath_mage_concussive_shot
5582.desc_loc: Skywrath Mage sets off a long range shot that hits the closest hero within a long range.  Upon impact, it deals damage and slows in an area of effect.
5582.lore_loc: Those who serve the court of the Ghastly Eyrie are ever locked in covert war. One must always know where danger lurks nearest.
notes_loc: If no enemy heroes are in range or they are in fog, Concussive Shot targets the nearest enemy creep.
Damages creeps around the impact area.
Provides 400 vision around the projectile, and reveals the target area for 3.34 seconds upon impact.
5582.scepter_loc: When Skywrath Mage casts Concussive Shot, a different random target within cast range will be hit with the same ability. Heroes will take priority.

5583.name: skywrath_mage_ancient_seal
5583.desc_loc: Skywrath Mage seals the targeted unit with an ancient rune, silencing it and causing it to take additional damage from spells.
5583.lore_loc: A holy incantation, whosoever finds themselves touched by Avilliva's sigil must suffer in penitent silence.
notes_loc: The magic damage resistance reduction doesn't affect creeps.
5583.shard_loc: Ancient Seal debuff now causes other debuffs applied to last 50%% longer. Grants vision over the target.
5583.scepter_loc: Anytime Skywrath Mage casts Ancient Seal, a different random target within %scepter_radius% range will be affected by the same ability. Heroes will take priority.

5584.name: skywrath_mage_mystic_flare
5584.desc_loc: Skywrath Mage uses his ultimate magical ability to conjure a precise and violent mystical field that lays waste to his adversaries. Deals massive damage distributed evenly among any Heroes in the area over %duration% seconds.
5584.lore_loc: Only the most practiced of Skywrath sorcerers could hope to shape the skies into such a storm.
notes_loc: Mystic Flare only affects Heroes; it does not damage illusions or creep heroes.
Spell immune enemies do not count toward the damage distribution.
Mystic Flare will damage enemy creeps if no enemy heroes are present.
5584.shard_loc: Causes Mystic Flare to not split its damage and affect creeps as well.
5584.scepter_loc: When Skywrath Mage casts Mystic Flare, another Mystic Flare will be created on the position of a different random target enemy within %scepter_radius% range. Heroes will take priority

5585.name: abaddon_death_coil
5585.desc_loc: Abaddon releases a coil of deathly mist that can damage an enemy unit or heal a friendly unit at the cost of some of Abaddon's health.
5585.lore_loc: A mysterious vapor from the Font of Avernus now infuses the breath of Abaddon, who releases it at will.
notes_loc: Abaddon can not kill himself with this skill.

5586.name: abaddon_aphotic_shield
5586.desc_loc:
Summons dark energies around an ally unit, creating a shield that absorbs a set amount of damage before expiring. When the shield is destroyed it will burst and deal damage equal to the amount it could absorb to an area around it. Removes certain types of negative buffs and stuns on cast.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
5586.lore_loc: The powers of the black mist rise to absorb attacks like the black mist absorbs light.
notes_loc: The max damage is always dealt whether the shield is destroyed by expiring or absorbing damage.
The explosion does not damage units hidden by the fog of war.

5587.name: abaddon_frostmourne
5587.desc_loc: Abaddon strikes an enemy, slowing the target's movement speed. If the target gets hit %hit_count% times, they become affected by a chilling curse causing them to be silenced and slowed, and all attacks against them gain an attack speed boost.
5587.lore_loc: While the baptized draw strength from the Font, the gifts of Avernus are debilitating to the uninitiated.
5587.shard_loc: Causes Mist Coil and Aphotic Shield to apply a Curse of Avernus stack on enemies. Increase base slow by 10%%. Lowers Cooldown for Mist Coil and Aphotic Shield by 1 second.

5588.name: abaddon_borrowed_time
5588.desc_loc:
When activated, all damage dealt to you will heal instead of harm. Most negative buffs will also be removed. If the ability is not on cooldown, it will automatically activate if your health falls below %hp_threshold%.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
5588.lore_loc: The most unnatural of all the gifts of the Font of Avernus, this power defies mortal understanding.  What should hurt, instead heals; and what should kill gives strength anew.
notes_loc: Borrowed Time can be manually activated while Abaddon is disabled, but not while silenced.  The passive activation can still occur while silenced.
Aphotic Shield does not block any damage to Abaddon when Borrowed Time is active, allowing him to heal.
5588.scepter_loc: Increases duration. While Borrowed Time is active, anytime an ally takes more than %ally_threshold_scepter% damage while within %redirect_range_scepter% range of Abaddon, an individual Mist Coil will automatically fire towards that ally.

5589.name: elder_titan_echo_stomp
5589.desc_loc: Elder Titan and his Astral Spirit both stomp the ground, damaging and knocking nearby enemy units unconscious around their locations.  The Elder Titan stomp deals physical damage, while the Spirit stomp deals magical damage.
5589.lore_loc: The force of creation still echoes in the stomp of the Titan.
notes_loc: If a unit is hit by Astral Spirit and Elder Titan, they will take both instances of damage.
5589.shard_loc: Allows you to switch Echo Stomp to autocast. When cast while on autocast, Elder Titan will take the place of the Astral Spirit as it completes its stomp.

5591.name: elder_titan_ancestral_spirit
5591.desc_loc:
Elder Titan sends forth his Astral Spirit, damaging any units it passes through.  When the spirit rejoins the Titan, it grants bonus damage and movement speed for each unit it passed through.

The Astral Spirit can be controlled and possesses the Echo Stomp, Return Spirit, and Natural Order abilities.
5591.lore_loc: Like the four fundamentals, Elder Titan exists across all planes at once and can draw other aspects of himself to assist in times of need.
5591.scepter_loc: Causes you to become Spell Immune for %scepter_magic_immune_per_hero% seconds per affected enemy hero when the spirit returns to you.

5593.name: elder_titan_natural_order
5593.desc_loc: Reduces all elements to their basic levels, removing base armor and magic damage resistance from nearby enemy units. The armor reduction is centered around the hero, while the magic armor reduction is centered around Astral Spirit.
5593.lore_loc: As it was at the beginning, Elder Titan makes it so again.
notes_loc: When the Astral Spirit isn't present, both the armor and magic armor reduction is centered around Elder Titan.

5594.name: elder_titan_earth_splitter
5594.desc_loc: Sends forth a jagged crack in front of Elder Titan. After 3 seconds, the crack implodes, slowing movement while dealing damage to each enemy based on their maximum life. Half of the damage dealt is Magical damage, while the other half is Physical damage.
5594.lore_loc: That which he created, the titan tears asunder.

5595.name: legion_commander_overwhelming_odds
5595.desc_loc: Turns the enemies' numbers against them, dealing damage and granting you bonus movement speed per unit or per hero.  Deals bonus damage to illusions and summoned units as a percent of their current health.
5595.lore_loc: The archers of Stonehall are ready at Tresdin's command.

5596.name: legion_commander_press_the_attack
5596.desc_loc:
Removes debuffs and disables from the target friendly unit, and grants bonus attack speed and health regen for a short time.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
5596.lore_loc: The rallying horn of the Bronze Legion is able to inspire any heart.
5596.shard_loc: Press The Attack targets now gain Spell Immunity for 1.75 seconds. Reduces cooldown by 2 seconds.

5597.name: legion_commander_moment_of_courage
5597.desc_loc: When attacked, Legion Commander has a chance to immediately counterattack with bonus lifesteal.
5597.lore_loc: Tresdin knows that an enemy's most vulnerable moment often follows their fiercest stroke.

5598.name: legion_commander_duel
5598.desc_loc: Legion Commander and the target enemy hero are forced to attack each other for a short duration.  Neither hero can use items or abilities.  If either hero dies during the duration, the hero winning the Duel gains permanent bonus damage.
5598.lore_loc: To face a soldier of Stonehall in single combat is a challenge few can resist.
notes_loc: Duels will end if the units are pushed 2000 units apart.
Winning a Duel automatically casts Press the Attack on yourself.
5598.shard_loc: While Dueling, immediately and every 2 seconds, an Overwhelming Odds is cast centered on a random enemy unit within 900 radius. Does not center on the same target twice. Prioritizes heroes.
5598.scepter_loc: Increases Duel duration, and makes Legion Commander and her opponent only take 50% damage from other sources. Reduces cooldown by 20 seconds.

5603.name: ember_spirit_searing_chains
5603.desc_loc: Ember Spirit unleashes fiery bolas that wrap around nearby enemies, anchoring them in place and dealing damage each second.
5603.lore_loc: Xin's harshest lessons often employed the use of red-hot chains.
notes_loc: Targets are chosen randomly around Xin.
Does not affect Spell Immune or invisible units.
Interrupts channeling spells.

5604.name: ember_spirit_sleight_of_fist
5604.desc_loc: Ember Spirit dashes around with blazing speed, attacking all enemies in the targeted area of effect, then returning to his start location.  Deals bonus damage to heroes, and less damage to creeps.
5604.lore_loc: The studied warrior must whip and weave through its enemies, burning each without pause.
notes_loc: Targets are determined when the spell is cast.
A regular attack is done to each target every %attack_interval% seconds.
Any attack modifier that Xin has (such as Critical Strike, Bash, Cleave, or Orb effects) will be applied normally on these attacks.
Abilities and items can be used while Sleight of Fist is active.

5605.name: ember_spirit_flame_guard
5605.desc_loc: Ember Spirit surrounds himself with a ring of fire that consumes incoming magic damage, leaving him unharmed.  Flame Guard deals damage per second in an area around Ember Spirit while Flame Guard is active.  If the shield is broken, the damage is also lost.
5605.lore_loc: An enemy should never be allowed to approach without difficulty.
notes_loc: Magic damage reduction is calculated before any reductions.

5607.name: ember_spirit_activate_fire_remnant
5607.desc_loc: Select the Fire Remnant to arrive at.
5607.lore_loc: With blazing speed does a spirit fly!

5606.name: ember_spirit_fire_remnant
5606.desc_loc: Ember Spirit generates Fire Remnant charges every %charge_restore_time% seconds, with a max of %max_charges% charges. Releasing a charge sends a Fire Remnant that runs to the target location at %speed_multiplier%%% Ember Spirit's speed.  Using Activate Fire Remnant, Ember Spirit can dash out to his Remnants, dealing damage along the way and exploding them upon arrival.  The targeted Remnant will be arrived at last.
5606.lore_loc: By the spirit's power are Xin's teachings spread anew.
notes_loc: Starts with 3 charges (maximum).
5606.shard_loc: Fire Remnants deal 45 damage per second in a 600 AoE around them. If an enemy hero dies within 400 range of Ember Spirit, a Fire Remnant charge will be replenished.
5606.scepter_loc: Increases cast range, initial remnant speed, and maximum charges. Activate Fire Remnant costs less mana.

5608.name: earth_spirit_boulder_smash
5608.desc_loc: Earth Spirit smashes the target enemy or ally, sending them in the direction he is facing. If Earth Spirit targets an area, he will smash the nearest Stone Remnant in a %remnant_smash_radius_tooltip% radius. The travelling unit or Remnant damages all enemy units it hits.  If an enemy is hit by a Stone Remnant, they are also slowed. Stone Remnants travel further than other units.
5608.lore_loc: It is with the power of a mountain that Earth Spirit strikes his enemies.

5609.name: earth_spirit_rolling_boulder
5609.desc_loc: Earth Spirit gathers himself into a boulder and, after a %delay%s delay, rolls toward the target location, damaging and stunning enemy units. He will stop if he collides with an enemy hero or is stunned. If he rolls over a Stone Remnant, he will travel further and faster, and stun enemies for longer.
5609.lore_loc: Calling upon his connection to the land, the Earth Spirit draws loose stone to him, which forms a protective ball that he can use to roll short distances.
notes_loc: Rolling over a Stone Remnant will destroy the Remnant.
The boulder has a radius of 150.

5610.name: earth_spirit_geomagnetic_grip
5610.desc_loc: Earth Spirit pulls the target Stone Remnant. Enemies struck by the gripped target will be silenced and take damage.
5610.lore_loc: Like calls to like. Even the minerals found in the blood and bones of living beings are not immune to the call of the Earth Spirit.
notes_loc: Will not work on a unit inside Chronosphere, Duel, or Black Hole.
Geomagnetic Grip can also target allied creeps.

5611.name: earth_spirit_stone_caller
5611.desc_loc: Call a Stone Remnant to the target location.  Stone Remnants have no vision and are invulnerable, and can be used with Earth Spirit's abilities.  Calling a Stone Remnant consumes a charge, which recharge over time.
5611.lore_loc: Earth Spirit calls forth a remnant of his stone army, long buried with him in the dark embrace of the Earth.
5611.shard_loc: Causes Stone Remnant to provide 375 ground vision. Increases charge count by 4.

5648.name: earth_spirit_petrify
5648.desc_loc:
Earth Spirit temporarily enchants a hero, granting them the properties of a Stone Remnant. After a short duration the remnant shatters, releasing the hero and damaging nearby enemies.

Can be cast on Earth Remnants. Has a 5 second cooldown when used that way.
5648.lore_loc: Kaolin uses the elemental power of the Earth to temporarily petrify living beings, so that they might be conscripted into his stone funerary army.

5612.name: earth_spirit_magnetize
5612.desc_loc: Magnetizes units in a small nearby area, causing them to take damage for a short duration. Magnetized heroes cause nearby Stone Remnants to explode, destroying the remnant and refreshing Magnetize's duration on all nearby enemies. This process can repeat multiple times. If an enemy hero is affected by Geomagnetic Grip or Boulder Smash, all magnetized heroes share the effects.
5612.lore_loc: At the Earth Spirit's call, the minerals in the blood and bones of his enemies rebel against the bodies they find themselves in.

5613.name: abyssal_underlord_firestorm
5613.desc_loc: Calls down waves of fire that damage enemy units in the target area, burning for additional damage over time.
5613.lore_loc: The flames of conquest blaze forth from the darkest depths of the abyss.
5613.shard_loc: Firestorm can be self-targeted. When used that way, the Firestorm follows Underlord around. Increases the wave count by 3. Reduces cast point by half.

5614.name: abyssal_underlord_pit_of_malice
5614.desc_loc: A deadly pit is conjured at the target location; any unit that enters will be rooted. Each enemy unit within the pit are affected every %pit_interval% seconds.
5614.lore_loc: Twisting into the seams of reality itself, Vrogros' manifest hatred paralyzes those who defy his will.

5615.name: abyssal_underlord_atrophy_aura
5615.desc_loc: Nearby enemy units are weakened, losing a portion of their base damage. If an enemy dies while under this effect, Underlord gains temporary bonus damage.
5615.lore_loc: To merely stand in the presence of the Underlord is to feel the conviction of battle sapped from one's soul.

5616.name: abyssal_underlord_dark_rift
5616.desc_loc: Opens a dark rift at the targeted friendly unit's or building's position.  After a short delay, Underlord and all nearby friendly heroes are teleported to that unit's location.  Dark Rift can be cancelled at anytime during the cast.  If it is cancelled in this way or the target unit dies before the spell becomes active, Dark Rift goes into cooldown.
5616.lore_loc: They come without warning, leaving fire and blood where kingdoms once flourished.
notes_loc: Double-click to teleport to your team's base fountain.
5616.scepter_loc: Dark Rift has two charges and can be cast on allied heroes. Reduces cast delay by 1 second.

5619.name: terrorblade_reflection
5619.desc_loc: Terrorblade brings forth an invulnerable dark reflection of all enemy heroes in a target area. Affected enemy heroes are slowed and attacked by their reflection.
5619.lore_loc: In the fractal prison of Foulfell, Terrorblade learned the truth of this old tale: you are your own worst enemy.  Now it is a lesson he teaches others.
notes_loc: Reflections are untargetable, invulnerable illusions, that will be destroyed if the slow debuff is removed.
Reflections can only attack their source.

5620.name: terrorblade_conjure_image
5620.desc_loc: Creates an illusion of Terrorblade that deals damage.
5620.lore_loc: There's only one thing more dangerous than facing Terrorblade.  Facing MORE Terrorblades!
notes_loc: Illusions created by Conjure Image are visually different for enemies.

5621.name: terrorblade_metamorphosis
5621.desc_loc: Terrorblade transforms into a powerful demon with a ranged attack. Any of Terrorblade's illusions that are within %metamorph_aura_tooltip% range will also be transformed by Metamorphosis.
5621.lore_loc: Temper, temper. The rage rises up and takes control.  Meet Terrorblade's own worst self.
notes_loc: Cooldowns of items that are different for ranged and melee units will be based on which form Terrorblade was in when the item was used.

699.name: terrorblade_demon_zeal
699.desc_loc: Costs %health_cost_pct%%% of Terrorblade's Current HP to cast, providing him +%berserk_bonus_movement_speed% Movement and +%berserk_bonus_attack_speed% Attack Speed for %duration% seconds. Provides %melee_bonus%%% more bonus while melee. Cooldown: 14.

425.name: terrorblade_terror_wave
425.desc_loc: Causes a wave to travel outwards in all directions forcing enemy heroes to become feared upon impact, and grants Terrorblade Metamorphosis for %scepter_meta_duration% seconds.

5622.name: terrorblade_sunder
5622.desc_loc: Severs the life from both Terrorblade and a target hero, exchanging a percentage of both units' current health. Some health points must remain.
5622.lore_loc: You didn't need that life, did you?  The demon marauder steals that which you hold most dear.

5623.name: phoenix_icarus_dive
5623.desc_loc: Phoenix dives forward in an arc with a fixed distance in the targeted direction, dealing damage over time and slowing the movement speed of any units it comes into contact with, and then orbiting back to its original position. If Phoenix casts Supernova, the dive ends.
5623.lore_loc: Though no stranger to travelling the cosmic void, soaring within an atmosphere offers unique pleasures.
notes_loc: Icarus Dive has a %dive_duration% second travel duration, and can be cancelled by casting the ability again while in flight.

5625.name: phoenix_fire_spirits
5625.desc_loc: Summons 4 fire spirits that circle around Phoenix. Each spirit can be launched independently at a targeted area of effect. Affected enemy units take damage over time and have their attack speed greatly reduced.
5625.lore_loc: The ever-collapsing core of Phoenix often emits short-lived bursts of conscious light.
notes_loc: Fire Spirits reveal the area they strike for 1 second.
5625.shard_loc: Causes Fire Spirits to become a passive charge-based ability. Has 7 second replenish time.

5626.name: phoenix_sun_ray
5626.desc_loc: Phoenix expels a beam of light at the cost of its own health. The beam damages enemies and heals allies for a base amount plus a percentage of their health. The percentage increases as the beam continues to fire.
5626.lore_loc: The vent through which such stellar energy flows is mere atoms wide.
notes_loc: Sun Ray has a width of %radius% units, and a length of %abilitycastrange% units.
Sun Ray is canceled if Phoenix gets stunned, silenced, cycloned, hexed or slept.
Phoenix can use items and abilities without canceling Sun Ray.
5626.shard_loc: Allows Sun Ray to be cast during Supernova. Slows enemies by 12%.

5630.name: phoenix_supernova
5630.desc_loc:
The Phoenix willingly ends its current life for the chance to be reborn. Transforms into a burning sun that scorches enemies in a huge area. The sun can be destroyed by attacks from enemy Heroes. After %abilityduration% seconds the sun explodes, stunning all nearby enemies while restoring Phoenix to full health and mana with refreshed abilities.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
5630.lore_loc: The solar crucible of a Supernova may be fatal, yet from its flames arise new beacons to wander infinity.
5630.scepter_loc: Increases number of attacks to destroy Supernova and allows Phoenix to cast Supernova on an allied hero, bringing both into the sun to be reborn together.

5637.name: oracle_fortunes_end
5637.desc_loc:
CHANNELED - Gathers Oracle's power into a bolt of scouring energy that, when released, damages, roots, and purges enemies of buffs in an area around the target. If target is an ally it will only purge debuffs. The root duration is equal to the time spent channeling.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
5637.lore_loc: The astral orb crackles with power while raw energy lances out, temporarily disrupting an enemy's connection to their own body.

5638.name: oracle_fates_edict
5638.desc_loc: Oracle enraptures a target, disarming them and granting them %magic_damage_resistance_pct_tooltip%%% magic damage resistance. Can be cast on allies and enemies.
5638.lore_loc: An unbreakable prophecy resounds: a chosen ally shall briefly suffer no magics.  Other kinds of suffering however...
5638.scepter_loc: Fate's Edict no longer causes allies to be disarmed or enemies to be immune to magic damage.

5639.name: oracle_purifying_flames
5639.desc_loc: Burns away impurities, dealing heavy magic damage to the target before causing them to regenerate health over time. The amount of health regenerated over its duration exceeds the amount of initial damage. Can be cast on enemies and allies.
5639.lore_loc: Like a hall of mirrors might amplify the light of a single candle, the shattered walls of the universe can transform the light of prophecy into a burning torch.
notes_loc: The healing from Purifying Flames can be stacked with itself.

5640.name: oracle_false_promise
5640.desc_loc:
Temporarily alters an ally's destiny, delaying any healing or damage taken until False Promise ends. Any healing that is delayed by False Promise is doubled. Removes most negative status effects and disables on initial cast.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
5640.lore_loc: Foes and false prophets oft make lies of men's fates.
notes_loc: Delayed damage and healing will take armor and magic resistance reductions into account when received.
The delayed damage and healing takes effect as soon as the target becomes vulnerable.
5640.shard_loc: Causes False Promise to have a 0.15-second fade delay invisibility.

5599.name: techies_land_mines
5599.desc_loc: Plant an invisible mine that cannot be detected by True Sight, but is visible if an enemy is within the active %radius% AoE of the mine. Mines detonate if an enemy is standing within the active AoE for %proximity_threshold% seconds. The explosion deals full damage in the blast radius, and deals %building_damage_pct%%% damage to buildings.
notes_loc: Cannot be placed within active AoE of another Proximity Mine.
Proximity Mines do not block neutral creep camps from spawning.
Mines last until they explode or are destroyed.
Mines are triggered by invisible units.
Mines will not be triggered by some flying units.
Grants 30 gold if destroyed by an enemy hero.
Mines are triggered by, but do not damage spell-immune units.

5600.name: techies_stasis_trap
5600.desc_loc: Plant an invisible trap that roots nearby enemy units instantly when triggered.
notes_loc: Stasis Traps destroy all other Stasis Traps in their area of effect when they detonate.
Stasis Traps are not triggered by invisible units.
Stasis Traps do not block neutral creep camps from spawning.

5601.name: techies_suicide
5601.desc_loc: Techies hurtle themselves into the enemy's midst, detonating charges upon impact which deal massive area of effect damage and silence enemies. Upon landing, the assault deals Techies damage equal to 50% of their max health.
notes_loc: Dying from this ability counts as suicide, and does not award gold or experience to the enemy team.
Techies still earn experience for suicide kills made with this ability.
This ability destroys trees.
5601.shard_loc: Increases Blast Off! cast range by 300 and applies a 1.75 second stun to affected enemies.

5635.name: techies_focused_detonate
5635.desc_loc: Detonate all remote mines in the target area.
5635.lore_loc: Why light one fuse when you can light them all?

5644.name: techies_minefield_sign
5644.desc_loc: Plant a warning sign to remind enemies to step lightly. Only one sign can exist at a time. Lasts %lifetime% seconds.
5644.scepter_loc: Allows Minefield Sign to hide any Proximity Mines, Stasis Traps, and Remote Mines in an area around the sign from True Sight.

5602.name: techies_remote_mines
5602.desc_loc: Plant an invisible explosive that will only detonate after a brief delay when triggered.  Does not damage buildings.
