notes_loc: Grants 10 gold if destroyed by an enemy hero.

6998.name: special_bonus_unique_techies_4
6998.desc_loc: All mines, including Stasis Traps, can be ordered to move to a location once placed.

5651.name: winter_wyvern_arctic_burn
5651.desc_loc: Winter Wyvern soars upon an arctic wind, granting her unobstructed movement and allowing her to exhale a blistering chill into each attack. While soaring, her attacks travel further and faster, and slow enemies with a magical freeze that strips them of %percent_damage%%% of their current health each second. Her sight is also hardened against night's chill, granting her %night_vision_bonus% additional vision range at night while soaring.
5651.lore_loc: The same organ where some dragons stoke their inner flame is, in Auroth, a crucible of unimaginable cold. From deep within her frosty gullet, an exhalation sends enemies into burning agony.
notes_loc: Enemy units can only receive the Arctic Burn debuff once per cast.
This ability does not affect Roshan.
Reduces Winter Wyvern's attack point to %attack_point%.
The damage and slow from Arctic Burn can be dispelled.
5651.scepter_loc: Causes Arctic Burn to be a toggle ability, draining mana every second when active. Removes limit on number of attacks per target. Increases Winter Wyvern's movement speed.

5652.name: winter_wyvern_splinter_blast
5652.desc_loc: Launches a ball of brittle ice toward an enemy. The ice shatters on impact, leaving the primary target completely unaffected, while hurling damaging splinters into nearby enemies in a %split_radius% radius. Enemies struck by these splinters are slowed by %movespeed_slow_tooltip%%%.
5652.lore_loc: Produced slowly by specialized vesicles in her frozen gullet, Winter Wyvern blast shards of ice at her enemies.
notes_loc: The primary projectile moves at %projectile_speed% movement speed, or reaches the target in %projectile_max_time% second, whichever is faster.
The primary projectile cannot be disjointed.

5653.name: winter_wyvern_cold_embrace
5653.desc_loc: Encases an ally in an icy cocoon, freezing them solid while healing a base amount as well as a percentage of their maximum health each second. The cocoon blocks all physical damage.
5653.lore_loc: From winter's heart comes a cold, healing embrace. The ice slows the blood and allows the spell to better work its curative magic.
5653.shard_loc: When Cold Embrace ends, a Splinter Blast goes off at that location, hitting enemies within 1200 range. Reduces cooldown by 5 seconds.

5654.name: winter_wyvern_winters_curse
5654.desc_loc: Winter Wyvern freezes an enemy in place while striking those nearby with a maddening curse which causes them to attack their frozen ally with increased attack speed. The frozen ally and those cursed to attack their ally are immune to all damage from their enemies with the exception of Winter Wyvern or her controlled units.
5654.lore_loc: The oldest of the bookwurm’s spells, this curse lends truth to the old saw: sometimes the enemy of my enemy is my enemy still.
notes_loc: If the target dies to its allies, Winter Wyvern will receive credit for the kill.
Will only pierce the spell immunity of the primary target, not the target's surrounding allies.

6994.name: special_bonus_unique_winter_wyvern_4
6994.desc_loc: The slow is still applied for the same duration.

5677.name: arc_warden_flux
5677.desc_loc: Infuses a lone enemy unit with swirling, volatile energy, slowing its movement speed and dealing damage over time. The effect is muted if another enemy unit is near the target.
5677.lore_loc: An infinitesimal fraction of the power which imprisoned the Ancients.

5678.name: arc_warden_magnetic_field
5678.desc_loc: Generates a circular distortion field of magnetic energy that protects allied heroes and buildings within it by evading attacks coming from outside the field.
5678.lore_loc: Time and space are of little consequence to one as old as Zet.
5678.shard_loc: Magnetic Field now pushes enemies out of the area at cast time, and provides allies in it with +40% Magic Resistance. Slows enemies inside by 20%.

5679.name: arc_warden_spark_wraith
5679.desc_loc: Summons a Spark Wraith that slowly materializes and patrols a targeted area until an enemy comes within its range. Once a target has been found the wraith fuses with them, dealing magical damage and slowing the unit.
5679.lore_loc: Lesser fragments of Zet's original self.
notes_loc: Spark Wraiths can not be disjointed.
5679.scepter_loc: Causes Spark Wraiths to spawn a new Spark Wraith after impacting an enemy, which then starts its 3 second activation period.

5683.name: arc_warden_tempest_double
5683.desc_loc: Briefly refocusing its fractured elements into a single form, the Arc Warden is able to create a perfect electrical duplication of itself. The duplicate can use all of Arc Warden's current items and spells, except most consumables and items that drop on death. The duplicate has separate item and ability cooldowns.  The Tempest Double gives bounty gold to enemies when killed.
5683.lore_loc: Warped by the power of its peers, Arc Warden becomes what it despises most: disharmony.
notes_loc: Tempest Double and Refresher Orb cannot be used by the duplicate.

5716.name: monkey_king_boundless_strike
5716.desc_loc: Monkey King enlarges his staff and slams it against the ground, stunning enemies in a line and damaging them with a critical hit based on his attack. Has True Strike.
5716.lore_loc: The legendary Jingu Bang grows to match its master's will, ensuring no enemy can escape the Monkey King's reach.
notes_loc: Does not affect spell-immune enemies.

5721.name: monkey_king_tree_dance
5721.desc_loc: Monkey King jumps to a tree and perches atop it. While perched, he gains the Primal Spring ability-a channeled leap attack. If Monkey King's tree is destroyed, he falls and is stunned for 4 seconds. Taking damage from player controlled units or Roshan while on the ground puts Tree Dance on cooldown.
5721.lore_loc: Sun Wukong dances nimbly along the treetop canopy, always just out of arm's reach.
notes_loc: Tree Dance cooldown starts upon landing.
Right-clicking the ground will have Monkey King drop from the tree.
5721.shard_loc: Reduces cooldown to 0.3 and cast point to 0.1.

5723.name: monkey_king_jingu_mastery
5723.desc_loc: Monkey King's attacks awaken the Jingu Bang's power. Upon the fourth hit on the same enemy hero, Monkey King earns four charged attacks that have bonus damage and lifesteal.
5723.lore_loc: Always sensitive to the moods of its master, the Jingu Bang radiates power when Sun Wukong's combat fervor is on full display.
notes_loc: Hitting an enemy with Boundless Strike adds to the hit counter.
Repeatedly hitting an enemy refreshes the Jingu Mastery debuff duration.
Hit charges on enemies cannot be dispelled.

5725.name: monkey_king_wukongs_command
5725.desc_loc: Monkey King creates a circular formation of soldiers that spread out from his position. If Monkey King leaves the area his soldiers disperse. The soldiers have Monkey King's attack and only target heroes. Monkey King is granted bonus armor for the spell's duration.
5725.lore_loc: Monkey King rips out a tuft of fur to blow at his enemies, charging each strand to transform into a copy of himself.
notes_loc: Soldiers do not receive Jingu Mastery bonuses.
Soldiers do not copy Basher or Abyssal.
5725.scepter_loc: Spawns a monkey soldier near Monkey King at regular intervals. Soldiers do not spawn while invisible or on trees. Soldiers only attack buildings when Monkey King himself is nearby.

7025.name: special_bonus_unique_monkey_king_6
7025.desc_loc: Creates an additional ring of {s:value2} soldiers at {s:value} range from the center.

6339.name: dark_willow_bramble_maze
6339.desc_loc: Dark Willow creates a maze of brambles that grow in the target area after %initial_creation_delay% seconds.  Enemies that walk into a bramble are rooted and take damage over time.
6339.lore_loc: The fae realm exists all around you, merely waiting to draw you in...
notes_loc: Does not reveal rooted invisible enemies.
Does not interrupt channeling spells upon rooting.

6341.name: dark_willow_shadow_realm
6341.desc_loc: Dark Willow recedes into the shadows, becoming untargetable.  Her next attack has increased attack range and deals bonus magic damage, and will end Shadow Realm. Damage scales based on how long she remains under the effects of Shadow Realm, the maximum being reached after %max_damage_duration% seconds.
6341.lore_loc: What you can't see will most definitely hurt you.
notes_loc: Disjoints projectiles upon cast.
Grants phased movement.
Spells which require vision cannot affect Dark Willow in the Shadow Realm.
6341.scepter_loc: Attacking no longer takes Dark Willow out of Shadow Realm. Each attack still has bonus damage based on the duration of the buff.

6342.name: dark_willow_cursed_crown
6342.desc_loc: Dark Willow casts an ancient fae curse on the target. After a delay, the target and nearby enemies are stunned.
6342.lore_loc: Didn't anyone ever tell you? Never strike a deal with a fairy...
6342.shard_loc: Cursed Crown creates four brambles around the target after the counter ends. Triggers even upon dispel. Reduces cooldown by 3 seconds and stun delay by 1 second.

6340.name: dark_willow_bedlam
6340.desc_loc: Dark Willow's pet wisp roams around her for the duration, rapidly attacking nearby enemies.  Bedlam cannot be used while Terrorize is active.
6340.lore_loc: You'll have to excuse my friend Jex. He's really into murder.

8340.name: dark_willow_terrorize
8340.desc_loc: Dark Willow releases her pet wisp to terrorize her enemies. After a short delay, all enemies in the target area become fearful and run toward their home fountain. Terrorize cannot be used while Bedlam is active.
8340.lore_loc: You think you know the first thing about fear? Jex'll show you what that word truly means...
notes_loc: Terrorize provides vision on affected units.

6344.name: pangolier_swashbuckle
6344.desc_loc:
Vector Targeted. Pangolier dashes along the target line, then slashes all enemies in the drawn direction with several quick swipes.

Lucky Shot has a chance to activate from this damage.
6344.lore_loc: The Pangolier's blade is even nimbler than his tongue.
notes_loc: Attack modifiers have a chance to proc on Swashbuckle attacks.
Casting Swashbuckle during Rolling Thunder ends Rolling Thunder.

6461.name: pangolier_shield_crash
6461.desc_loc:
Pangolier jumps in the air and slams back to the ground in front of his current position, damaging all enemies in a radius. For each enemy hero hit, he gains a percentage of incoming damage reduction for a short time.

Forward movement is maintained if Shield Crash is used while Rolling Thunder is active, and allows Rolling Thunder to clear walls or cliffs.
6461.lore_loc: Only in the midst of his enemies does the Pangolier truly thrive.
6461.scepter_loc: Causes Shield Crash to cast a 2-attack Swashbuckle in every 90 degrees around your hero.

7307.name: pangolier_lucky_shot
7307.desc_loc: Pangolier rolls the dice and lets fate decide the outcome for his enemies. Grants a chance to slow, apply a Disarm and reduce armor.
7307.lore_loc: The Pangolier's blade is guided more often by whim than reason.

8027.name: pangolier_rollup
8027.desc_loc: Pangolier curls into an immobile protective ball for up to 4 seconds, gaining magic immunity and allowing him to turn. Can be cast during Rolling Thunder to temporarily hit the brakes. Can cast Rolling Thunder and Shield Crash during Roll Up. If enemies attack Pangolier during this, he will roll away from the attacker for 0.75 seconds, applying Rolling Thunder damage/stun if there are enemies in the way. Cooldown: 30

6343.name: pangolier_gyroshell
6343.desc_loc:
Pangolier curls into a spell-immune ball and rolls out. When rolling, he moves at an increased speed and can move through trees, but has a decreased ability to turn. Striking enemies knocks them back, inflicting damage and stunning them when they land. 

Colliding with walls or cliffs will cause a temporary pause while Pangolier reverses in direction.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
6343.lore_loc: Where his ancestors sought only refuge, the Pangolier saw opportunity...
notes_loc: Enemies can be stunned multiple times per use, but cannot be affected a subsequent time until the previous stun duration ends.
If Pangolier is disabled while rolling, he will continue to stun and knock enemies that come within range.

8000.name: grimstroke_dark_artistry
8000.desc_loc: Grimstroke paints a path of ink with his brush, damaging and slowing enemies. The damage is increased with each enemy the ink hits.
8000.lore_loc: The corruptive force of Grimstroke's ink, drawn from the reservoir of his fallen people, consumes any enemy caught in its path.

8006.name: grimstroke_ink_creature
8006.desc_loc:
Summons a phantom that moves quickly towards the target, latching to it when she arrives. Once latched, the phantom damages and silences. If she survives the full latch duration she rends her victim for heavy damage and refreshes Phantom's Embrace's cooldown.

Hero attacks against the phantom count as 3 attacks each.
8006.lore_loc: Grimstroke holds no sorrow for the downfall of his people. Only for Yaovhi, she who was most dear to him, does he feel even a semblance of longing.
notes_loc: The phantom falls off if the target becomes invisible or spell immune.
The phantom will return if the target dies during the latch.

8007.name: grimstroke_spirit_walk
8007.desc_loc: Grimstroke shrouds an allied unit in ink, increasing its movement speed. Enemies in range of the allied unit are damaged with inky tendrils over time. After %buff_duration% seconds it triggers, applying damage and stun in an area around the unit in proportion to how long ink tendril was near any hero.
8007.lore_loc: Now that the rise of the ink tide no longer threatens to overwhelm Grimstroke, its tendrils of power are never far from his hand.
8007.shard_loc: Causes Ink Swell to deal 40% more damage and heal the target for 40% of the damage Ink Swell deals. Upon expiration, the target will receive a strong dispell.

7852.name: grimstroke_dark_portrait
7852.desc_loc: Creates an ink illusion of a target enemy hero. Illusion is spell immune, and has bonus movement speed and attack damage.
7852.lore_loc: No dark creation is beyond the skill of the master's hand.

6491.name: grimstroke_soul_chain
6491.desc_loc: Binds a targeted enemy hero to its nearest allied hero within the bind radius, preventing both from moving away from each other. Any unit-targeted ability that either bound hero receives also gets cast on the other hero. If the bind is broken before the duration expires, the initial target will be bound to its nearest allied hero in the radius.
6491.lore_loc: The Ascended were chosen sons of Ashkavor, granted immense power by the bonds forged between their own souls and those they were charged with protecting. In the years that followed the ruination of his kin, Grimstroke discovered much more sinister applications for the binding rituals...
notes_loc: Affected units are leashed, and prevented from blinking.
Provides vision of both leashed units.

7701.name: void_spirit_aether_remnant
7701.desc_loc: Vector targeted. Void Spirit dispatches a remnant to the target location. The remnant stands watch over the region, facing the direction of his vector. When a unit crosses its gaze, the remnant pulls it in and damages it.
7701.lore_loc: Inai exists far beyond the scope of a single point in space and time.

6470.name: void_spirit_dissimilate
6470.desc_loc: Void Spirit temporarily fades into the aether, creating a number of portals through which he can reassemble himself. Upon exiting a portal, he damages all enemies in the area.
6470.lore_loc: Inai much prefers to observe our plane free from the confines of corporeal form.
6470.shard_loc: Adds a partial outer ring to Dissimilate. Increases damage by %shard_bonus_damage%.

7710.name: void_spirit_resonant_pulse
7710.desc_loc: Void Spirit wraps himself in a protective shield that absorbs physical damage and emits a single damaging pulse around him. The shield gains increased damage absorption for each enemy hero the pulse hits.
7710.lore_loc: Inai never hesitates to shroud himself in the essence of his true self when forced to interact with the mortal plane.
7710.scepter_loc: Causes Resonant Pulse to silence and gain two charges.

7705.name: void_spirit_astral_step
7705.desc_loc: Void Spirit tears a rift through the astral plane to appear at the target location, attacking all enemies along the path. This attack inflicts a void mark that slows for %pop_damage_delay% seconds and then detonates.
7705.lore_loc: A small step for Inai creates great devastation on the mortal plane.
notes_loc: Astral Step attacks do not cleave.

7714.name: special_bonus_unique_void_spirit_8
7714.desc_loc: Attacks made with Astral Step deal a critical strike.

6480.name: snapfire_scatterblast
6480.desc_loc: Snapfire unloads with a wide blast that damages and slows enemies in a cone. Enemies caught at point-blank range take an extra %point_blank_dmg_bonus_pct%%% damage.
6480.lore_loc: A favorite from her collection, Beadie crafted Ol' Rackatee as her first line of defense when she ventured into the Outlands.
6480.shard_loc: Causes Scatterblast to knock units back in the point blank range for 250 units, dealing 125 extra damage and stunning for 2 seconds.

6483.name: snapfire_firesnap_cookie
6483.desc_loc: Snapfire feeds a potent cookie to Mortimer or an ally, causing them to hop a short distance. The hopping unit stuns and damages enemies in the landing zone.
6483.lore_loc: With the help of a secret mixture that pairs Beadie's baking skills with her passion for black powder, these battle biscuits pack a punch.
notes_loc: The cookie projectile has a speed of %projectile_speed%.

6488.name: snapfire_lil_shredder
6488.desc_loc: Snapfire heats up her mounted turret to rapidly fire %buffed_attacks% fixed-damage attacks. Each attack reduces the enemy's armor. Provides bonus attack range for the duration.
6488.lore_loc: Beadie constantly tinkers with a design she first dreamed up plotting an exodus from her old gang.
notes_loc: Sets %base_attack_time% base attack rate for the duration.
Attack modifiers have a chance to proc on Lil' Shredder attacks.

6484.name: snapfire_gobble_up
6484.desc_loc: Mortimer gobbles up a creep or an allied hero, which he can then spit towards enemies. The unit stays in his belly up to %max_time_in_belly% seconds.
notes_loc: Snapfire earns the creep's bounty after it has been spat out and died.

6486.name: snapfire_spit_creep
6486.desc_loc: Mortimer spits out the unit that's in his mouth, causing impact damage and stun in a large area. The glob leaves a pool of firespit that slows and applies damage over time.

6482.name: snapfire_mortimer_kisses
6482.desc_loc: Snapfire's friend launches a barrage of firespit globs over %duration_tooltip% seconds. Globs cause impact damage and create pools of firespit, which slow and apply damage over time. Snapfire has a reduced turn rate for the duration and a minimum launch range of %min_range%. Each glob can be targeted with a right click.
6482.lore_loc: Little did Beadie know when she adopted Mortimer, dragon toads--which aren't even toads at all--share more than just a name with their distant draconic cousins.
notes_loc: Can be cancelled by pressing Stop, Hold Position, or using another ability.
Has a minimum travel time of %min_lob_travel_time% and maximum travel time of %max_lob_travel_time%.

382.name: special_bonus_unique_snapfire_6
382.name_loc: Lil' Shredder Uses Your Attack Damage

6583.name: mars_spear
6583.desc_loc: Mars throws his legendary Spear with deadly precision, damaging each enemy unit it strikes. The first enemy hero it hits is skewered on the spear, pushing it back. If a skewered hero hits a tree, building, or cliff, they will be impaled to it and stunned.
6583.lore_loc: The legendary Spear of Mars still glows with the heat of the forge god's fires.
notes_loc: Spear of Mars can hit invisible units and reveals them if they are stunned.
Spear of Mars will only pin a units to cliffs onto elevated areas, otherwise it will push them off onto lower ground.
6583.shard_loc: Spear of Mars impales up to two units and leaves a fire trail behind for 10 seconds. Deals 35 damage per second and slows by 20%%. Debuff lingers for 2 seconds.

6495.name: mars_gods_rebuke
6495.desc_loc: Mars smashes enemies in front of him with his shield, knocking them back and damaging them with a critical hit based on his attack. Bonus damage is added when hitting heroes. Has True Strike.
6495.lore_loc: There isn't a warrior alive who can stand unmoved by the sting of Mars' rebuke.
notes_loc: Attack modifiers have a chance to proc on God's Rebuke attacks.

6582.name: mars_bulwark
6582.desc_loc:
Mars wields his massive shield to block a portion of each physical attack when hit from the front or sides.

Can be toggled, removing Mars's ability to attack, and locking the direction he is facing. When active, reduces movement speed and re-directs %redirect_chance%%% of the attack projectiles aimed at Mars's allies towards Mars instead.
6582.lore_loc: Only the very foolish dare to fight fair with the god of war.
6582.scepter_loc: Creates invulnerable soldiers around Mars' front while Bulwark is toggled on. Soldiers move alongside Mars, dealing his full damage +75 and applying procs. Attacks slow enemies by 30% for 1 second. An enemy can only be attacked by one soldier at a time.

6598.name: mars_arena_of_blood
6598.desc_loc: After a short formation time, Mars summons an arena lined with the undead warriors of the Ash Legion, who block enemy attacks and movement. Enemy heroes near the inside edge of the arena will be attacked by spears, dealing damage and knocking them back.
6598.lore_loc: The long-dead members of the Ash Legion, assembled from the finest warriors to ever test the might of Mars, still revel in the thrill of combat, gladly beholden to the hand that fell them for as long as he so commands.

6766.name: special_bonus_unique_mars_arena_of_blood_hp_regen
6766.name_loc: Arena Of Blood Grants Team +{s:value} HP Regen

8429.name: hoodwink_acorn_shot
8429.desc_loc:
Fires Hoodwink's attack with an acorn at the target unit.  The acorn bounces to nearby targets, slowing them and dealing a percentage of Hoodwink's attack with bonus damage.
If point targeted, a tree is created at the target position and the acorn will bounce to nearby targets.  The ability may be placed on auto-cast to force this behavior.
8429.lore_loc: Though she'll make do with almost anything, Oak and Ironwood acorns make the most effective projectiles -- and the bulk of Hoodwink's stash.
notes_loc: The same target can be hit more than once.
Bounces will seek units in the fog of war in a 525 radius, but not invisible units.
The planted tree lasts for 20 seconds.
Acorn Shot benefits from attack range bonuses.

8158.name: hoodwink_bushwhack
8158.desc_loc: Tosses a net trap that stuns enemy heroes if they are near a tree in the area.  Affected enemies take damage and are pulled towards the tree nearest to them, and have their vision reduced to 0 for the duration of the stun.
8158.lore_loc: Hoodwink favors Ironwood groves for ambushes, but the wary step carefully in all areas of the mistwoods.
notes_loc: Units can be freed from the stun by destroying the tree.

9501.name: hoodwink_scurry
9501.desc_loc: Hoodwink passively has a chance to evade physical attacks while near trees.  When activated, Hoodwink gains bonus movement speed, phased collision, and tree-walking for a brief time.
9501.lore_loc: There's not a nook or cranny in the Wood Tomo'kan out of reach of Hoodwink's paws.

8107.name: hoodwink_decoy
8107.desc_loc: Hoodwink sends a decoy illusion to the target location.  When the illusion is attacked or hit by a targeted ability, it is destroyed and plants a tree in its place that applies a lesser Bushwhack to enemy heroes around it.

9627.name: hoodwink_hunters_boomerang
9627.desc_loc: Tosses a boomerang at the target enemy in an arc. Upon contact, it returns to Hoodwink.  The boomerang will deal damage as it passes through or hits enemies, and apply a Hunter's Mark that causes affected enemies to be slowed and be more vulnerable to spell damage and have reduced status resistance.

8106.name: hoodwink_sharpshooter
8106.desc_loc:
Hoodwink charges up and fires a deadly bolt from her crossbow, dealing heavy damage and slow to an enemy Hero.  The damage and debuff duration scale up to max after %max_charge_time% seconds, and the bolt is fired automatically after %misfire_time% seconds.
Hoodwink is knocked backwards for a distance of %recoil_distance% from the force of the shot.
8106.lore_loc: While her first arbalest was a chance discovery, Hoodwink now takes great care in carving and caring for her own -- of course with some necessary components pilfered or otherwise cleverly procured.

9505.name: special_bonus_unique_hoodwink_camouflage
9505.desc_loc: Hoodwink becomes invisible near trees after {s:fade_time} seconds of not moving, attacking, or casting spells.

9507.name: special_bonus_unique_hoodwink_sharpshooter_pure_damage
9507.name_loc: Sharpshooter Pure Damage and Pierces Spell Immunity

7902.name: dawnbreaker_fire_wreath
7902.desc_loc: Dawnbreaker whirls her hammer around 3 times, damaging enemies with her attack plus bonus damage. On the final strike, she smashes her hammer down, stunning and damaging enemies in front of her.
7902.lore_loc: Across the vast lineage of star progeny, there were multitudes unwilling to align with the aims of the Children of Light. To those who dared organize defiance, the Children would dispatch Valora and her hammer to show a measure of their power--to leave the rebels either shattered or set back to rights.
notes_loc: Dawnbreaker travels at a rate of %movement_speed% for the duration of the ability and takes a brief %self_stun_duration%s to recover after the final strike.
Celestial Hammer or Solar Guardian cannot be cast during the combo.
Cleave does not work with this ability.
Can be self-cast to move forward

7914.name: dawnbreaker_celestial_hammer
7914.desc_loc: Dawnbreaker hurls her weapon at a target, damaging enemies struck along the way. The hammer pauses for %pause_duration% seconds at the destination before flying back to her, leaving a trail of fire that slows enemies. Dawnbreaker can recall the hammer at any time, pulling her towards it so they meet in the middle.
7914.lore_loc: The Brightmaul is Valora's oldest companion and sole remaining connection to the glow of her creators.
notes_loc: The hammer damages enemies both when thrown and when returning to Dawnbreaker.
Dawnbreaker's Converge movement distance is capped at the ability's cast range.
Starbreaker or Solar Guardian cannot be cast while the Hammer is out.

7918.name: dawnbreaker_luminosity
7918.desc_loc: After %attack_count% attacks, Dawnbreaker powers up, charging her next attack with a critical hit that heals all allied heroes within %heal_radius% units around her for a portion of attack damage dealt. Creeps and neutral enemies provide less healing. Allies are healed for %allied_healing_pct%%% of the amount.
7918.lore_loc: Diminished in power without access to the Children's replenishing light, Valora can still recharge herself and her allies by creating order from the chaos which resides within each fight.

7906.name: dawnbreaker_solar_guardian
7906.desc_loc: Dawnbreaker creates a pulsing effect at a location within %max_offset_distance% units of an allied hero anywhere on the map, damaging enemies and healing allies with each pulse. After a short duration, she flies to the target location, dealing additional damage and stunning enemies upon landing. Once channeled, Dawnbreaker cannot stop the ability.
7906.lore_loc: Only in defense of an ally will Valora relent to call upon the last reserves of her old powers that still allow cosmic flight.
notes_loc: Pulse interval is %pulse_interval%s.
Total duration flight duration is %abilitychanneltime% seconds of channel time + %airtime_duration% of flight time.
Cannot be cast without the Hammer.
Healing does not affect Dawnbreaker herself.
